{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784650185889,"sessionID":"ses_07a91b76bffeQVZz6UB7PapKuO","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_C0mEn7PW3LNetWxoyvU7LF6Z","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"step_dispatch|cli-opencode|prompt-pack|post_dispatch|phase_synthesis|reduce-state|step_synthesize","path":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-review-auto.yaml"},"output":"Found 100 matches (more matches available)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-model-benchmark-confirm.yaml:\n  Line 105:     reducer: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs\n\n  Line 200:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}/improvement\"\n\n  Line 219:   phase_synthesis:\n\n  Line 223:         description: \"Render the final dashboard via reduce-state and present benchmark trends and stop reason\"\n\n  Line 224:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}/improvement\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-skill-benchmark-auto.yaml:\n  Line 34:   trace_mode: \"[TRACE_MODE] - router (Mode A, deterministic, default/CI) or live (Mode B, playbook corpus dispatched through cli-opencode). Default: router.\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-presentation.txt:\n  Line 39:   executor: native  # native | cli-opencode | cli-claude-code\n\n  Line 40:   executor_model: \"\"  # optional executor-specific model id (cli-opencode e.g. xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro, minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed)\n\n  Line 94:    |-- --executor=<type> -> config.executor.type (`native` | `cli-opencode` | `cli-claude-code`)\n\n  Line 127:    - Invalid combinations fail fast with clear errors, including `cli-opencode` without `--model` and reserved-but-unwired executor kinds\n\n  Line 137:    - Include Q-Exec only when `--executor` is NOT present and the topic text does NOT already mention executor hints such as `cli-opencode`, `cli-claude-code`, or `gpt-5.4`\n\n  Line 157:      B) cli-opencode — `opencode run --model X --format json --dangerously-skip-permissions --pure --dir {repo_root} [--variant Y] \"PROMPT\" </dev/null` (no `--agent`: current opencode rejects top-level `--agent general` — default agent runs; required for MiniMax/Xiaomi token-plan models). `reasoningEffort` maps to `--variant`. No service-tier.\n\n  Line 319: # Fan-out: two CLI lineages in parallel (cli-opencode + cli-claude-code)\n\n  Line 321:   --executor=cli-opencode --model=o4-mini --label= \\\n\n  Line 328:   --executor=cli-opencode --model=o4-mini --count=2 \\\n\n  Line 333:   --executors='[{\"kind\":\"cli-opencode\",\"model\":\"o4-mini\",\"label\":\"\",\"count\":3},{\"kind\":\"cli-claude-code\",\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-8\",\"label\":\"claude\",\"count\":2}]' \\\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-review-presentation.txt:\n  Line 43:   executor: native  # one of: native | cli-opencode | cli-claude-code\n\n  Line 44:   executor_model: \"\"  # optional, executor-specific (cli-opencode e.g. xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro, minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed)\n\n  Line 86: **Fan-out default policy:** 0–1 `--executor` flags and no `--executors` → `config.executor` (single-executor, default, unchanged). 2+ `--executor` flags, `--executors`, or any `--count > 1` → `config.fanout`. Review fan-out uses strongest-restriction: any lineage active P0 → merged FAIL. Native and CLI fan-out lineages run under `fanout-run.cjs` in the capped pool so every lineage shares retries, artifact checks, and stop-policy validation. The native adapter calls the `deep/review` command with the internal `--fanout-lineage-artifact-dir` override; it must not dispatch the LEAF `@deep-review` agent or a pasted phase-running prompt as a full-loop sub-agent. When fan-out includes `cli-opencode`, that lineage is an explicit parallel-detached OpenCode session with its own lineage directory and session id; this is the documented exception to the cli-opencode self-invocation guard. Single-executor `cli-opencode` remains cross-runtime only.\n\n  Line 119:    |-- --executor=<type> -> config.executor.type (`native` | `cli-opencode` | `cli-claude-code`)\n\n  Line 154:    - Invalid combinations fail fast with clear errors, including `cli-opencode` without `--model` and reserved-but-unwired executor kinds\n\n  Line 164:    - Include Q-Exec only when `--executor` is NOT present and the target text does NOT already mention executor hints such as `cli-opencode`, ``, or `gpt-5.4`\n\n  Line 196:      B) cli-opencode — `opencode run --model X --format json --dangerously-skip-permissions --pure --dir {repo_root} [--variant Y] \"PROMPT\" </dev/null` (no `--agent`: current opencode rejects top-level `--agent general` — default agent runs; required for MiniMax/Xiaomi token-plan models). `reasoningEffort` maps to `--variant`. No service-tier.\n\n  Line 432:   --executor=cli-opencode --model=o4-mini --label= \\\n\n  Line 439:   --executor=cli-opencode --model=o4-mini --count=2 \\\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-agent-improvement-confirm.yaml:\n  Line 100:     reducer: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs\n\n  Line 270:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}/improvement\"\n\n  Line 292:   phase_synthesis:\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-alignment-auto.yaml:\n  Line 42:   # is not read from here. `cli-opencode` / `cli-claude-code` stay reserved and unwired\n\n  Line 197:           skip_to: phase_synthesis\n\n  Line 352:       step_dispatch_alignment_iteration:\n\n  Line 358:           note: \"This mode resolves only native and cli-codex single executors. There is no if_cli_opencode branch here (the self-invocation guard makes a single-executor cli-opencode dispatch from this surface invalid), and fan-out is a separate parallel path this step never touches.\"\n\n  Line 360:           template_path: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-alignment/assets/alignment-prompt-pack.md.tmpl\"\n\n  Line 361:           renderer: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n\n  Line 501:             - \"No if_cli_opencode single-executor branch exists here by design; the cli-opencode self-invocation guard makes it invalid from this surface, and parallel cli-codex/cli-opencode fan-out is a separate path this step never touches\"\n\n  Line 541:         if_converged: { proceed_to: phase_synthesis }\n\n  Line 542:         if_stop_max_iterations: { log: \"Max iterations ({max_iterations}) reached without full convergence; proceeding to synthesis with current coverage/stability as recorded evidence.\", proceed_to: phase_synthesis }\n\n  Line 543:         if_nothing_to_converge: { log: \"Zero applicable lanes (every lane discovered zero artifacts, or none resolved) -- nothing to converge. Proceeding to synthesis.\", proceed_to: phase_synthesis }\n\n  Line 549:   phase_synthesis:\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep-alignment.contract.md:\n  Line 398:   - \"Native and CLI executors must produce only the required prompt-pack artifacts inside the resolved boundary.\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-auto.yaml:\n  Line 116:   # post_dispatch_validate step enforces the canonical type below.\n\n  Line 157:       After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n\n  Line 159:       phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n\n  Line 772:               step_dispatch_pivot_seat_001:\n\n  Line 805:               step_dispatch_pivot_seat_002:\n\n  Line 838:               step_dispatch_pivot_seat_003:\n\n  Line 897:                   command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n\n  Line 902:                   skip_to: phase_synthesis\n\n  Line 905:               skip_to: phase_synthesis\n\n  Line 908:             skip_to: phase_synthesis\n\n  Line 1008:       step_dispatch_iteration:\n\n  Line 1023:             template_path: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/assets/prompt-pack-iteration.md.tmpl\"\n\n  Line 1024:             renderer: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n\n  Line 1140:               kind: 'cli-opencode',\n\n  Line 1203:             - \"input:'' yields closed stdin (EOF), equivalent to </dev/null — opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup and hangs at 0% CPU after +60s snapshot prune without it (the `cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §4 ALWAYS rule)\"\n\n  Line 1207:             - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude Code/raw shell). the `cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n\n  Line 1284:         post_dispatch_validate:\n\n  Line 1310:             redispatch_once: \"On the FIRST failure of the mechanical command check for this iteration, re-run step_dispatch_iteration exactly once for the same iteration number, then re-run the check. If it still fails, record the iteration as error and continue. Never re-dispatch a given iteration more than once.\"\n\n  Line 1374:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}\"\n\n  Line 1427:           - \"Update memory_context_prompt_line with a concise summary for the next step_dispatch_iteration.pre_dispatch.generate_summary.\"\n\n  Line 1553:   phase_synthesis:\n\n  Line 1596:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} --emit-resource-map\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-review-auto.yaml:\n  Line 171:       A cli-opencode lineage inside this fan-out is an explicit parallel-detached OpenCode\n\n  Line 179:       After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n\n  Line 181:       phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n\n  Line 313:           skip_to: phase_synthesis\n\n  Line 780:               step_dispatch_pivot_seat_001:\n\n  Line 813:               step_dispatch_pivot_seat_002:\n\n  Line 846:               step_dispatch_pivot_seat_003:\n\n  Line 905:                   command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} {reducer_artifact_arg} --create-missing-anchors\"\n\n  Line 910:                   skip_to: phase_synthesis\n\n  Line 913:               skip_to: phase_synthesis\n\n  Line 916:             skip_to: phase_synthesis\n\n  Line 985:       step_dispatch_iteration:\n\n  Line 1004:             template_path: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/prompt-pack-iteration.md.tmpl\"\n\n  Line 1005:             renderer: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n\n  Line 1230:               kind: 'cli-opencode',\n\n  Line 1241:               throw new Error('Unsafe cli-opencode dispatch: rendered prompt is missing required write-containment sections');\n\n  Line 1248:               throw new Error('Unsafe cli-opencode dispatch: artifact directory must be a strict descendant of the worktree root');\n\n  Line 1259:               throw new Error('Unsafe cli-opencode dispatch: --dir must point at an isolated linked worktree');\n\n  Line 1267:               throw new Error('Unsafe cli-opencode dispatch: primary main/master worktree could not be resolved');\n\n  Line 1272:               throw new Error('Unsafe cli-opencode dispatch: primary worktree must be clean before unrestricted execution');\n\n  Line 1284:               throw new Error(`Unsafe cli-opencode dispatch: worktree changes outside the artifact directory: ${outsideArtifactDir.join(', ')}`);\n\n  Line 1347:             - \"input:'' yields closed stdin (EOF), equivalent to </dev/null — opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup and hangs at 0% CPU after +60s snapshot prune without it (the `cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §4 ALWAYS rule)\"\n\n  Line 1351:             - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this single-executor branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude Code/raw shell). Explicit parallel-detached cli-opencode fan-out is handled by step_fanout_spawn_cli/fanout-run.cjs, not this branch. the `cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n\n  Line 1428:         post_dispatch_validate:\n\n  Line 1474:             redispatch_once: \"On the FIRST failure of the mechanical command check for this iteration, re-run step_dispatch_iteration exactly once for the same iteration number, then re-run the check. If it still fails, record the iteration as error (per step_evaluate_results.on_missing_outputs) and continue. Never re-dispatch a given iteration more than once.\"\n\n  Line 1539:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} {reducer_artifact_arg} --create-missing-anchors\"\n\n  Line 1647:   phase_synthesis:\n\n  Line 1751:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} {reducer_artifact_arg} --create-missing-anchors --emit-resource-map\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-model-benchmark-auto.yaml:\n  Line 100:     reducer: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs\n\n  Line 178:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}/improvement\"\n\n  Line 186:   phase_synthesis:\n\n  Line 190:         description: \"Render the final dashboard via reduce-state and present benchmark trends and stop reason\"\n\n  Line 191:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder}/improvement\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-research-confirm.yaml:\n  Line 171:       After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n\n  Line 173:       phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n\n  Line 670:            