{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784650212506,"sessionID":"ses_07a91b76bffeQVZz6UB7PapKuO","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_sbxCOmz1XPhH6eo6gVVJwjqV","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/specs/sk-design/017-remediation-program-review/review/lineages/gpt-56-sol-high"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/specs/sk-design/017-remediation-program-review/review/lineages/gpt-56-sol-high</path>\n<type>directory</type>\n<entries>\n.executor-state/\n\n(1 entries)\n</entries>","metadata":{"preview":".executor-state/","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"directory","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/specs/sk-design/017-remediation-program-review/review/lineages/gpt-56-sol-high","entries":[".executor-state/"],"offset":1,"totalEntries":1,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/017-remediation-program-review/review/lineages/gpt-56-sol-high","time":{"start":1784650212450,"end":1784650212497}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03f0e82d94f6d585016a5f99e44d1881918c8af3d40dce25df"}},"id":"prt_f8571245d001vrLqs9FUgBsabS","sessionID":"ses_07a91b76bffeQVZz6UB7PapKuO","messageID":"msg_f8570c374001ieeOYdHuun9tY9"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784650212568,"sessionID":"ses_07a91b76bffeQVZz6UB7PapKuO","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_adL2wRx21XnqcH4w8NodzdVG","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep-review-strategy.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep-review-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Review Strategy Template\n3: description: Runtime template copied to review/ during initialization to track review progress, dimension coverage, findings, and outcomes across iterations.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep review strategy template\"\n6:   - \"review dimension tracking\"\n7:   - \"exhausted review approaches\"\n8:   - \"review session tracking\"\n9: importance_tier: normal\n10: contextType: planning\n11: version: 1.11.0.13\n12: ---\n13: \n14: # Deep Review Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n15: \n16: Runtime template copied into the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` during initialization. Tracks review progress across iterations.\n17: \n18: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n19: \n20: ### Purpose\n21: \n22: Serves as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep review session. Records which dimensions remain, what was found (P0/P1/P2), what review approaches worked or failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n23: \n24: ### Usage\n25: \n26: - **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Review Dimensions, Known Context, and Review Boundaries from config and memory context.\n27: - **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, reviews the assigned dimension/files, updates findings, marks dimensions complete, and sets new Next Focus.\n28: - **Mutability:** Mutable, updated by both orchestrator and agents throughout the session.\n29: - **Protection:** None (shared mutable state). Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n30: - **Ownership:** Machine-managed metrics and coverage blocks are wrapped in explicit ownership markers. Human commentary and operator overrides live outside those markers.\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n34: ## 2. TOPIC\n35: [Review target description from config -- set during initialization]\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ## 3. REVIEW DIMENSIONS (remaining)\n40: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n41: - [ ] D1 Correctness, Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants\n42: - [ ] D2 Security, Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization\n43: - [ ] D3 Traceability, Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity\n44: - [ ] D4 Maintainability, Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, safe follow-on change cost\n45: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n50: [What this review session is NOT trying to assess -- populated during initialization]\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n55: [Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## 6. COMPLETED DIMENSIONS\n60: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n61: [None yet -- populated as iterations complete dimension reviews]\n62: \n63: | Dimension | Verdict | Iteration | Summary |\n64: |-----------|---------|-----------|---------|\n65: | [D1 Correctness] | [PASS/CONDITIONAL/FAIL] | [N] | [1-sentence result] |\n66: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n67: \n68: ---\n69: \n70: ## 7. RUNNING FINDINGS\n71: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n72: - **P0 (Critical):** 0 active\n73: - **P1 (Major):** 0 active\n74: - **P2 (Minor):** 0 active\n75: - **Delta this iteration:** +0 P0, +0 P1, +0 P2\n76: \n77: [Findings are tracked in `deep-review-findings-registry.json`. This section provides a running count summary updated after each iteration.]\n78: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: ## 8. WHAT WORKED\n83: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n84: - [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ## 9. WHAT FAILED\n89: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n90: - [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n91: \n92: ---\n93: \n94: ## 10. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n95: [Populated when a review approach has been tried from multiple angles without yielding new findings]\n96: \n97: ### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n98: - What was tried: [specific review approaches attempted]\n99: - Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n100: - Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n101: \n102: ### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n103: - What worked: [successful review approaches in this category]\n104: - Prefer for: [related dimensions where this category may help]\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ## 10A. SATURATED / SWEPT DIMENSIONS AND EXPANSION FRONTIER\n109: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n110: - Completed pivots: 0\n111: - Failed pivots: 0\n112: - Audited overrides: 0\n113: - Swept: none yet\n114: - Pivot lineage: none yet\n115: - Remaining frontier: none recorded\n116: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n117: \n118: ---\n119: \n120: ## 11. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n121: [Review angles that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n122: - [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: ## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n127: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n128: [Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration. Includes target dimension and/or specific files to review.]\n129: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n130: \n131: ---\n132: \n133: ## 13. KNOWN CONTEXT\n134: [Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n135: \n136: ### Bounded Context Snapshot\n137: \n138: Populate during initialization before the first review dimension runs. Keep this pointer-based and scoped to the declared review target:\n139: \n140: - Target pointers: files, specs, symbols, or resource-map entries under review.\n141: - Behavior claims: acceptance criteria, public contracts, or docs to verify.\n142: - Reuse and conventions: existing patterns that define expected implementation shape.\n143: - Review risks and gaps: stale graph or memory caveats, missing files, and out-of-scope areas.\n144: \n145: Do not inline full source bodies. Do not dispatch the retired standalone context loop. Use this snapshot only to seed review dimensions and final traceability.\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: ## 14. CROSS-REFERENCE STATUS\n150: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n151: [Alignment checks completed across core and overlay protocols]\n152: \n153: | Protocol | Level | Status | Iteration | Notes |\n154: |----------|-------|--------|-----------|-------|\n155: | `spec_code` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n156: | `checklist_evidence` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n157: | `skill_agent` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n158: | `agent_cross_runtime` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n159: | `feature_catalog_code` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n160: | `playbook_capability` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n161: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n162: \n163: ---\n164: \n165: ## 15. FILES UNDER REVIEW\n166: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n167: [Per-file coverage state table -- populated during initialization from scope discovery]\n168: \n169: | File | Dimensions Reviewed | Last Iteration | Findings | Status |\n170: |------|-------------------|----------------|----------|--------|\n171: | [path/to/file] | [D1, D3] | [N] | [0 P0, 1 P1, 2 P2] | [partial/complete] |\n172: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n173: \n174: ---\n175: \n176: ## 16. REVIEW BOUNDARIES\n177: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n178: - Max iterations: [from config]\n179: - Convergence threshold: [from config]\n180: - Rolling STOP threshold: 0.08\n181: - No-progress threshold: 0.05\n182: - Coverage stabilization passes required: 1\n183: - Session lineage: sessionId=[from config.sessionId], parentSessionId=[from config.parentSessionId], generation=[from config.generation], lineageMode=[from config.lineageMode]\n184: - Findings registry: `deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n185: - Release-readiness states: in-progress | converged | release-blocking\n186: - Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n187: - Severity threshold: [from config.severityThreshold]\n188: - Review target type: [from config.reviewTargetType]\n189: - Cross-reference checks: core=[from config.crossReference.core], overlay=[from config.crossReference.overlay]\n190: - Started: [timestamp]\n191: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n192: \n193: ---\n194: \n195: ## 17. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n196: \n197: Reference snippet showing a partially populated strategy file mid-review. Use this as a visual anchor when opening a live strategy doc.\n198: \n199: ```markdown\n200: ## 1. REVIEW CHARTER\n201: - Target: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research (skill, v1.4.0)\n202: - Dimensions: correctness, test-coverage, cross-runtime-parity, observability\n203: - Stop conditions: rolling newInfoRatio < 0.08 for 2 iterations OR all dimensions converged OR max=7 reached\n204: - Success criteria: zero P0 in correctness; test-coverage P0 resolved or deferred with rationale\n205: \n206: ## 4. NEXT FOCUS\n207: - Dimension: test-coverage\n208: - Files: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs, .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/deep-research-contract-parity.vitest.ts\n209: - Why: Iteration 2 surfaced a P0 (convergence-path coverage gap); needs a focused follow-up before correctness can terminate PASS.\n210: \n211: ## 9. COVERAGE MATRIX\n212: | Dimension            | Status     | Iterations touched |\n213: |----------------------|------------|--------------------|\n214: | correctness          | converged  | 1                  |\n215: | test-coverage        | converging | 2, 4               |\n216: | cross-runtime-parity | converging | 3                  |\n217: | observability        | converging | 4                  |\n218: ```\n\n(End of file - total 218 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to review/ during initialization to track review progress, dimension coverage, findings, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review strategy template\"\n  - \"review dimension tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted review approaches\"\n  - \"review session tracking\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\nversion: 1.11.0.13\n---\n\n# Deep Review Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied into the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` during initialization. Tracks review progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep-review-strategy.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to review/ during initialization to track review progress, dimension coverage, findings, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep review strategy template\"\n  - \"review dimension tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted review approaches\"\n  - \"review session tracking\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\nversion: 1.11.0.13\n---\n\n# Deep Review Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied into the resolved `{artifact_dir}/` during initialization. Tracks review progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nServes as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep review session. Records which dimensions remain, what was found (P0/P1/P2), what review approaches worked or failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n\n### Usage\n\n- **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Review Dimensions, Known Context, and Review Boundaries from config and memory context.\n- **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, reviews the assigned dimension/files, updates findings, marks dimensions complete, and sets new Next Focus.\n- **Mutability:** Mutable, updated by both orchestrator and agents throughout the session.\n- **Protection:** None (shared mutable state). Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n- **Ownership:** Machine-managed metrics and coverage blocks are wrapped in explicit ownership markers. Human commentary and operator overrides live outside those markers.\n\n---\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n[Review target description from config -- set during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 3. REVIEW DIMENSIONS (remaining)\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- [ ] D1 Correctness, Logic errors, off-by-one, wrong return types, broken invariants\n- [ ] D2 Security, Injection, auth bypass, secrets exposure, unsafe deserialization\n- [ ] D3 Traceability, Spec/code alignment, checklist evidence, cross-reference integrity\n- [ ] D4 Maintainability, Patterns, clarity, documentation quality, safe follow-on change cost\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n[What this review session is NOT trying to assess -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n[Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 6. COMPLETED DIMENSIONS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[None yet -- populated as iterations complete dimension reviews]\n\n| Dimension | Verdict | Iteration | Summary |\n|-----------|---------|-----------|---------|\n| [D1 Correctness] | [PASS/CONDITIONAL/FAIL] | [N] | [1-sentence result] |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 7. RUNNING FINDINGS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- **P0 (Critical):** 0 active\n- **P1 (Major):** 0 active\n- **P2 (Minor):** 0 active\n- **Delta this iteration:** +0 P0, +0 P1, +0 P2\n\n[Findings are tracked in `deep-review-findings-registry.json`. This section provides a running count summary updated after each iteration.]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 8. WHAT WORKED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n\n---\n\n## 9. WHAT FAILED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n\n---\n\n## 10. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n[Populated when a review approach has been tried from multiple angles without yielding new findings]\n\n### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n- What was tried: [specific review approaches attempted]\n- Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n- Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n\n### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n- What worked: [successful review approaches in this category]\n- Prefer for: [related dimensions where this category may help]\n\n---\n\n## 10A. SATURATED / SWEPT DIMENSIONS AND EXPANSION FRONTIER\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Completed pivots: 0\n- Failed pivots: 0\n- Audited overrides: 0\n- Swept: none yet\n- Pivot lineage: none yet\n- Remaining frontier: none recorded\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 11. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n[Review angles that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n- [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n\n---\n\n## 12. NEXT FOCUS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration. Includes target dimension and/or specific files to review.]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 13. KNOWN CONTEXT\n[Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n\n### Bounded Context Snapshot\n\nPopulate during initialization before the first review dimension runs. Keep this pointer-based and scoped to the declared review target:\n\n- Target pointers: files, specs, symbols, or resource-map entries under review.\n- Behavior claims: acceptance criteria, public contracts, or docs to verify.\n- Reuse and conventions: existing patterns that define expected implementation shape.\n- Review risks and gaps: stale graph or memory caveats, missing files, and out-of-scope areas.\n\nDo not inline full source bodies. Do not dispatch the retired standalone context loop. Use this snapshot only to seed review dimensions and final traceability.\n\n---\n\n## 14. CROSS-REFERENCE STATUS\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[Alignment checks completed across core and overlay protocols]\n\n| Protocol | Level | Status | Iteration | Notes |\n|----------|-------|--------|-----------|-------|\n| `spec_code` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n| `checklist_evidence` | core | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked] | [N] | [details] |\n| `skill_agent` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n| `agent_cross_runtime` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n| `feature_catalog_code` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n| `playbook_capability` | overlay | [pending/pass/partial/fail/blocked/notApplicable] | [N] | [details] |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 15. FILES UNDER REVIEW\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n[Per-file coverage state table -- populated during initialization from scope discovery]\n\n| File | Dimensions Reviewed | Last Iteration | Findings | Status |\n|------|-------------------|----------------|----------|--------|\n| [path/to/file] | [D1, D3] | [N] | [0 P0, 1 P1, 2 P2] | [partial/complete] |\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 16. REVIEW BOUNDARIES\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n- Max iterations: [from config]\n- Convergence threshold: [from config]\n- Rolling STOP threshold: 0.08\n- No-progress threshold: 0.05\n- Coverage stabilization passes required: 1\n- Session lineage: sessionId=[from config.sessionId], parentSessionId=[from config.parentSessionId], generation=[from config.generation], lineageMode=[from config.lineageMode]\n- Findings registry: `deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n- Release-readiness states: in-progress | converged | release-blocking\n- Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n- Severity threshold: [from config.severityThreshold]\n- Review target type: [from config.reviewTargetType]\n- Cross-reference checks: core=[from config.crossReference.core], overlay=[from config.crossReference.overlay]\n- Started: [timestamp]\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 17. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n\nReference snippet showing a partially populated strategy file mid-review. Use this as a visual anchor when opening a live strategy doc.\n\n```markdown\n## 1. REVIEW CHARTER\n- Target: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research (skill, v1.4.0)\n- Dimensions: correctness, test-coverage, cross-runtime-parity, observability\n- Stop conditions: rolling newInfoRatio < 0.08 for 2 iterations OR all dimensions converged OR max=7 reached\n- Success criteria: zero P0 in correctness; test-coverage P0 resolved or deferred with rationale\n\n## 4. NEXT FOCUS\n- Dimension: test-coverage\n- Files: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs, .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/tests/deep-research-contract-parity.vitest.ts\n- Why: Iteration 2 surfaced a P0 (convergence-path coverage gap); needs a focused follow-up before correctness can terminate PASS.\n\n## 9. COVERAGE MATRIX\n| Dimension            | Status     | Iterations touched |\n|----------------------|------------|--------------------|\n| correctness          | converged  | 1                  |\n| test-coverage        | converging | 2, 4               |\n| cross-runtime-parity | converging | 3                  |\n| observability        | converging | 4                  |\n```","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":218,"totalLines":218,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/deep-review-strategy.md","time":{"start":1784650212461,"end":1784650212564}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03f0e82d94f6d585016a5f99e44d248191b5b9cb424921c671"}},"id":"prt_f8571246a001VP2HESKQJ0uGiz","sessionID":"ses_07a91b76bffeQVZz6UB7PapKuO","messageID":"msg_f8570c374001ieeOYdHuun9tY9"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784650212596,"sessionID":"ses_07a91b76bffeQVZz6UB7PapKuO","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_wQdTaPA0IycHol8m6J54X6CG","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Review Core Doctrine\n3: description: Shared findings-first review doctrine for both single-pass and deep-review workflows.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"findings first severity ordering\"\n6:   - \"review finding schema\"\n7:   - \"severity contract for merge decisions\"\n8:   - \"evidence file line citation\"\n9:   - \"baseline surface precedence\"\n10:   - \"baseline check families\"\n11: importance_tier: important\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: version: 1.5.0.11\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Review Core Doctrine\n17: \n18: Shared doctrine consumed by both `@review` and `@deep-review`.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: Shared findings-first review doctrine for both single-pass and deep-review workflows.\n25: \n26: ---\n27: \n28: ## 2. SEVERITY DEFINITIONS\n29: \n30: | Level | Meaning | Handling |\n31: | --- | --- | --- |\n32: | P0 | Blocker: exploitable security issue, auth bypass, destructive data loss | Block merge |\n33: | P1 | Required: correctness bug, spec mismatch, must-fix gate issue | Fix before merge |\n34: | P2 | Suggestion: non-blocking improvement, documentation polish, style or maintainability follow-up | Optional or schedule follow-up |\n35: \n36: Escalation rule: if confidence is low but impact is high, classify toward the higher severity and state the uncertainty explicitly.\n37: \n38: ### Numeric Severity Calibration\n39: \n40: Numeric scores are advisory context, not the gate. A reviewer may add an optional `riskScore` to a finding and adjust it by `+/-2` for local context such as exploitability, blast radius, user impact, confidence, or proven containment. The merge/block decision remains the severity contract above: `P0` blocks, `P1` requires remediation, and `P2` is advisory. Do not adopt `score>=4` or any numeric threshold as a blocker.\n41: \n42: ---\n43: \n44: ## 3. EVIDENCE REQUIREMENTS\n45: \n46: - Every `P0` and `P1` finding must include a concrete `file:line` citation.\n47: - Evidence must tie the finding to observed code behavior, not just a general concern.\n48: - `P2` findings should still include specific evidence when available, even if impact is advisory.\n49: - If evidence is incomplete, state the assumption and why the risk still matters.\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ## 4. FINDINGS OUTPUT ORDERING\n54: \n55: - Present findings before summary or praise sections.\n56: - Order findings by severity first: `P0`, then `P1`, then `P2`.\n57: - Keep ordering stable within a severity bucket by impact and confidence.\n58: - Separate required fixes from optional suggestions so merge decisions stay clear.\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ## 5. BASELINE + SURFACE PRECEDENCE\n63: \n64: Apply this skill as the baseline first, then pair it with `sk-code` surface evidence when available:\n65: \n66: - Detected code surface -> `sk-code:code-webflow` or `sk-code:code-opencode`; unsupported or unclear surfaces -> `sk-code:unknown`\n67: - Unclear surfaces -> baseline-only plus explicit uncertainty\n68: \n69: Precedence rules:\n70: \n71: - Baseline security and correctness minimums are always enforced.\n72: - Surface style, process, build, and test conventions override generic baseline guidance.\n73: - Unclear conflicts must be escalated rather than guessed.\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## 6. BASELINE CHECK FAMILIES\n78: \n79: Mandatory baseline families:\n80: \n81: - Correctness minimums: regression risk, contract safety, spec mismatch, destructive side effects, and boundary handling.\n82: - Security minimums: auth and authorization gaps, injection exposure, unsafe secrets handling, privilege misuse, and reliability risks with security impact.\n83: \n84: These minimums cannot be relaxed by surface guidance.\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ## 7. FINDING SCHEMA\n89: \n90: Each finding should provide:\n91: \n92: | Field | Requirement |\n93: | --- | --- |\n94: | `id` | Stable label within the review report, such as `P1-001` |\n95: | `severity` | One of `P0`, `P1`, `P2` |\n96: | `title` | Short, risk-oriented summary |\n97: | `file` | Primary `path:line` location |\n98: | `evidence` | Plain-language explanation tied to observed code |\n99: | `findingClass` | One of `instance-only`, `class-of-bug`, `cross-consumer`, `algorithmic`, `matrix/evidence`, or `test-isolation` |\n100: | `scopeProof` | Grep/test/audit evidence that the recommendation covers same-class sites and consumers, or proves the finding is instance-only |\n101: | `affectedSurfaceHints` | Optional string array of producer/consumer surfaces the fix should address; recommended for actionable findings, required for cross-consumer findings. Use free-form short strings, max about 5 entries. Optional for instance-only findings. |\n102: | `riskScore` | Optional advisory number for relative risk calibration; never gating and never a substitute for `severity` |\n103: | `recommendation` | Specific, scope-proportional fix or follow-up |\n104: \n105: Suggested shape:\n106: \n107: ```markdown\n108: ### P1-001 [P1] Missing authorization check\n109: - File: path/to/file.ts:42\n110: - Evidence: Request handling reaches the write path before role validation.\n111: - Finding class: cross-consumer\n112: - Scope proof: `rg -n \"permission guard|write path\" path/to` shows the write handler is the only unchecked consumer.\n113: - Affected surface hints: [\"request handler\", \"write path\", \"permission guard\"]\n114: - riskScore: 6 (advisory only)\n115: - Recommendation: Enforce the existing permission guard before mutation.\n116: ```\n117: \n118: ---\n119: \n120: ## 8. RELATED RESOURCES\n121: \n122: - [review-ux-single-pass.md](./review-ux-single-pass.md) - Interactive single-pass report flow and next-step prompts.\n123: - [quick-reference.md](./quick-reference.md) - Lightweight index across baseline review references.\n124: - [security-checklist.md](../assets/security-checklist.md) - Security and reliability checks.\n125: - [code-quality-checklist.md](../assets/code-quality-checklist.md) - Correctness, KISS, DRY, and maintainability checks.\n126: \n127: ---\n\n(End of file - total 127 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Review Core Doctrine\ndescription: Shared findings-first review doctrine for both single-pass and deep-review workflows.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"findings first severity ordering\"\n  - \"review finding schema\"\n  - \"severity contract for merge decisions\"\n  - \"evidence file line citation\"\n  - \"baseline surface precedence\"\n  - \"baseline check families\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.5.0.11\n---\n\n# Review Core Doctrine\n\nShared doctrine consumed by both `@review` and `@deep-review`.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md","text":"---\ntitle: Review Core Doctrine\ndescription: Shared findings-first review doctrine for both single-pass and deep-review workflows.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"findings first severity ordering\"\n  - \"review finding schema\"\n  - \"severity contract for merge decisions\"\n  - \"evidence file line citation\"\n  - \"baseline surface precedence\"\n  - \"baseline check families\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.5.0.11\n---\n\n# Review Core Doctrine\n\nShared doctrine consumed by both `@review` and `@deep-review`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nShared findings-first review doctrine for both single-pass and deep-review workflows.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SEVERITY DEFINITIONS\n\n| Level | Meaning | Handling |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| P0 | Blocker: exploitable security issue, auth bypass, destructive data loss | Block merge |\n| P1 | Required: correctness bug, spec mismatch, must-fix gate issue | Fix before merge |\n| P2 | Suggestion: non-blocking improvement, documentation polish, style or maintainability follow-up | Optional or schedule follow-up |\n\nEscalation rule: if confidence is low but impact is high, classify toward the higher severity and state the uncertainty explicitly.\n\n### Numeric Severity Calibration\n\nNumeric scores are advisory context, not the gate. A reviewer may add an optional `riskScore` to a finding and adjust it by `+/-2` for local context such as exploitability, blast radius, user impact, confidence, or proven containment. The merge/block decision remains the severity contract above: `P0` blocks, `P1` requires remediation, and `P2` is advisory. Do not adopt `score>=4` or any numeric threshold as a blocker.\n\n---\n\n## 3. EVIDENCE REQUIREMENTS\n\n- Every `P0` and `P1` finding must include a concrete `file:line` citation.\n- Evidence must tie the finding to observed code behavior, not just a general concern.\n- `P2` findings should still include specific evidence when available, even if impact is advisory.\n- If evidence is incomplete, state the assumption and why the risk still matters.\n\n---\n\n## 4. FINDINGS OUTPUT ORDERING\n\n- Present findings before summary or praise sections.\n- Order findings by severity first: `P0`, then `P1`, then `P2`.\n- Keep ordering stable within a severity bucket by impact and confidence.\n- Separate required fixes from optional suggestions so merge decisions stay clear.\n\n---\n\n## 5. BASELINE + SURFACE PRECEDENCE\n\nApply this skill as the baseline first, then pair it with `sk-code` surface evidence when available:\n\n- Detected code surface -> `sk-code:code-webflow` or `sk-code:code-opencode`; unsupported or unclear surfaces -> `sk-code:unknown`\n- Unclear surfaces -> baseline-only plus explicit uncertainty\n\nPrecedence rules:\n\n- Baseline security and correctness minimums are always enforced.\n- Surface style, process, build, and test conventions override generic baseline guidance.\n- Unclear conflicts must be escalated rather than guessed.\n\n---\n\n## 6. BASELINE CHECK FAMILIES\n\nMandatory baseline families:\n\n- Correctness minimums: regression risk, contract safety, spec mismatch, destructive side effects, and boundary handling.\n- Security minimums: auth and authorization gaps, injection exposure, unsafe secrets handling, privilege misuse, and reliability risks with security impact.\n\nThese minimums cannot be relaxed by surface guidance.\n\n---\n\n## 7. FINDING SCHEMA\n\nEach finding should provide:\n\n| Field | Requirement |\n| --- | --- |\n| `id` | Stable label within the review report, such as `P1-001` |\n| `severity` | One of `P0`, `P1`, `P2` |\n| `title` | Short, risk-oriented summary |\n| `file` | Primary `path:line` location |\n| `evidence` | Plain-language explanation tied to observed code |\n| `findingClass` | One of `instance-only`, `class-of-bug`, `cross-consumer`, `algorithmic`, `matrix/evidence`, or `test-isolation` |\n| `scopeProof` | Grep/test/audit evidence that the recommendation covers same-class sites and consumers, or proves the finding is instance-only |\n| `affectedSurfaceHints` | Optional string array of producer/consumer surfaces the fix should address; recommended for actionable findings, required for cross-consumer findings. Use free-form short strings, max about 5 entries. Optional for instance-only findings. |\n| `riskScore` | Optional advisory number for relative risk calibration; never gating and never a substitute for `severity` |\n| `recommendation` | Specific, scope-proportional fix or follow-up |\n\nSuggested shape:\n\n```markdown\n### P1-001 [P1] Missing authorization check\n- File: path/to/file.ts:42\n- Evidence: Request handling reaches the write path before role validation.\n- Finding class: cross-consumer\n- Scope proof: `rg -n \"permission guard|write path\" path/to` shows the write handler is the only unchecked consumer.\n- Affected surface hints: [\"request handler\", \"write path\", \"permission guard\"]\n- riskScore: 6 (advisory only)\n- Recommendation: Enforce the existing permission guard before mutation.\n```\n\n---\n\n## 8. RELATED RESOURCES\n\n- [review-ux-single-pass.md](./review-ux-single-pass.md) - Interactive single-pass report flow and next-step prompts.\n- [quick-reference.md](./quick-reference.md) - Lightweight index across baseline review references.\n- [security-checklist.md](../assets/security-checklist.md) - Security and reliability checks.\n- [code-quality-checklist.md](../assets/code-quality-checklist.md) - Correctness, KISS, DRY, and maintainability checks.\n\n---","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":127,"totalLines":127,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md","time":{"start":1784650212472,"end":1784650212579}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03f0e82d94f6d585016a5f99e44d30819181d6f76e1eb28b93"}},"id":"prt_f85712475001B3O7deNG8tULqh","sessionID":"ses_07a91b76bffeQVZz6UB7PapKuO","messageID":"msg_f8570c374001ieeOYdHuun9tY9"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784650212596,"sessionID":"ses_07a91b76bffeQVZz6UB7PapKuO","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_bLTrgS8CTsIcOoYZqwBqTqFu","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/review-mode-contract.yaml"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/review-mode-contract.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Canonical review-mode contract for deep-review.\n2: # This file is the single source of truth for review-mode taxonomy,\n3: # convergence settings, cross-reference protocols, downstream render targets,\n4: # and validation expectations.\n5: \n6: meta:\n7:   ownerSkill: deep-review\n8:   reviewModeVersion: 2\n9:   generatedNotice:\n10:     warning: \"Exactly one artifact is machine-generated from this file: render.artifacts[0] (review-contract-snapshot). Its begin/end markers live on that artifact entry, not here. Every other contract-taxonomy consumer is hand-authored; see authoredArtifacts.\"\n11:   sourceOfTruth: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/review-mode-contract.yaml\n12: \n13: # Core contract definitions consumed by workflows, agents, docs, and validators.\n14: contract:\n15:   defaultTargetType: spec-folder\n16: \n17:   contextSnapshot:\n18:     requiredAtInit: true\n19:     ownerArtifact: deep-review-strategy.md\n20:     section: Known Context\n21:     source: bounded-review-context-snapshot\n22:     bounded: true\n23:     pointerBased: true\n24:     includes:\n25:       - targetPointers\n26:       - behaviorClaims\n27:       - reuseAndConventionPointers\n28:       - riskAreasAndContextGaps\n29:     forbids:\n30:       - deepContextDispatch\n31:       - fullSourceBodyInlining\n32:       - contextLoopReportCreation\n33:       - scopeWideningBeyondReviewTarget\n34: \n35:   # Review target taxonomy.\n36:   targetTypes:\n37:     - id: spec-folder\n38:       cliValue: spec-folder\n39:       label: Spec Folder\n40:       description: Review a single spec folder and its referenced implementation, tests, and release artifacts.\n41:     - id: skill\n42:       cliValue: skill\n43:       label: Skill\n44:       description: Review a skill package including SKILL.md, references, assets, scripts, and runtime integrations.\n45:     - id: agent\n46:       cliValue: agent\n47:       label: Agent\n48:       description: Review a named agent across runtime-specific definitions and capability parity surfaces.\n49:     - id: track\n50:       cliValue: track\n51:       label: Track\n52:       description: Review a spec track spanning multiple child spec folders and shared coordination artifacts.\n53:     - id: files\n54:       cliValue: files\n55:       label: Files\n56:       description: Review an explicit file set plus immediate cross-references required to evaluate shipped behavior.\n57: \n58:   # Simplified review dimensions. Traceability and maintainability absorb the\n59:   # prior seven-dimension model's overlap.\n60:   dimensions:\n61:     - id: correctness\n62:       priority: 1\n63:       label: Correctness\n64:       checks: Validate logic, invariants, state transitions, edge cases, and behavior against observable intent.\n65:       requiredForSeverityCoverage: true\n66:     - id: security\n67:       priority: 2\n68:       label: Security\n69:       checks: Validate trust boundaries, authz/authn behavior, input handling, secrets exposure, and exploit paths.\n70:       requiredForSeverityCoverage: true\n71:     - id: traceability\n72:       priority: 3\n73:       label: Traceability\n74:       checks: Validate spec alignment, completeness, checklist evidence, and cross-reference integrity across linked artifacts.\n75:       requiredForSeverityCoverage: false\n76:     - id: maintainability\n77:       priority: 4\n78:       label: Maintainability\n79:       checks: Validate codebase patterns, documentation quality, clarity, and ease of safe follow-on changes.\n80:       requiredForSeverityCoverage: false\n81: \n82:   # Severity contract stays stable across review outputs.\n83:   severities:\n84:     - id: P0\n85:       weight: 10.0\n86:       label: Blocker\n87:       requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n88:     - id: P1\n89:       weight: 5.0\n90:       label: Required\n91:       requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n92:     - id: P2\n93:       weight: 1.0\n94:       label: Suggestion\n95:       requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n96: \n97:   # Verdicts collapse PASS WITH NOTES into PASS + hasAdvisories metadata.\n98:   verdicts:\n99:     - id: FAIL\n100:       label: Fail\n101:       condition: \"activeP0 > 0 OR any required quality gate fails\"\n102:       nextCommand: /speckit:plan\n103:     - id: CONDITIONAL\n104:       label: Conditional\n105:       condition: \"activeP0 == 0 AND activeP1 > 0\"\n106:       nextCommand: /speckit:plan\n107:     - id: PASS\n108:       label: Pass\n109:       condition: \"activeP0 == 0 AND activeP1 == 0\"\n110:       hasAdvisoriesMetadata: \"Set hasAdvisories=true when activeP2 > 0.\"\n111:       nextCommand: /create:changelog\n112: \n113:   # Binary gates applied after convergence math votes STOP.\n114:   qualityGates:\n115:     - id: evidence\n116:       label: Evidence\n117:       binary: true\n118:       combines:\n119:         - evidence-completeness\n120:         - no-inference-only\n121:       rule: Every active finding must be backed by concrete file:line evidence and may not rely only on inference.\n122:     - id: scope\n123:       label: Scope\n124:       binary: true\n125:       combines:\n126:         - scope-alignment\n127:       rule: Reviewed files, targets, and conclusions must stay inside the declared review scope.\n128:     - id: coverage\n129:       label: Coverage\n130:       binary: true\n131:       combines:\n132:         - severity-coverage\n133:         - cross-reference\n134:       rule: Required dimensions and required traceability protocols must be covered before STOP is allowed.\n135: \n136:   # Review-specific convergence settings calibrated from the v2 research.\n137:   convergence:\n138:     defaults:\n139:       maxIterations: 7\n140:       convergenceThreshold: 0.10\n141:       stuckThreshold: 2\n142:     signals:\n143:       - id: rolling-average\n144:         weight: 0.30\n145:         description: Rolling average of severity-weighted new findings across recent evidence-bearing iterations.\n146:       - id: mad-noise-floor\n147:         weight: 0.25\n148:         description: Robust noise-floor test comparing the latest severity-weighted ratio against MAD-derived churn.\n149:       - id: dimension-coverage\n150:         weight: 0.45\n151:         description: Coverage vote based on required dimension completion plus required protocol coverage stability.\n152:     severityMath:\n153:       refinementMultiplier: 0.5\n154:       p0OverrideMinRatio: 0.50\n155:       noFindingsRatio: 0.0\n156:     coverageAge:\n157:       minStabilizationPasses: 1\n158:     thresholds:\n159:       rollingStopThreshold: 0.08\n160:       noProgressThreshold: 0.05\n161:       compositeStopScore: 0.60\n162: \n163:   lifecycleModes:\n164:     - id: new\n165:       description: Create a brand-new review lineage with generation 1 and no parent session.\n166:     - id: resume\n167:       description: Continue the current review lineage without changing generation.\n168:     - id: restart\n169:       description: Start a new generation for the same target and archive the prior review packet state.\n170:     - id: fork\n171:       status: deferred\n172:       description: Reserved compatibility branch. The current runtime does not emit or accept fork review lineages.\n173:     - id: completed-continue\n174:       status: deferred\n175:       description: Reserved compatibility branch. The current runtime does not reopen completed sessions under a completed-continue lineage.\n176: \n177:   lineageFields:\n178:     - sessionId\n179:     - parentSessionId\n180:     - lineageMode\n181:     - generation\n182:     - continuedFromRun\n183: \n184:   reducer:\n185:     enabled: true\n186:     inputs:\n187:       - latestJSONLDelta\n188:       - newIterationFile\n189:       - priorReducedState\n190:     outputs:\n191:       - findingsRegistry\n192:       - dashboardMetrics\n193:       - strategyUpdates\n194:     failureModes:\n195:       malformedDelta: skip-and-warn\n196:       missingIterationFile: no-op-with-error\n197:       schemaMismatch: reject-with-conflict-event\n198:     idempotent: true\n199: \n200:   releaseReadinessStates:\n201:     - id: in-progress\n202:       description: Review is ongoing or coverage is incomplete.\n203:     - id: converged\n204:       description: All dimensions are covered and no new P0/P1 findings appeared in the latest stabilization pass.\n205:     - id: release-blocking\n206:       description: At least one unresolved P0 finding is present.\n207: \n208:   # Cross-reference protocols are typed traceability checks. Core protocols are\n209:   # hard gates; overlay protocols apply only to matching target types.\n210:   crossReferenceProtocols:\n211:     - id: spec_code\n212:       dimension: traceability\n213:       level: core\n214:       appliesTo: [spec-folder, skill, agent, track, files]\n215:       gateClass: hard\n216:       passCriteria: All normative claims resolve to shipped behavior or explicitly documented non-applicability with evidence.\n217:       partialCriteria: Some claims resolve, but one or more claims remain ambiguous or blocked by missing evidence.\n218:       failCriteria: A normative claim contradicts shipped behavior, references missing implementation, or cannot be reconciled.\n219:     - id: checklist_evidence\n220:       dimension: traceability\n221:       level: core\n222:       appliesTo: [spec-folder, skill, agent, track, files]\n223:       gateClass: hard\n224:       passCriteria: Every checked checklist-style claim has supporting evidence and no unsupported completion marks remain.\n225:       partialCriteria: Evidence exists for part of the checked set, but some checked items remain unproven or weakly linked.\n226:       failCriteria: Checked items are unsupported, contradicted by evidence, or materially overstate completion.\n227:     - id: skill_agent\n228:       dimension: traceability\n229:       level: overlay\n230:       appliesTo: [skill]\n231:       gateClass: advisory\n232:       passCriteria: SKILL.md contracts, routing guidance, and referenced runtime agents agree on capabilities and boundaries.\n233:       partialCriteria: Shared intent is consistent, but one or more runtime contracts drift in wording, tools, or expectations.\n234:       failCriteria: SKILL.md and runtime agents materially disagree on capability, routing, permissions, or operating contract.\n235:     - id: agent_cross_runtime\n236:       dimension: traceability\n237:       level: overlay\n238:       appliesTo: [agent]\n239:       gateClass: advisory\n240:       passCriteria: Runtime-specific agent definitions express equivalent behavior, constraints, and evidence requirements.\n241:       partialCriteria: Runtime definitions are broadly aligned but contain non-blocking drift in examples, labels, or metadata.\n242:       failCriteria: Runtime definitions materially diverge in contract, permissions, workflow, or severity/evidence rules.\n243:     - id: feature_catalog_code\n244:       dimension: traceability\n245:       level: overlay\n246:       appliesTo: [skill, spec-folder, track, files]\n247:       gateClass: advisory\n248:       passCriteria: Feature catalog claims match current capability, entry points, and discoverable implementation surfaces.\n249:       partialCriteria: Catalog coverage is incomplete or stale, but no confirmed contradiction to shipped behavior is present.\n250:       failCriteria: Catalog claims are materially false, missing required features, or point to absent implementation.\n251:     - id: playbook_capability\n252:       dimension: traceability\n253:       level: overlay\n254:       appliesTo: [skill, agent, spec-folder]\n255:       gateClass: advisory\n256:       passCriteria: Playbook scenario preconditions, steps, and expected signals are executable against current capability.\n257:       partialCriteria: Scenarios mostly match reality, but one or more steps need updates, clarifications, or narrower scoping.\n258:       failCriteria: Playbook scenarios assume capabilities that do not exist or cannot be executed as documented.\n259: \n260:   # Output contracts consumed by synthesis and replay tooling.\n261:   outputs:\n262:     config:\n263:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n264:       machineOwned: false\n265:       fields:\n266:         - sessionId\n267:         - parentSessionId\n268:         - lineageMode\n269:         - generation\n270:         - continuedFromRun\n271:         - releaseReadinessState\n272:     findingsRegistry:\n273:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n274:       machineOwned: true\n275:       sections:\n276:         - openFindings\n277:         - resolvedFindings\n278:         - repeatedFindings\n279:         - dimensionCoverage\n280:         - findingsBySeverity\n281:         - convergenceScore\n282:     reviewReport:\n283:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n284:       sections:\n285:         - executive-summary\n286:         - planning-trigger\n287:         - active-finding-registry\n288:         - remediation-workstreams\n289:         - spec-seed\n290:         - plan-seed\n291:         - traceability-status\n292:         - deferred-items\n293:         - audit-appendix\n294:     strategy:\n295:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n296:       requiredSections:\n297:         - topic\n298:         - review-dimensions\n299:         - completed-dimensions\n300:         - running-findings\n301:         - what-worked\n302:         - what-failed\n303:         - exhausted-approaches\n304:         - ruled-out-directions\n305:         - next-focus\n306:         - known-context\n307:         - cross-reference-status\n308:         - files-under-review\n309:         - review-boundaries\n310:     dashboard:\n311:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n312:       machineOwned: true\n313:       sections:\n314:         - status\n315:         - findings-summary\n316:         - dimension-coverage\n317:         - progress\n318:         - next-focus\n319:     pauseSentinel:\n320:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\"\n321:       machineOwned: false\n322:       description: Operator-controlled sentinel checked between iterations to pause the loop without discarding state.\n323:     jsonl:\n324:       pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\"\n325:       iterationRecord:\n326:         required:\n327:           - type\n328:           - mode\n329:           - run\n330:           - status\n331:           - focus\n332:           - dimensions\n333:           - filesReviewed\n334:           - findingsCount\n335:           - findingsSummary\n336:           - findingsNew\n337:           - findingDetails\n338:           - newFindingsRatio\n339:           - sessionId\n340:           - generation\n341:           - lineageMode\n342:           - timestamp\n343:           - durationMs\n344:         optional:\n345:           - parentSessionId\n346:           - continuedFromRun\n347:           - findingsRefined\n348:           - findingRefs\n349:           - traceabilityChecks\n350:           - coverage\n351:           - noveltyJustification\n352:           - ruledOut\n353:           - focusTrack\n354:           - scoreEstimate\n355:           - segment\n356:           - convergenceSignals\n357:           - graphEvents\n358:       synthesisEvent:\n359:         required:\n360:           - type\n361:           - event\n362:           - mode\n363:           - totalIterations\n364:           - verdict\n365:           - activeP0\n366:           - activeP1\n367:           - activeP2\n368:           - dimensionCoverage\n369:           - stopReason\n370:           - timestamp\n371: \n372: # Render targets define machine-generated contract fragments. Exactly one\n373: # target is real: the human-readable snapshot rendered by\n374: # render-contract-snapshot.cjs. Everything else that mentions this contract's\n375: # taxonomy (target types, dimensions, severities, verdicts, quality gates,\n376: # convergence, cross-reference protocols) is hand-authored — see\n377: # authoredArtifacts below, not rendered from this file.\n378: render:\n379:   artifacts:\n380:     - id: review-contract-snapshot\n381:       path: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/review-mode-contract-snapshot.md\n382:       ownership: generated\n383:       generator: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/scripts/render-contract-snapshot.cjs\n384:       format: markdown\n385:       markers:\n386:         begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/snapshot -->\"\n387:         end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/snapshot -->\"\n388:       sections:\n389:         - meta\n390:         - target-types\n391:         - dimensions\n392:         - severities\n393:         - verdicts\n394:         - quality-gates\n395:         - convergence\n396:         - cross-reference-protocols\n397:         - outputs\n398:         - validation\n399: \n400: # Authored artifacts reference this manifest's taxonomy in hand-written prose\n401: # or YAML. They are not machine-rendered and carry no generated markers;\n402: # operators keep them in sync by hand when this contract changes. Each\n403: # entry's enumParityChecked list is mechanically enforced (not aspirational):\n404: # deep-review-contract-parity.vitest.ts confirms every id in those families\n405: # still appears literally in the target file, as a lightweight drift\n406: # tripwire that does not require full rendering.\n407: authoredArtifacts:\n408:   - id: workflow-auto\n409:     path: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-review-auto.yaml\n410:     ownership: authored\n411:     format: yaml\n412:     enumParityChecked:\n413:       - dimensions\n414:       - severities\n415:       - verdicts\n416:       - cross-reference-protocols\n417:     note: Hand-maintained workflow YAML for the :auto command path. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n418:   - id: workflow-confirm\n419:     path: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-review-confirm.yaml\n420:     ownership: authored\n421:     format: yaml\n422:     enumParityChecked:\n423:       - dimensions\n424:       - severities\n425:       - verdicts\n426:       - cross-reference-protocols\n427:     note: Hand-maintained workflow YAML for the :confirm command path. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n428:   - id: agent-opencode\n429:     path: .opencode/agents/deep-review.md\n430:     ownership: authored\n431:     format: markdown\n432:     enumParityChecked:\n433:       - dimensions\n434:       - severities\n435:       - verdicts\n436:     note: Hand-maintained OpenCode agent definition. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n437:   - id: agent-claude\n438:     path: .claude/agents/deep-review.md\n439:     ownership: authored\n440:     format: markdown\n441:     enumParityChecked:\n442:       - dimensions\n443:       - severities\n444:       - verdicts\n445:     note: Hand-maintained Claude Code agent definition. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n446:   - id: quick-reference-review-mode\n447:     path: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/quick-reference.md\n448:     ownership: authored\n449:     format: markdown\n450:     enumParityChecked:\n451:       - dimensions\n452:       - severities\n453:       - verdicts\n454:     note: Hand-maintained quick reference. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n455: \n456: # Validator contract for CI, render verification, and drift detection.\n457: validation:\n458:   schemaVersion: 1\n459:   checks:\n460:     - id: schema\n461:       description: Validate this manifest against the canonical review-mode contract schema.\n462:     - id: render-verify\n463:       description: \"Re-render the single review-contract-snapshot artifact (node render-contract-snapshot.cjs --check) and fail on drift. The five authoredArtifacts entries are hand-maintained and are not re-rendered by this check.\"\n464:     - id: marker-integrity\n465:       description: Ensure the review-contract-snapshot artifact contains intact begin/end markers with no overlapping generated blocks.\n466:     - id: enum-parity\n467:       description: \"Confirm the dimension, severity, and verdict ids (plus cross-reference-protocol ids for the two workflow YAMLs) declared in each authoredArtifacts entry's enumParityChecked are still literally present in that file; see deep-review-contract-parity.vitest.ts.\"\n468:     - id: jsonl-parity\n469:       description: Ensure JSONL iteration and synthesis-event fields match the outputs contract.\n470:     - id: lifecycle-parity\n471:       description: \"Ensure lifecycle mode docs and workflow branches agree on the three supported modes: new, resume, and restart.\"\n472:     - id: reducer-contract\n473:       description: Ensure reducer inputs, outputs, and findings-registry metrics are documented consistently across assets and runtime mirrors.\n474:     - id: duplicate-literal-lint\n475:       description: Detect duplicated hard-coded review taxonomy literals outside generated sections.\n476:     - id: runtime-coverage\n477:       description: Ensure every supported runtime deep-review agent has a declared authoredArtifacts entry and parity coverage.\n478:     - id: playbook-assertions\n479:       description: Assert manual testing playbook scenarios reference the canonical simplified contract where applicable.\n\n(End of file - total 479 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Canonical review-mode contract for deep-review.\n# This file is the single source of truth for review-mode taxonomy,\n# convergence settings, cross-reference protocols, downstream render targets,\n# and validation expectations.\n\nmeta:\n  ownerSkill: deep-review\n  reviewModeVersion: 2\n  generatedNotice:\n    warning: \"Exactly one artifact is machine-generated from this file: render.artifacts[0] (review-contract-snapshot). Its begin/end markers live on that artifact entry, not here. Every other contract-taxonomy consumer is hand-authored; see authoredArtifacts.\"\n  sourceOfTruth: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/review-mode-contract.yaml\n\n# Core contract definitions consumed by workflows, agents, docs, and validators.\ncontract:\n  defaultTargetType: spec-folder\n\n  contextSnapshot:\n    requiredAtInit: true\n    ownerArtifact: deep-review-strategy.md\n    section: Known Context","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/review-mode-contract.yaml","text":"# Canonical review-mode contract for deep-review.\n# This file is the single source of truth for review-mode taxonomy,\n# convergence settings, cross-reference protocols, downstream render targets,\n# and validation expectations.\n\nmeta:\n  ownerSkill: deep-review\n  reviewModeVersion: 2\n  generatedNotice:\n    warning: \"Exactly one artifact is machine-generated from this file: render.artifacts[0] (review-contract-snapshot). Its begin/end markers live on that artifact entry, not here. Every other contract-taxonomy consumer is hand-authored; see authoredArtifacts.\"\n  sourceOfTruth: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/review-mode-contract.yaml\n\n# Core contract definitions consumed by workflows, agents, docs, and validators.\ncontract:\n  defaultTargetType: spec-folder\n\n  contextSnapshot:\n    requiredAtInit: true\n    ownerArtifact: deep-review-strategy.md\n    section: Known Context\n    source: bounded-review-context-snapshot\n    bounded: true\n    pointerBased: true\n    includes:\n      - targetPointers\n      - behaviorClaims\n      - reuseAndConventionPointers\n      - riskAreasAndContextGaps\n    forbids:\n      - deepContextDispatch\n      - fullSourceBodyInlining\n      - contextLoopReportCreation\n      - scopeWideningBeyondReviewTarget\n\n  # Review target taxonomy.\n  targetTypes:\n    - id: spec-folder\n      cliValue: spec-folder\n      label: Spec Folder\n      description: Review a single spec folder and its referenced implementation, tests, and release artifacts.\n    - id: skill\n      cliValue: skill\n      label: Skill\n      description: Review a skill package including SKILL.md, references, assets, scripts, and runtime integrations.\n    - id: agent\n      cliValue: agent\n      label: Agent\n      description: Review a named agent across runtime-specific definitions and capability parity surfaces.\n    - id: track\n      cliValue: track\n      label: Track\n      description: Review a spec track spanning multiple child spec folders and shared coordination artifacts.\n    - id: files\n      cliValue: files\n      label: Files\n      description: Review an explicit file set plus immediate cross-references required to evaluate shipped behavior.\n\n  # Simplified review dimensions. Traceability and maintainability absorb the\n  # prior seven-dimension model's overlap.\n  dimensions:\n    - id: correctness\n      priority: 1\n      label: Correctness\n      checks: Validate logic, invariants, state transitions, edge cases, and behavior against observable intent.\n      requiredForSeverityCoverage: true\n    - id: security\n      priority: 2\n      label: Security\n      checks: Validate trust boundaries, authz/authn behavior, input handling, secrets exposure, and exploit paths.\n      requiredForSeverityCoverage: true\n    - id: traceability\n      priority: 3\n      label: Traceability\n      checks: Validate spec alignment, completeness, checklist evidence, and cross-reference integrity across linked artifacts.\n      requiredForSeverityCoverage: false\n    - id: maintainability\n      priority: 4\n      label: Maintainability\n      checks: Validate codebase patterns, documentation quality, clarity, and ease of safe follow-on changes.\n      requiredForSeverityCoverage: false\n\n  # Severity contract stays stable across review outputs.\n  severities:\n    - id: P0\n      weight: 10.0\n      label: Blocker\n      requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n    - id: P1\n      weight: 5.0\n      label: Required\n      requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n    - id: P2\n      weight: 1.0\n      label: Suggestion\n      requiresFileLineEvidence: true\n\n  # Verdicts collapse PASS WITH NOTES into PASS + hasAdvisories metadata.\n  verdicts:\n    - id: FAIL\n      label: Fail\n      condition: \"activeP0 > 0 OR any required quality gate fails\"\n      nextCommand: /speckit:plan\n    - id: CONDITIONAL\n      label: Conditional\n      condition: \"activeP0 == 0 AND activeP1 > 0\"\n      nextCommand: /speckit:plan\n    - id: PASS\n      label: Pass\n      condition: \"activeP0 == 0 AND activeP1 == 0\"\n      hasAdvisoriesMetadata: \"Set hasAdvisories=true when activeP2 > 0.\"\n      nextCommand: /create:changelog\n\n  # Binary gates applied after convergence math votes STOP.\n  qualityGates:\n    - id: evidence\n      label: Evidence\n      binary: true\n      combines:\n        - evidence-completeness\n        - no-inference-only\n      rule: Every active finding must be backed by concrete file:line evidence and may not rely only on inference.\n    - id: scope\n      label: Scope\n      binary: true\n      combines:\n        - scope-alignment\n      rule: Reviewed files, targets, and conclusions must stay inside the declared review scope.\n    - id: coverage\n      label: Coverage\n      binary: true\n      combines:\n        - severity-coverage\n        - cross-reference\n      rule: Required dimensions and required traceability protocols must be covered before STOP is allowed.\n\n  # Review-specific convergence settings calibrated from the v2 research.\n  convergence:\n    defaults:\n      maxIterations: 7\n      convergenceThreshold: 0.10\n      stuckThreshold: 2\n    signals:\n      - id: rolling-average\n        weight: 0.30\n        description: Rolling average of severity-weighted new findings across recent evidence-bearing iterations.\n      - id: mad-noise-floor\n        weight: 0.25\n        description: Robust noise-floor test comparing the latest severity-weighted ratio against MAD-derived churn.\n      - id: dimension-coverage\n        weight: 0.45\n        description: Coverage vote based on required dimension completion plus required protocol coverage stability.\n    severityMath:\n      refinementMultiplier: 0.5\n      p0OverrideMinRatio: 0.50\n      noFindingsRatio: 0.0\n    coverageAge:\n      minStabilizationPasses: 1\n    thresholds:\n      rollingStopThreshold: 0.08\n      noProgressThreshold: 0.05\n      compositeStopScore: 0.60\n\n  lifecycleModes:\n    - id: new\n      description: Create a brand-new review lineage with generation 1 and no parent session.\n    - id: resume\n      description: Continue the current review lineage without changing generation.\n    - id: restart\n      description: Start a new generation for the same target and archive the prior review packet state.\n    - id: fork\n      status: deferred\n      description: Reserved compatibility branch. The current runtime does not emit or accept fork review lineages.\n    - id: completed-continue\n      status: deferred\n      description: Reserved compatibility branch. The current runtime does not reopen completed sessions under a completed-continue lineage.\n\n  lineageFields:\n    - sessionId\n    - parentSessionId\n    - lineageMode\n    - generation\n    - continuedFromRun\n\n  reducer:\n    enabled: true\n    inputs:\n      - latestJSONLDelta\n      - newIterationFile\n      - priorReducedState\n    outputs:\n      - findingsRegistry\n      - dashboardMetrics\n      - strategyUpdates\n    failureModes:\n      malformedDelta: skip-and-warn\n      missingIterationFile: no-op-with-error\n      schemaMismatch: reject-with-conflict-event\n    idempotent: true\n\n  releaseReadinessStates:\n    - id: in-progress\n      description: Review is ongoing or coverage is incomplete.\n    - id: converged\n      description: All dimensions are covered and no new P0/P1 findings appeared in the latest stabilization pass.\n    - id: release-blocking\n      description: At least one unresolved P0 finding is present.\n\n  # Cross-reference protocols are typed traceability checks. Core protocols are\n  # hard gates; overlay protocols apply only to matching target types.\n  crossReferenceProtocols:\n    - id: spec_code\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: core\n      appliesTo: [spec-folder, skill, agent, track, files]\n      gateClass: hard\n      passCriteria: All normative claims resolve to shipped behavior or explicitly documented non-applicability with evidence.\n      partialCriteria: Some claims resolve, but one or more claims remain ambiguous or blocked by missing evidence.\n      failCriteria: A normative claim contradicts shipped behavior, references missing implementation, or cannot be reconciled.\n    - id: checklist_evidence\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: core\n      appliesTo: [spec-folder, skill, agent, track, files]\n      gateClass: hard\n      passCriteria: Every checked checklist-style claim has supporting evidence and no unsupported completion marks remain.\n      partialCriteria: Evidence exists for part of the checked set, but some checked items remain unproven or weakly linked.\n      failCriteria: Checked items are unsupported, contradicted by evidence, or materially overstate completion.\n    - id: skill_agent\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: overlay\n      appliesTo: [skill]\n      gateClass: advisory\n      passCriteria: SKILL.md contracts, routing guidance, and referenced runtime agents agree on capabilities and boundaries.\n      partialCriteria: Shared intent is consistent, but one or more runtime contracts drift in wording, tools, or expectations.\n      failCriteria: SKILL.md and runtime agents materially disagree on capability, routing, permissions, or operating contract.\n    - id: agent_cross_runtime\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: overlay\n      appliesTo: [agent]\n      gateClass: advisory\n      passCriteria: Runtime-specific agent definitions express equivalent behavior, constraints, and evidence requirements.\n      partialCriteria: Runtime definitions are broadly aligned but contain non-blocking drift in examples, labels, or metadata.\n      failCriteria: Runtime definitions materially diverge in contract, permissions, workflow, or severity/evidence rules.\n    - id: feature_catalog_code\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: overlay\n      appliesTo: [skill, spec-folder, track, files]\n      gateClass: advisory\n      passCriteria: Feature catalog claims match current capability, entry points, and discoverable implementation surfaces.\n      partialCriteria: Catalog coverage is incomplete or stale, but no confirmed contradiction to shipped behavior is present.\n      failCriteria: Catalog claims are materially false, missing required features, or point to absent implementation.\n    - id: playbook_capability\n      dimension: traceability\n      level: overlay\n      appliesTo: [skill, agent, spec-folder]\n      gateClass: advisory\n      passCriteria: Playbook scenario preconditions, steps, and expected signals are executable against current capability.\n      partialCriteria: Scenarios mostly match reality, but one or more steps need updates, clarifications, or narrower scoping.\n      failCriteria: Playbook scenarios assume capabilities that do not exist or cannot be executed as documented.\n\n  # Output contracts consumed by synthesis and replay tooling.\n  outputs:\n    config:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-config.json\"\n      machineOwned: false\n      fields:\n        - sessionId\n        - parentSessionId\n        - lineageMode\n        - generation\n        - continuedFromRun\n        - releaseReadinessState\n    findingsRegistry:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-findings-registry.json\"\n      machineOwned: true\n      sections:\n        - openFindings\n        - resolvedFindings\n        - repeatedFindings\n        - dimensionCoverage\n        - findingsBySeverity\n        - convergenceScore\n    reviewReport:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n      sections:\n        - executive-summary\n        - planning-trigger\n        - active-finding-registry\n        - remediation-workstreams\n        - spec-seed\n        - plan-seed\n        - traceability-status\n        - deferred-items\n        - audit-appendix\n    strategy:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-strategy.md\"\n      requiredSections:\n        - topic\n        - review-dimensions\n        - completed-dimensions\n        - running-findings\n        - what-worked\n        - what-failed\n        - exhausted-approaches\n        - ruled-out-directions\n        - next-focus\n        - known-context\n        - cross-reference-status\n        - files-under-review\n        - review-boundaries\n    dashboard:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-dashboard.md\"\n      machineOwned: true\n      sections:\n        - status\n        - findings-summary\n        - dimension-coverage\n        - progress\n        - next-focus\n    pauseSentinel:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-review-pause\"\n      machineOwned: false\n      description: Operator-controlled sentinel checked between iterations to pause the loop without discarding state.\n    jsonl:\n      pathPattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-review-state.jsonl\"\n      iterationRecord:\n        required:\n          - type\n          - mode\n          - run\n          - status\n          - focus\n          - dimensions\n          - filesReviewed\n          - findingsCount\n          - findingsSummary\n          - findingsNew\n          - findingDetails\n          - newFindingsRatio\n          - sessionId\n          - generation\n          - lineageMode\n          - timestamp\n          - durationMs\n        optional:\n          - parentSessionId\n          - continuedFromRun\n          - findingsRefined\n          - findingRefs\n          - traceabilityChecks\n          - coverage\n          - noveltyJustification\n          - ruledOut\n          - focusTrack\n          - scoreEstimate\n          - segment\n          - convergenceSignals\n          - graphEvents\n      synthesisEvent:\n        required:\n          - type\n          - event\n          - mode\n          - totalIterations\n          - verdict\n          - activeP0\n          - activeP1\n          - activeP2\n          - dimensionCoverage\n          - stopReason\n          - timestamp\n\n# Render targets define machine-generated contract fragments. Exactly one\n# target is real: the human-readable snapshot rendered by\n# render-contract-snapshot.cjs. Everything else that mentions this contract's\n# taxonomy (target types, dimensions, severities, verdicts, quality gates,\n# convergence, cross-reference protocols) is hand-authored — see\n# authoredArtifacts below, not rendered from this file.\nrender:\n  artifacts:\n    - id: review-contract-snapshot\n      path: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/review-mode-contract-snapshot.md\n      ownership: generated\n      generator: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/scripts/render-contract-snapshot.cjs\n      format: markdown\n      markers:\n        begin: \"<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: review-mode-contract/snapshot -->\"\n        end: \"<!-- END GENERATED: review-mode-contract/snapshot -->\"\n      sections:\n        - meta\n        - target-types\n        - dimensions\n        - severities\n        - verdicts\n        - quality-gates\n        - convergence\n        - cross-reference-protocols\n        - outputs\n        - validation\n\n# Authored artifacts reference this manifest's taxonomy in hand-written prose\n# or YAML. They are not machine-rendered and carry no generated markers;\n# operators keep them in sync by hand when this contract changes. Each\n# entry's enumParityChecked list is mechanically enforced (not aspirational):\n# deep-review-contract-parity.vitest.ts confirms every id in those families\n# still appears literally in the target file, as a lightweight drift\n# tripwire that does not require full rendering.\nauthoredArtifacts:\n  - id: workflow-auto\n    path: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-review-auto.yaml\n    ownership: authored\n    format: yaml\n    enumParityChecked:\n      - dimensions\n      - severities\n      - verdicts\n      - cross-reference-protocols\n    note: Hand-maintained workflow YAML for the :auto command path. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n  - id: workflow-confirm\n    path: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-review-confirm.yaml\n    ownership: authored\n    format: yaml\n    enumParityChecked:\n      - dimensions\n      - severities\n      - verdicts\n      - cross-reference-protocols\n    note: Hand-maintained workflow YAML for the :confirm command path. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n  - id: agent-opencode\n    path: .opencode/agents/deep-review.md\n    ownership: authored\n    format: markdown\n    enumParityChecked:\n      - dimensions\n      - severities\n      - verdicts\n    note: Hand-maintained OpenCode agent definition. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n  - id: agent-claude\n    path: .claude/agents/deep-review.md\n    ownership: authored\n    format: markdown\n    enumParityChecked:\n      - dimensions\n      - severities\n      - verdicts\n    note: Hand-maintained Claude Code agent definition. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n  - id: quick-reference-review-mode\n    path: .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/references/protocol/quick-reference.md\n    ownership: authored\n    format: markdown\n    enumParityChecked:\n      - dimensions\n      - severities\n      - verdicts\n    note: Hand-maintained quick reference. References this contract's taxonomy in prose; not machine-rendered from this manifest.\n\n# Validator contract for CI, render verification, and drift detection.\nvalidation:\n  schemaVersion: 1\n  checks:\n    - id: schema\n      description: Validate this manifest against the canonical review-mode contract schema.\n    - id: render-verify\n      description: \"Re-render the single review-contract-snapshot artifact (node render-contract-snapshot.cjs --check) and fail on drift. The five authoredArtifacts entries are hand-maintained and are not re-rendered by this check.\"\n    - id: marker-integrity\n      description: Ensure the review-contract-snapshot artifact contains intact begin/end markers with no overlapping generated blocks.\n    - id: enum-parity\n      description: \"Confirm the dimension, severity, and verdict ids (plus cross-reference-protocol ids for the two workflow YAMLs) declared in each authoredArtifacts entry's enumParityChecked are still literally present in that file; see deep-review-contract-parity.vitest.ts.\"\n    - id: jsonl-parity\n      description: Ensure JSONL iteration and synthesis-event fields match the outputs contract.\n    - id: lifecycle-parity\n      description: \"Ensure lifecycle mode docs and workflow branches agree on the three supported modes: new, resume, and restart.\"\n    - id: reducer-contract\n      description: Ensure reducer inputs, outputs, and findings-registry metrics are documented consistently across assets and runtime mirrors.\n    - id: duplicate-literal-lint\n      description: Detect duplicated hard-coded review taxonomy literals outside generated sections.\n    - id: runtime-coverage\n      description: Ensure every supported runtime deep-review agent has a declared authoredArtifacts entry and parity coverage.\n    - id: playbook-assertions\n      description: Assert manual testing playbook scenarios reference the canonical simplified contract where applicable.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":479,"totalLines":479,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/review-mode-contract.yaml","time":{"start":1784650212467,"end":1784650212583}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03f0e82d94f6d585016a5f99e44d2c819190e6bd9e6658d215"}},"id":"prt_f8571246f001aihQ9I161ky7ze","sessionID":"ses_07a91b76bffeQVZz6UB7PapKuO","messageID":"msg_f8570c374001ieeOYdHuun9tY9"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784650212597,"sessionID":"ses_07a91b76bffeQVZz6UB7PapKuO","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_JWWWwhtVYty2lMkWhzMhuHwg","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-review-auto.yaml","offset":970,"limit":615},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-review-auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n970:         action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested review marker\"\n971:         algorithm: |\n972:           if current_iteration > 1:\n973:             PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n974:             if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n975:               PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n976:               if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n977:                 log \"ERROR: nested review-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n978:                 halt with exit code 2\n979:         note: |\n980:           False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n981:           three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n982:           True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n983:           starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested review-of-review dispatch.\n984: \n985:       step_dispatch_iteration:\n986:         action: \"Dispatch @deep-review agent for one review iteration\"\n987:         resolve_executor:\n988:           source: \"config.executor\"\n989:           loader: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n990:         pre_dispatch:\n991:           generate_summary: |\n992:             STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n993:             Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n994:             Dimension: {next_dimension}\n995:             Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n996:             Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n997:             Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n998:             {resource_map_prompt_line}\n999:             Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n1000:             Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n1001:             Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n1002:             Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n1003:           render_prompt_pack:\n1004:             template_path: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/prompt-pack-iteration.md.tmpl\"\n1005:             renderer: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n1006:             output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n1007:             variables:\n1008:               state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n1009:               current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n1010:               max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n1011:               next_dimension: \"{next_dimension}\"\n1012:               review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n1013:               review_scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n1014:               p0_count: \"{p0_count}\"\n1015:               p1_count: \"{p1_count}\"\n1016:               p2_count: \"{p2_count}\"\n1017:               pivot_lineage: \"{pivot_lineage}\"\n1018:               saturated_directions: \"{saturated_directions}\"\n1019:               state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1020:               state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1021:               state_paths_findings_registry: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1022:               state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1023:               state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1024:               state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n1025:         pre_dispatch_audit:\n1026:           skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n1027:           call: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n1028:           args:\n1029:             stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1030:             executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n1031:             iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n1032:         branch_on: \"config.executor.kind\"\n1033:         if_native:\n1034:           dispatch:\n1035:             agent: deep-review\n1036:             model: opus\n1037:             context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n1038:           wait_for_completion: true\n1039:         if_cli_copilot:\n1040:           command: |\n1041:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1042:             import { readFileSync, writeFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n1043:             import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n1044: \n1045:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n1046:             import { buildCopilotPromptArg } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n1047: \n1048:             const promptPath = '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md';\n1049:             const prompt = readFileSync(promptPath, 'utf8');\n1050: \n1051:             // Workflow-resolved spec folder is the only legal write authority.\n1052:             // The helper (`validateSpecFolder` inside `buildCopilotPromptArg`)\n1053:             // is the single source of truth for rejecting empty / unresolved\n1054:             // template / whitespace-only / string-coerced empty values. The\n1055:             // YAML hands the raw `{spec_folder}` directly; on rejection the\n1056:             // helper safe-fails to `type:\"missing\", writeIntent:true` (Gate-3\n1057:             // enforcement, --allow-all-tools stripped).\n1058:             const specFolderRaw = '{spec_folder}';\n1059:             const targetAuthority = { type: 'approved', specFolder: specFolderRaw };\n1060: \n1061:             const baseArgs = [\n1062:               '-p',\n1063:               prompt,\n1064:               '--model',\n1065:               '{config.executor.model}',\n1066:               '--allow-all-tools',\n1067:               '--no-ask-user',\n1068:             ];\n1069: \n1070:             const built = buildCopilotPromptArg({\n1071:               promptPath,\n1072:               prompt,\n1073:               targetAuthority,\n1074:               baseArgv: baseArgs,\n1075:             });\n1076: \n1077:             // Large-prompt @PROMPT_PATH wrapper: helper emits a `promptFileBody`\n1078:             // containing `<TARGET AUTHORITY preamble>\\n\\n---\\n\\n<original>`.\n1079:             // Write it to disk so the file Copilot reads via @path opens with\n1080:             // the authority block. Without this, recovered/bootstrap folder\n1081:             // mentions inside the file could still anchor the model.\n1082:             if (built.promptFileBody !== undefined) {\n1083:               writeFileSync(promptPath, built.promptFileBody, 'utf8');\n1084:             }\n1085: \n1086:             // Copilot is routed through the audited executor wrapper so it produces\n1087:             // INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts alongside claude-code/opencode\n1088:             // There is no cli-copilot kind in the executor schema, so it\n1089:             // dispatches as kind:'native' (full env passthrough, no recursion-guard\n1090:             // layer configured for copilot); the receipt still records the real\n1091:             // 'copilot' command + built.argv as facts.\n1092:             const dispatchFacts = {\n1093:               command: 'deep/review',\n1094:               mode: 'review',\n1095:               specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n1096:               artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n1097:               iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1098:               executorKind: '{config.executor.kind}',\n1099:               branchId: '{config.executor.kind}',\n1100:               sessionId: '{session_id}',\n1101:               generation: Number('{generation}'),\n1102:             };\n1103:             const dispatchId = 'review-i{current_iteration}-g{generation}';\n1104:             process.exit(\n1105:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n1106:                 command: 'copilot',\n1107:                 args: built.argv,\n1108:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n1109:                 timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n1110:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n1111:                 executor: {\n1112:                   kind: 'native',\n1113:                   model: '{config.executor.model}',\n1114:                   configDir: null,\n1115:                   reasoningEffort: null,\n1116:                   serviceTier: null,\n1117:                   sandboxMode: null,\n1118:                   timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n1119:                   governor: null,\n1120:                 },\n1121:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1122:                 receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n1123:                 dispatchId,\n1124:               }),\n1125:             );\n1126:             EOF\n1127:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1128:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n1129:           wait_for_completion: true\n1130:           notes:\n1131:             - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so copilot produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; built.argv (@PROMPT_PATH or positional) is forwarded verbatim as the receipt facts\"\n1132:             - \"copilot has no stdin support; prompt is positional\"\n1133:             - \"Size check uses 16KB threshold; above that uses @PROMPT_PATH wrapper prompt\"\n1134:             - \"Large-prompt path relies on copilot honoring @path references within its prompt string\"\n1135:             - \"buildCopilotPromptArg attaches a TARGET AUTHORITY preamble bound to the workflow-approved spec folder; recovered context cannot override it (authority guard source: .opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_deep-review_auto.yaml)\"\n1136:             - \"If spec_folder is missing/malformed/unresolved on a write-intent dispatch, the helper enforces plan-only by replacing the prompt with a Gate-3 question and stripping --allow-all-tools\"\n1137:             - \"Large-prompt wrapper mode rewrites the prompt file at promptPath to include the TARGET AUTHORITY preamble (prefix + divider + original body); the argv becomes a bare @promptPath reference\"\n1138:         if_cli_claude_code:\n1139:           command: |\n1140:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1141:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n1142:             import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n1143: \n1144:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n1145: \n1146:             const configDir = '{optional_claude_config_dir}';\n1147:             const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n1148:             const executor = {\n1149:               kind: 'cli-claude-code',\n1150:               model: '{config.executor.model}',\n1151:               configDir: configDir || null,\n1152:               reasoningEffort,\n1153:               serviceTier: null,\n1154:               sandboxMode: null,\n1155:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n1156:               governor: null,\n1157:             };\n1158:             const args = [\n1159:               '-p',\n1160:               readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n1161:               '--model',\n1162:               executor.model,\n1163:               '--permission-mode',\n1164:               'acceptEdits',\n1165:               '--output-format',\n1166:               'text',\n1167:             ];\n1168:             if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n1169:               args.push('--effort', executor.reasoningEffort);\n1170:             }\n1171: \n1172:             // CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR rides through guardContext.env; the CLAUDE_ prefix is\n1173:             // on the cli-claude-code env allowlist so buildExecutorDispatchEnv admits it.\n1174:             const parentEnv = { ...process.env };\n1175:             if (configDir) {\n1176:               parentEnv.CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR = configDir;\n1177:             }\n1178: \n1179:             const dispatchFacts = {\n1180:               command: 'deep/review',\n1181:               mode: 'review',\n1182:               specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n1183:               artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n1184:               iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1185:               executorKind: '{config.executor.kind}',\n1186:               branchId: '{config.executor.kind}',\n1187:               sessionId: '{session_id}',\n1188:               generation: Number('{generation}'),\n1189:             };\n1190:             const dispatchId = 'review-i{current_iteration}-g{generation}';\n1191:             process.exit(\n1192:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n1193:                 command: 'claude',\n1194:                 args,\n1195:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n1196:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n1197:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n1198:                 executor,\n1199:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1200:                 guardContext: { env: parentEnv },\n1201:                 receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n1202:                 dispatchId,\n1203:               }),\n1204:             );\n1205:             EOF\n1206:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1207:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n1208:           wait_for_completion: true\n1209:           render_hint:\n1210:             optional_claude_config_dir: |\n1211:               If config.executor.configDir is set and non-null, expand a leading ~ to HOME and bind that path.\n1212:               Otherwise expand to empty string.\n1213:           notes:\n1214:             - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so claude-code produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard + env allowlist enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n1215:             - \"CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR is forwarded through guardContext.env (CLAUDE_ prefix is allowlisted) so account-specific Claude Code routing is preserved\"\n1216:             - \"permission-mode stays acceptEdits (review's existing iteration-write behavior); claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n1217:             - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n1218:         if_cli_opencode:\n1219:           command: |\n1220:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1221:             import { execFileSync } from 'node:child_process';\n1222:             import { appendFileSync, readFileSync, realpathSync } from 'node:fs';\n1223:             import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n1224:             import { isAbsolute, relative, resolve } from 'node:path';\n1225: \n1226:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n1227: \n1228:             const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n1229:             const executor = {\n1230:               kind: 'cli-opencode',\n1231:               model: '{config.executor.model}',\n1232:               configDir: null,\n1233:               reasoningEffort,\n1234:               serviceTier: null,\n1235:               sandboxMode: null,\n1236:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n1237:               governor: null,\n1238:             };\n1239:             const promptBody = readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8');\n1240:             if (!promptBody.includes('BANNED OPERATIONS') || !promptBody.includes('ALLOWED WRITE PATHS')) {\n1241:               throw new Error('Unsafe cli-opencode dispatch: rendered prompt is missing required write-containment sections');\n1242:             }\n1243: \n1244:             const repoRoot = realpathSync('{repo_root}');\n1245:             const artifactDir = resolve(repoRoot, '{state_paths.packet_dir}');\n1246:             const artifactRelative = relative(repoRoot, artifactDir);\n1247:             if (artifactRelative === '' || artifactRelative.startsWith('..') || isAbsolute(artifactRelative)) {\n1248:               throw new Error('Unsafe cli-opencode dispatch: artifact directory must be a strict descendant of the worktree root');\n1249:             }\n1250: \n1251:             const git = (args, cwd = repoRoot, trim = true) => {\n1252:               const output = execFileSync('git', args, { cwd, encoding: 'utf8' });\n1253:               return trim ? output.trim() : output;\n1254:             };\n1255:             const resolveGitPath = (candidate) => realpathSync(isAbsolute(candidate) ? candidate : resolve(repoRoot, candidate));\n1256:             const gitDir = resolveGitPath(git(['rev-parse', '--git-dir']));\n1257:             const commonGitDir = resolveGitPath(git(['rev-parse', '--git-common-dir']));\n1258:             if (gitDir === commonGitDir) {\n1259:               throw new Error('Unsafe cli-opencode dispatch: --dir must point at an isolated linked worktree');\n1260:             }\n1261: \n1262:             const primaryBlock = git(['worktree', 'list', '--porcelain'])\n1263:               .split(/\\n\\n+/)\n1264:               .find((block) => /^branch refs\\/heads\\/(?:main|master)$/m.test(block));\n1265:             const primaryLine = primaryBlock?.split('\\n').find((line) => line.startsWith('worktree '));\n1266:             if (!primaryLine) {\n1267:               throw new Error('Unsafe cli-opencode dispatch: primary main/master worktree could not be resolved');\n1268:             }\n1269:             const primaryRoot = realpathSync(primaryLine.slice('worktree '.length));\n1270:             const primaryStatus = git(['status', '--porcelain=v1', '--untracked-files=all'], primaryRoot);\n1271:             if (primaryStatus) {\n1272:               throw new Error('Unsafe cli-opencode dispatch: primary worktree must be clean before unrestricted execution');\n1273:             }\n1274: \n1275:             const dirtyPaths = [\n1276:               ...git(['diff', '--name-only', '-z', 'HEAD', '--'], repoRoot, false).split('\\0'),\n1277:               ...git(['ls-files', '--others', '--exclude-standard', '-z'], repoRoot, false).split('\\0'),\n1278:             ].filter(Boolean);\n1279:             const outsideArtifactDir = dirtyPaths.filter((candidate) => {\n1280:               const candidateRelative = relative(artifactDir, resolve(repoRoot, candidate));\n1281:               return candidateRelative.startsWith('..') || isAbsolute(candidateRelative);\n1282:             });\n1283:             if (outsideArtifactDir.length > 0) {\n1284:               throw new Error(`Unsafe cli-opencode dispatch: worktree changes outside the artifact directory: ${outsideArtifactDir.join(', ')}`);\n1285:             }\n1286: \n1287:             const recoveryBaselineCommit = git(['rev-parse', '--verify', 'HEAD']);\n1288:             appendFileSync(\n1289:               '{state_paths.state_log}',\n1290:               `${JSON.stringify({ type: 'event', event: 'recovery_baseline', mode: 'review', iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'), recoveryBaselineCommit, worktree: repoRoot, timestamp: new Date().toISOString() })}\\n`,\n1291:               'utf8',\n1292:             );\n1293:             const message = 'Resolved route: mode=review; target_agent=@deep-review; execution=single_review_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true'\n1294:               + '\\n\\n'\n1295:               + promptBody;\n1296:             const args = [\n1297:               'run',\n1298:               '--model',\n1299:               executor.model,\n1300:               '--format',\n1301:               'json',\n1302:               '--dangerously-skip-permissions',\n1303:               '--pure',\n1304:               '--dir',\n1305:               '{repo_root}',\n1306:             ];\n1307:             if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n1308:               args.push('--variant', executor.reasoningEffort);\n1309:             }\n1310:             args.push(message);\n1311: \n1312:             const dispatchFacts = {\n1313:               command: 'deep/review',\n1314:               mode: 'review',\n1315:               specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n1316:               artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n1317:               iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1318:               executorKind: '{config.executor.kind}',\n1319:               branchId: '{config.executor.kind}',\n1320:               sessionId: '{session_id}',\n1321:               generation: Number('{generation}'),\n1322:             };\n1323:             const dispatchId = 'review-i{current_iteration}-g{generation}';\n1324:             process.exit(\n1325:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n1326:                 command: 'opencode',\n1327:                 args,\n1328:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n1329:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n1330:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n1331:                 executor,\n1332:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1333:                 // opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation;\n1334:                 // an empty input gives EOF stdin, equivalent to </dev/null.\n1335:                 input: '',\n1336:                 receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n1337:                 dispatchId,\n1338:               }),\n1339:             );\n1340:             EOF\n1341:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1342:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n1343:           wait_for_completion: true\n1344:           notes:\n1345:             - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so opencode produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard + env allowlist enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n1346:             - \"Fail closed before dispatch unless the rendered containment sections exist, --dir is an isolated linked worktree, the primary worktree is clean, and current-worktree changes are confined to artifact_dir; append the recovery-baseline commit to state_log\"\n1347:             - \"input:'' yields closed stdin (EOF), equivalent to </dev/null — opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup and hangs at 0% CPU after +60s snapshot prune without it (the `cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §4 ALWAYS rule)\"\n1348:             - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is the route-proof preamble + iteration body\"\n1349:             - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n1350:             - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n1351:             - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this single-executor branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude Code/raw shell). Explicit parallel-detached cli-opencode fan-out is handled by step_fanout_spawn_cli/fanout-run.cjs, not this branch. the `cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n1352:         if_cli_codex:\n1353:           command: |\n1354:             node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1355:             import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n1356:             import { execFileSync } from 'node:child_process';\n1357: \n1358:             import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n1359: \n1360:             // Fail closed: a requested codex executor must dispatch codex or abort,\n1361:             // never silently degrade to another executor. Undetected absence is what\n1362:             // got Codex deprecated before, so the branch exits non-zero when the\n1363:             // binary is missing instead of falling through to a native/other path.\n1364:             let codexAvailable = false;\n1365:             try {\n1366:               execFileSync('/bin/sh', ['-c', 'command -v codex >/dev/null 2>&1'], { stdio: 'ignore' });\n1367:               codexAvailable = true;\n1368:             } catch {}\n1369:             if (!codexAvailable) {\n1370:               console.error('cli-codex executor unavailable: command -v codex failed');\n1371:               process.exit(1);\n1372:             }\n1373: \n1374:             const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n1375:             const serviceTier = '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}';\n1376:             const model = '{config.executor.model}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.model}';\n1377:             const executor = {\n1378:               kind: 'cli-codex',\n1379:               model,\n1380:               configDir: null,\n1381:               reasoningEffort,\n1382:               serviceTier,\n1383:               sandboxMode: 'workspace-write',\n1384:               timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n1385:               governor: null,\n1386:             };\n1387: \n1388:             const promptBody = readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8');\n1389: \n1390:             // codex reads the iteration prompt from stdin via the trailing '-'. A review\n1391:             // iteration must WRITE its own iteration file, delta and state record, so the\n1392:             // sandbox is workspace-write — read-only would block those required writes.\n1393:             // approval_policy=never keeps the run non-interactive.\n1394:             const args = ['exec'];\n1395:             if (model) {\n1396:               args.push('--model', model);\n1397:             }\n1398:             args.push('-c', 'model_reasoning_effort=' + (reasoningEffort || 'medium'));\n1399:             if (serviceTier) {\n1400:               args.push('-c', 'service_tier=' + serviceTier);\n1401:             }\n1402:             args.push('-c', 'approval_policy=never', '--sandbox', executor.sandboxMode, '-');\n1403: \n1404:             const dispatchId = 'review-i{current_iteration}-g{generation}';\n1405:             process.exit(\n1406:               runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n1407:                 command: 'codex',\n1408:                 args,\n1409:                 cwd: '{repo_root}',\n1410:                 timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n1411:                 stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n1412:                 executor,\n1413:                 iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n1414:                 input: promptBody,\n1415:                 receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n1416:                 dispatchId,\n1417:               }),\n1418:             );\n1419:             EOF\n1420:           working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1421:           timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n1422:           wait_for_completion: true\n1423:           notes:\n1424:             - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so codex produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard (CODEX_SESSION_ID) + env allowlist (CODEX_/OPENAI_/AZURE_OPENAI_) enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n1425:             - \"Fails closed when the codex binary is absent (exit 1) — parity with the fan-out cli-codex lineage guard in fanout-run.cjs; codex routing never degrades to native\"\n1426:             - \"codex exec reads the iteration prompt from stdin via the trailing '-' (input: promptBody); '-c model_reasoning_effort=' maps reasoning depth, default medium; '-c service_tier=' forwarded when configured\"\n1427:             - \"--sandbox workspace-write is required so the iteration can write its own iteration file/delta/state record (read-only would fail the post-dispatch artifact gate); -c approval_policy=never keeps it non-interactive; --model omitted when unset so ~/.codex/config.toml default applies\"\n1428:         post_dispatch_validate:\n1429:           validator: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n1430:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/verify-iteration.cjs --loop-type review --artifact-dir {artifact_dir} --iteration {current_iteration}\"\n1431:           command_note: \"Mechanical leaf-reliability gate: exit 0 = complete; non-zero prints one machine reason (iteration_file_missing|iteration_verdict_missing|state_record_missing|route_proof_missing|route_proof_mismatch|delta_file_missing). The script enforces the artifact + route-proof contract instead of trusting the leaf to self-report, and a non-zero exit triggers on_failure.redispatch_once.\"\n1432:           assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1433:           assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1434:           assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, mode, run, status, focus, dimensions, filesReviewed, findingsCount, findingsSummary, findingsNew, findingDetails, newFindingsRatio, sessionId, generation, lineageMode, timestamp, durationMs]\n1435:           route_proof:\n1436:             mode: review\n1437:             target_agent: deep-review\n1438:             agent_definition_loaded: true\n1439:             resolved_route: \"Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review\"\n1440:           dispatchReceipt:\n1441:             receiptDir: \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts\"\n1442:             dispatchId: \"review-i{current_iteration}-g{generation}\"\n1443:           assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n1444:           assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n1445:           assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n1446:           failure_reasons:\n1447:             - iteration_file_missing\n1448:             - iteration_file_empty\n1449:             - jsonl_not_appended\n1450:             - jsonl_missing_fields\n1451:             - jsonl_parse_error\n1452:             - jsonl_wrong_type\n1453:             - delta_file_missing\n1454:             - delta_file_empty\n1455:             - delta_file_missing_iteration_record\n1456:             - executor_missing\n1457:             - dispatch_failure_logged\n1458:             - v2_missing_ledger\n1459:             - v2_uncited_ledger_row\n1460:             - v2_broken_linked_finding\n1461:             - v2_shallow_finding_details\n1462:             - delta_iteration_id_mismatch\n1463:             - state_delta_iteration_mismatch\n1464:             - route_proof_missing\n1465:             - route_proof_mismatch\n1466:           warning_surface:\n1467:             source: \"result.warnings\"\n1468:             action: \"emit schema_advisory canonical conflict event\"\n1469:             severity: \"advisory\"\n1470:             event_shape: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"schema_advisory\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"warnings\":{result.warnings},\"severity\":\"advisory\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n1471:             note: \"Warnings do not fail dispatch. Hard failures still emit schema_mismatch through on_failure.\"\n1472:           on_failure:\n1473:             action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n1474:             redispatch_once: \"On the FIRST failure of the mechanical command check for this iteration, re-run step_dispatch_iteration exactly once for the same iteration number, then re-run the check. If it still fails, record the iteration as error (per step_evaluate_results.on_missing_outputs) and continue. Never re-dispatch a given iteration more than once.\"\n1475:             escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures across iterations, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n1476:         record_executor_audit:\n1477:           skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n1478:           target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1479:           field: \"executor\"\n1480:           value:\n1481:             kind: \"{config.executor.kind}\"\n1482:             model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n1483:             reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n1484:             serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n1485: \n1486:       step_evaluate_results:\n1487:         action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n1488:         verify:\n1489:           - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1490:           - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n1491:           - strategy_updated: \"Strategy.md has been modified\"\n1492:         extract:\n1493:           - newFindingsRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1494:           - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1495:           - severity_counts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record (P0, P1, P2)\"\n1496:           - dimensions: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1497:           - files_reviewed: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1498:           - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1499:           - reviewed_artifacts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n1500:           - traceability_checks: \"From latest JSONL iteration record when present\"\n1501:         on_missing_outputs:\n1502:           action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n1503:           # Canonical iteration record: include sessionId, generation, durationMs so the reducer can persist\n1504:           # the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state-format.md §Iteration Records.\n1505:           command: |\n1506:             cat <<'DEEP_LOOP_STATE_RECORD' | node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/append-state-record.cjs {state_paths.state_log}\n1507:             {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"review\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_dimension}\",\"dimensions\":[\"{next_dimension}\"],\"filesReviewed\":[],\"findingsCount\":0,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingsNew\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingDetails\":[],\"traceabilityChecks\":{\"summary\":{\"required\":0,\"executed\":0,\"pass\":0,\"partial\":0,\"fail\":0,\"blocked\":0,\"notApplicable\":0,\"gatingFailures\":0},\"results\":[]},\"newFindingsRatio\":0.0,\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation},\"lineageMode\":\"{config.lineage.lineageMode}\"}\n1508:             DEEP_LOOP_STATE_RECORD\n1509: \n1510:       step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication:\n1511:         action: \"Validate typed claim-adjudication packets for any new P0/P1 findings and persist the result to state.jsonl so the next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate can read it\"\n1512:         verify:\n1513:           - typed_packets_present: \"Every new P0/P1 finding in review/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md contains a claim-adjudication JSON block\"\n1514:           - packet_fields: \"Each packet includes claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, downgradeTrigger\"\n1515:           - missing_packet_ids: \"List of new P0/P1 finding IDs that are missing a typed packet or field; empty array when all packets validate\"\n1516:         on_pass:\n1517:           set:\n1518:             claim_adjudication_passed: true\n1519:           # Append via the deterministic stdin helper, never an edit/patch tool:\n1520:           # the state log holds multi-KB single-line records that a context-matched\n1521:           # apply_patch cannot anchor on (it halts the loop). See append-state-record.cjs.\n1522:           command: |\n1523:             cat <<'DEEP_LOOP_STATE_RECORD' | node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/append-state-record.cjs {state_paths.state_log}\n1524:             {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":true,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":[],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}\n1525:             DEEP_LOOP_STATE_RECORD\n1526:           log: \"Claim adjudication passed for iteration {current_iteration}. All new P0/P1 findings have typed packets.\"\n1527:         on_fail:\n1528:           action: \"Mark the iteration as invalid for convergence. The next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate (step_check_convergence step 0) reads the persisted `passed: false` event and vetoes STOP until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packets.\"\n1529:           set:\n1530:             claim_adjudication_passed: false\n1531:           command: |\n1532:             cat <<'DEEP_LOOP_STATE_RECORD' | node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/append-state-record.cjs {state_paths.state_log}\n1533:             {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":false,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":{missing_packet_ids},\"reason\":\"Missing typed packet fields for new P0/P1 findings\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}\n1534:             DEEP_LOOP_STATE_RECORD\n1535:           log: \"Claim adjudication incomplete for new P0/P1 findings. Event persisted. The next iteration's step_check_convergence claim-adjudication pre-check will veto STOP while `passed: false` remains the latest event and active P0/P1 > 0.\"\n1536: \n1537:       step_reduce_review_state:\n1538:         action: \"Run reducer to refresh the canonical findings registry before dashboard generation\"\n1539:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} {reducer_artifact_arg} --create-missing-anchors\"\n1540:         read:\n1541:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1542:           - \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n1543:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1544:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1545:         write:\n1546:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1547:           - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n1548:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1549:         failure_modes:\n1550:           malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n1551:           missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n1552:           schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n1553:         guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n1554:         note: \"Reducer outputs findingsRegistry, dashboardMetrics, and strategyUpdates. Re-running the same inputs must be idempotent.\"\n1555: \n1556:       step_graph_upsert:\n1557:         action: \"Project canonical review coverage plus optional graphEvents into graph nodes and edges, then upsert it\"\n1558:         read:\n1559:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1560:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1561:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1562:         transform: |\n1563:           1. Read the latest iteration JSONL record after reducer completion.\n1564:           2. Seed one stable DIMENSION node for every configured review dimension, falling back to correctness, security, traceability, and maintainability.\n1565:           3. Seed one stable FILE node for every latest-record filesReviewed entry and emit a COVERS edge from each latest-record dimension to each reviewed file.\n1566:           4. Merge optional graphEvents nodes after normalizing type = uppercase(event.kind || event.nodeKind || event.type); keep only DIMENSION, FILE, FINDING, EVIDENCE, REMEDIATION, BUG_CLASS, INVARIANT, PRODUCER, CONSUMER, TEST.\n1567:           5. Merge optional graphEvents edges after normalizing relation = uppercase(event.relation); keep only COVERS, EVIDENCE_FOR, CONTRADICTS, RESOLVES, CONFIRMS, ESCALATES, IN_DIMENSION, IN_FILE.\n1568:           6. Emit nodes as { id, type, name, iteration, metadata } and edges as { id, relation, sourceId, targetId, metadata }, deduplicated by id.\n1569:           7. Discard malformed or unknown optional events without discarding canonical dimension and file coverage.\n1570:         bash: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"review\\\" --session-id \\\"{session_id}\\\" --nodes '{graph_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_edges_json}'\"\n1571:         note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Canonical iteration fields provide baseline coverage; graphEvents add richer evidence.\"\n1572:         outputs:\n1573:           - graph_nodes_json: \"JSON array of canonical and optional review graph nodes\"\n1574:           - graph_edges_json: \"JSON array of canonical and optional review graph edges\"\n1575: \n1576:       step_generate_dashboard:\n1577:         action: \"Generate or refresh the review dashboard\"\n1578:         read:\n1579:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1580:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1581:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1582:         content: |\n1583:           # Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n1584: \n\n(Showing lines 970-1584 of 2123. Use offset=1585 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"        action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested review marker\"\n        algorithm: |\n          if current_iteration > 1:\n            PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n            if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n              PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n              if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n                log \"ERROR: nested review-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n                halt with exit code 2\n        note: |\n          False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n          three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n          True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n          starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested review-of-review dispatch.\n\n      step_dispatch_iteration:\n        action: \"Dispatch @deep-review agent for one review iteration\"\n        resolve_executor:\n          source: \"config.executor\"\n          loader: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-review-auto.yaml","text":"        action: \"H-2 loop-prevention guard: scan previous iteration's rendered prompt for nested review marker\"\n        algorithm: |\n          if current_iteration > 1:\n            PREV_PROMPT_PATH = \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{previous_iteration}.md\"\n            if file_exists(PREV_PROMPT_PATH):\n              PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE = head -1 of PREV_PROMPT_PATH\n              if PREV_PROMPT_FIRST_LINE matches ^(DEEP-REVIEW|DEEP-RESEARCH|CODE-REVIEW)$:\n                log \"ERROR: nested review-of-review loop detected (marker found in previous iteration prompt). Aborting.\"\n                halt with exit code 2\n        note: |\n          False-positive prevention: only matches when the first line is exactly one of the\n          three canonical markers. Markers appearing in comments or body text are ignored.\n          True-positive triggers only when a previous iteration's rendered prompt literally\n          starts with a deep-loop marker, indicating a nested review-of-review dispatch.\n\n      step_dispatch_iteration:\n        action: \"Dispatch @deep-review agent for one review iteration\"\n        resolve_executor:\n          source: \"config.executor\"\n          loader: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts#parseExecutorConfig\"\n        pre_dispatch:\n          generate_summary: |\n            STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n            Iteration: {current_iteration} of {max_iterations}\n            Dimension: {next_dimension}\n            Prior Findings: P0={p0_count} P1={p1_count} P2={p2_count}\n            Dimension Coverage: {dimensions_covered_list} ({dimension_coverage})\n            Traceability: core={core_protocol_status} overlay={overlay_protocol_status}\n            {resource_map_prompt_line}\n            Coverage Age: {coverage_age}\n            Last 2 ratios: {ratio_prev} -> {ratio_latest}\n            Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n            Provisional Verdict: {PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL|PENDING} hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n          render_prompt_pack:\n            template_path: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/deep-review/assets/prompt-pack-iteration.md.tmpl\"\n            renderer: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/prompt-pack.ts#renderPromptPack\"\n            output_path: \"{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md\"\n            variables:\n              state_summary: \"{state_summary}\"\n              current_iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n              max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n              next_dimension: \"{next_dimension}\"\n              review_target: \"{review_target}\"\n              review_scope_files: \"{review_scope_files}\"\n              p0_count: \"{p0_count}\"\n              p1_count: \"{p1_count}\"\n              p2_count: \"{p2_count}\"\n              pivot_lineage: \"{pivot_lineage}\"\n              saturated_directions: \"{saturated_directions}\"\n              state_paths_config: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n              state_paths_state_log: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n              state_paths_findings_registry: \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n              state_paths_strategy: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n              state_paths_iteration_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n              state_paths_delta_pattern: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n        pre_dispatch_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n          call: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts#writeFirstRecordExecutor\"\n          args:\n            stateLogPath: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n            executor: \"{config.executor}\"\n            iteration: \"{current_iteration}\"\n        branch_on: \"config.executor.kind\"\n        if_native:\n          dispatch:\n            agent: deep-review\n            model: opus\n            context_source: \"rendered_prompt_pack\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n        if_cli_copilot:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync, writeFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n            import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n            import { buildCopilotPromptArg } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts';\n\n            const promptPath = '{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md';\n            const prompt = readFileSync(promptPath, 'utf8');\n\n            // Workflow-resolved spec folder is the only legal write authority.\n            // The helper (`validateSpecFolder` inside `buildCopilotPromptArg`)\n            // is the single source of truth for rejecting empty / unresolved\n            // template / whitespace-only / string-coerced empty values. The\n            // YAML hands the raw `{spec_folder}` directly; on rejection the\n            // helper safe-fails to `type:\"missing\", writeIntent:true` (Gate-3\n            // enforcement, --allow-all-tools stripped).\n            const specFolderRaw = '{spec_folder}';\n            const targetAuthority = { type: 'approved', specFolder: specFolderRaw };\n\n            const baseArgs = [\n              '-p',\n              prompt,\n              '--model',\n              '{config.executor.model}',\n              '--allow-all-tools',\n              '--no-ask-user',\n            ];\n\n            const built = buildCopilotPromptArg({\n              promptPath,\n              prompt,\n              targetAuthority,\n              baseArgv: baseArgs,\n            });\n\n            // Large-prompt @PROMPT_PATH wrapper: helper emits a `promptFileBody`\n            // containing `<TARGET AUTHORITY preamble>\\n\\n---\\n\\n<original>`.\n            // Write it to disk so the file Copilot reads via @path opens with\n            // the authority block. Without this, recovered/bootstrap folder\n            // mentions inside the file could still anchor the model.\n            if (built.promptFileBody !== undefined) {\n              writeFileSync(promptPath, built.promptFileBody, 'utf8');\n            }\n\n            // Copilot is routed through the audited executor wrapper so it produces\n            // INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts alongside claude-code/opencode\n            // There is no cli-copilot kind in the executor schema, so it\n            // dispatches as kind:'native' (full env passthrough, no recursion-guard\n            // layer configured for copilot); the receipt still records the real\n            // 'copilot' command + built.argv as facts.\n            const dispatchFacts = {\n              command: 'deep/review',\n              mode: 'review',\n              specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n              artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n              iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n              executorKind: '{config.executor.kind}',\n              branchId: '{config.executor.kind}',\n              sessionId: '{session_id}',\n              generation: Number('{generation}'),\n            };\n            const dispatchId = 'review-i{current_iteration}-g{generation}';\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'copilot',\n                args: built.argv,\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor: {\n                  kind: 'native',\n                  model: '{config.executor.model}',\n                  configDir: null,\n                  reasoningEffort: null,\n                  serviceTier: null,\n                  sandboxMode: null,\n                  timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n                  governor: null,\n                },\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n                dispatchId,\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so copilot produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; built.argv (@PROMPT_PATH or positional) is forwarded verbatim as the receipt facts\"\n            - \"copilot has no stdin support; prompt is positional\"\n            - \"Size check uses 16KB threshold; above that uses @PROMPT_PATH wrapper prompt\"\n            - \"Large-prompt path relies on copilot honoring @path references within its prompt string\"\n            - \"buildCopilotPromptArg attaches a TARGET AUTHORITY preamble bound to the workflow-approved spec folder; recovered context cannot override it (authority guard source: .opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_deep-review_auto.yaml)\"\n            - \"If spec_folder is missing/malformed/unresolved on a write-intent dispatch, the helper enforces plan-only by replacing the prompt with a Gate-3 question and stripping --allow-all-tools\"\n            - \"Large-prompt wrapper mode rewrites the prompt file at promptPath to include the TARGET AUTHORITY preamble (prefix + divider + original body); the argv becomes a bare @promptPath reference\"\n        if_cli_claude_code:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n            import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n\n            const configDir = '{optional_claude_config_dir}';\n            const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-claude-code',\n              model: '{config.executor.model}',\n              configDir: configDir || null,\n              reasoningEffort,\n              serviceTier: null,\n              sandboxMode: null,\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n              governor: null,\n            };\n            const args = [\n              '-p',\n              readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8'),\n              '--model',\n              executor.model,\n              '--permission-mode',\n              'acceptEdits',\n              '--output-format',\n              'text',\n            ];\n            if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n              args.push('--effort', executor.reasoningEffort);\n            }\n\n            // CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR rides through guardContext.env; the CLAUDE_ prefix is\n            // on the cli-claude-code env allowlist so buildExecutorDispatchEnv admits it.\n            const parentEnv = { ...process.env };\n            if (configDir) {\n              parentEnv.CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR = configDir;\n            }\n\n            const dispatchFacts = {\n              command: 'deep/review',\n              mode: 'review',\n              specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n              artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n              iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n              executorKind: '{config.executor.kind}',\n              branchId: '{config.executor.kind}',\n              sessionId: '{session_id}',\n              generation: Number('{generation}'),\n            };\n            const dispatchId = 'review-i{current_iteration}-g{generation}';\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'claude',\n                args,\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                guardContext: { env: parentEnv },\n                receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n                dispatchId,\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          render_hint:\n            optional_claude_config_dir: |\n              If config.executor.configDir is set and non-null, expand a leading ~ to HOME and bind that path.\n              Otherwise expand to empty string.\n          notes:\n            - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so claude-code produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard + env allowlist enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n            - \"CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR is forwarded through guardContext.env (CLAUDE_ prefix is allowlisted) so account-specific Claude Code routing is preserved\"\n            - \"permission-mode stays acceptEdits (review's existing iteration-write behavior); claude-code has no serviceTier flag\"\n            - \"claude-code supports --effort for reasoning depth\"\n        if_cli_opencode:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { execFileSync } from 'node:child_process';\n            import { appendFileSync, readFileSync, realpathSync } from 'node:fs';\n            import { createHash } from 'node:crypto';\n            import { isAbsolute, relative, resolve } from 'node:path';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n\n            const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-opencode',\n              model: '{config.executor.model}',\n              configDir: null,\n              reasoningEffort,\n              serviceTier: null,\n              sandboxMode: null,\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n              governor: null,\n            };\n            const promptBody = readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8');\n            if (!promptBody.includes('BANNED OPERATIONS') || !promptBody.includes('ALLOWED WRITE PATHS')) {\n              throw new Error('Unsafe cli-opencode dispatch: rendered prompt is missing required write-containment sections');\n            }\n\n            const repoRoot = realpathSync('{repo_root}');\n            const artifactDir = resolve(repoRoot, '{state_paths.packet_dir}');\n            const artifactRelative = relative(repoRoot, artifactDir);\n            if (artifactRelative === '' || artifactRelative.startsWith('..') || isAbsolute(artifactRelative)) {\n              throw new Error('Unsafe cli-opencode dispatch: artifact directory must be a strict descendant of the worktree root');\n            }\n\n            const git = (args, cwd = repoRoot, trim = true) => {\n              const output = execFileSync('git', args, { cwd, encoding: 'utf8' });\n              return trim ? output.trim() : output;\n            };\n            const resolveGitPath = (candidate) => realpathSync(isAbsolute(candidate) ? candidate : resolve(repoRoot, candidate));\n            const gitDir = resolveGitPath(git(['rev-parse', '--git-dir']));\n            const commonGitDir = resolveGitPath(git(['rev-parse', '--git-common-dir']));\n            if (gitDir === commonGitDir) {\n              throw new Error('Unsafe cli-opencode dispatch: --dir must point at an isolated linked worktree');\n            }\n\n            const primaryBlock = git(['worktree', 'list', '--porcelain'])\n              .split(/\\n\\n+/)\n              .find((block) => /^branch refs\\/heads\\/(?:main|master)$/m.test(block));\n            const primaryLine = primaryBlock?.split('\\n').find((line) => line.startsWith('worktree '));\n            if (!primaryLine) {\n              throw new Error('Unsafe cli-opencode dispatch: primary main/master worktree could not be resolved');\n            }\n            const primaryRoot = realpathSync(primaryLine.slice('worktree '.length));\n            const primaryStatus = git(['status', '--porcelain=v1', '--untracked-files=all'], primaryRoot);\n            if (primaryStatus) {\n              throw new Error('Unsafe cli-opencode dispatch: primary worktree must be clean before unrestricted execution');\n            }\n\n            const dirtyPaths = [\n              ...git(['diff', '--name-only', '-z', 'HEAD', '--'], repoRoot, false).split('\\0'),\n              ...git(['ls-files', '--others', '--exclude-standard', '-z'], repoRoot, false).split('\\0'),\n            ].filter(Boolean);\n            const outsideArtifactDir = dirtyPaths.filter((candidate) => {\n              const candidateRelative = relative(artifactDir, resolve(repoRoot, candidate));\n              return candidateRelative.startsWith('..') || isAbsolute(candidateRelative);\n            });\n            if (outsideArtifactDir.length > 0) {\n              throw new Error(`Unsafe cli-opencode dispatch: worktree changes outside the artifact directory: ${outsideArtifactDir.join(', ')}`);\n            }\n\n            const recoveryBaselineCommit = git(['rev-parse', '--verify', 'HEAD']);\n            appendFileSync(\n              '{state_paths.state_log}',\n              `${JSON.stringify({ type: 'event', event: 'recovery_baseline', mode: 'review', iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'), recoveryBaselineCommit, worktree: repoRoot, timestamp: new Date().toISOString() })}\\n`,\n              'utf8',\n            );\n            const message = 'Resolved route: mode=review; target_agent=@deep-review; execution=single_review_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true'\n              + '\\n\\n'\n              + promptBody;\n            const args = [\n              'run',\n              '--model',\n              executor.model,\n              '--format',\n              'json',\n              '--dangerously-skip-permissions',\n              '--pure',\n              '--dir',\n              '{repo_root}',\n            ];\n            if (executor.reasoningEffort) {\n              args.push('--variant', executor.reasoningEffort);\n            }\n            args.push(message);\n\n            const dispatchFacts = {\n              command: 'deep/review',\n              mode: 'review',\n              specFolder: '{spec_folder}',\n              artifactDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}',\n              iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n              executorKind: '{config.executor.kind}',\n              branchId: '{config.executor.kind}',\n              sessionId: '{session_id}',\n              generation: Number('{generation}'),\n            };\n            const dispatchId = 'review-i{current_iteration}-g{generation}';\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'opencode',\n                args,\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                // opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup before session creation;\n                // an empty input gives EOF stdin, equivalent to </dev/null.\n                input: '',\n                receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n                dispatchId,\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so opencode produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard + env allowlist enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n            - \"Fail closed before dispatch unless the rendered containment sections exist, --dir is an isolated linked worktree, the primary worktree is clean, and current-worktree changes are confined to artifact_dir; append the recovery-baseline commit to state_log\"\n            - \"input:'' yields closed stdin (EOF), equivalent to </dev/null — opencode v1.14.39 reads stdin at startup and hangs at 0% CPU after +60s snapshot prune without it (the `cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §4 ALWAYS rule)\"\n            - \"opencode run takes a positional message; prompt is the route-proof preamble + iteration body\"\n            - \"--variant maps reasoningEffort to opencode's provider-specific reasoning lever (e.g., high, medium, minimal)\"\n            - \"--dangerously-skip-permissions enables hands-off automation; sandboxMode='read-only' is not currently honored (no opencode equivalent)\"\n            - \"cli-opencode self-invocation guard: this single-executor branch must only run from a non-OpenCode dispatch surface (Claude Code/raw shell). Explicit parallel-detached cli-opencode fan-out is handled by step_fanout_spawn_cli/fanout-run.cjs, not this branch. the `cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode` mode's SKILL.md (`.opencode/skills/cli-external-orchestration/cli-opencode/SKILL.md`) §SELF-INVOCATION PROHIBITED contract is the authoritative gate\"\n        if_cli_codex:\n          command: |\n            node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n            import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n            import { execFileSync } from 'node:child_process';\n\n            import { runAuditedExecutorCommand } from './.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts';\n\n            // Fail closed: a requested codex executor must dispatch codex or abort,\n            // never silently degrade to another executor. Undetected absence is what\n            // got Codex deprecated before, so the branch exits non-zero when the\n            // binary is missing instead of falling through to a native/other path.\n            let codexAvailable = false;\n            try {\n              execFileSync('/bin/sh', ['-c', 'command -v codex >/dev/null 2>&1'], { stdio: 'ignore' });\n              codexAvailable = true;\n            } catch {}\n            if (!codexAvailable) {\n              console.error('cli-codex executor unavailable: command -v codex failed');\n              process.exit(1);\n            }\n\n            const reasoningEffort = '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.reasoningEffort}';\n            const serviceTier = '{config.executor.serviceTier}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.serviceTier}';\n            const model = '{config.executor.model}' === 'null' ? null : '{config.executor.model}';\n            const executor = {\n              kind: 'cli-codex',\n              model,\n              configDir: null,\n              reasoningEffort,\n              serviceTier,\n              sandboxMode: 'workspace-write',\n              timeoutSeconds: Number('{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}'),\n              governor: null,\n            };\n\n            const promptBody = readFileSync('{state_paths.prompt_dir}/iteration-{current_iteration}.md', 'utf8');\n\n            // codex reads the iteration prompt from stdin via the trailing '-'. A review\n            // iteration must WRITE its own iteration file, delta and state record, so the\n            // sandbox is workspace-write — read-only would block those required writes.\n            // approval_policy=never keeps the run non-interactive.\n            const args = ['exec'];\n            if (model) {\n              args.push('--model', model);\n            }\n            args.push('-c', 'model_reasoning_effort=' + (reasoningEffort || 'medium'));\n            if (serviceTier) {\n              args.push('-c', 'service_tier=' + serviceTier);\n            }\n            args.push('-c', 'approval_policy=never', '--sandbox', executor.sandboxMode, '-');\n\n            const dispatchId = 'review-i{current_iteration}-g{generation}';\n            process.exit(\n              runAuditedExecutorCommand({\n                command: 'codex',\n                args,\n                cwd: '{repo_root}',\n                timeoutSeconds: executor.timeoutSeconds,\n                stateLogPath: '{state_paths.state_log}',\n                executor,\n                iteration: Number('{current_iteration}'),\n                input: promptBody,\n                receiptDir: '{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts',\n                dispatchId,\n              }),\n            );\n            EOF\n          working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n          timeout_seconds: \"{config.executor.timeoutSeconds}\"\n          wait_for_completion: true\n          notes:\n            - \"Routed through runAuditedExecutorCommand so codex produces INTENT + COMPLETION dispatch receipts; recursion guard (CODEX_SESSION_ID) + env allowlist (CODEX_/OPENAI_/AZURE_OPENAI_) enforced via buildExecutorDispatchEnv\"\n            - \"Fails closed when the codex binary is absent (exit 1) — parity with the fan-out cli-codex lineage guard in fanout-run.cjs; codex routing never degrades to native\"\n            - \"codex exec reads the iteration prompt from stdin via the trailing '-' (input: promptBody); '-c model_reasoning_effort=' maps reasoning depth, default medium; '-c service_tier=' forwarded when configured\"\n            - \"--sandbox workspace-write is required so the iteration can write its own iteration file/delta/state record (read-only would fail the post-dispatch artifact gate); -c approval_policy=never keeps it non-interactive; --model omitted when unset so ~/.codex/config.toml default applies\"\n        post_dispatch_validate:\n          validator: \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/lib/deep-loop/post-dispatch-validate.ts#validateIterationOutputs\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/verify-iteration.cjs --loop-type review --artifact-dir {artifact_dir} --iteration {current_iteration}\"\n          command_note: \"Mechanical leaf-reliability gate: exit 0 = complete; non-zero prints one machine reason (iteration_file_missing|iteration_verdict_missing|state_record_missing|route_proof_missing|route_proof_mismatch|delta_file_missing). The script enforces the artifact + route-proof contract instead of trusting the leaf to self-report, and a non-zero exit triggers on_failure.redispatch_once.\"\n          assert_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          assert_appended: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          assert_jsonl_fields: [type, iteration, mode, run, status, focus, dimensions, filesReviewed, findingsCount, findingsSummary, findingsNew, findingDetails, newFindingsRatio, sessionId, generation, lineageMode, timestamp, durationMs]\n          route_proof:\n            mode: review\n            target_agent: deep-review\n            agent_definition_loaded: true\n            resolved_route: \"Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review\"\n          dispatchReceipt:\n            receiptDir: \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dispatch-receipts\"\n            dispatchId: \"review-i{current_iteration}-g{generation}\"\n          assert_canonical_type: \"iteration\"\n          assert_delta_file_exists: \"{state_paths.delta_pattern}\"\n          assert_delta_file_has_iteration_record: true\n          failure_reasons:\n            - iteration_file_missing\n            - iteration_file_empty\n            - jsonl_not_appended\n            - jsonl_missing_fields\n            - jsonl_parse_error\n            - jsonl_wrong_type\n            - delta_file_missing\n            - delta_file_empty\n            - delta_file_missing_iteration_record\n            - executor_missing\n            - dispatch_failure_logged\n            - v2_missing_ledger\n            - v2_uncited_ledger_row\n            - v2_broken_linked_finding\n            - v2_shallow_finding_details\n            - delta_iteration_id_mismatch\n            - state_delta_iteration_mismatch\n            - route_proof_missing\n            - route_proof_mismatch\n          warning_surface:\n            source: \"result.warnings\"\n            action: \"emit schema_advisory canonical conflict event\"\n            severity: \"advisory\"\n            event_shape: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"schema_advisory\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"warnings\":{result.warnings},\"severity\":\"advisory\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n            note: \"Warnings do not fail dispatch. Hard failures still emit schema_mismatch through on_failure.\"\n          on_failure:\n            action: \"emit schema_mismatch canonical conflict event\"\n            redispatch_once: \"On the FIRST failure of the mechanical command check for this iteration, re-run step_dispatch_iteration exactly once for the same iteration number, then re-run the check. If it still fails, record the iteration as error (per step_evaluate_results.on_missing_outputs) and continue. Never re-dispatch a given iteration more than once.\"\n            escalation: \"After 3 consecutive failures across iterations, trigger stuck_recovery event with diagnostic context\"\n        record_executor_audit:\n          skip_when: \"config.executor.kind == 'native'\"\n          target: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          field: \"executor\"\n          value:\n            kind: \"{config.executor.kind}\"\n            model: \"{config.executor.model}\"\n            reasoningEffort: \"{config.executor.reasoningEffort}\"\n            serviceTier: \"{config.executor.serviceTier}\"\n\n      step_evaluate_results:\n        action: \"Verify iteration outputs and extract metrics\"\n        verify:\n          - file_exists: \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - jsonl_appended: \"New iteration record in state.jsonl\"\n          - strategy_updated: \"Strategy.md has been modified\"\n        extract:\n          - newFindingsRatio: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - findings_count: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - severity_counts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record (P0, P1, P2)\"\n          - dimensions: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - files_reviewed: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - status: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - reviewed_artifacts: \"From latest JSONL iteration record\"\n          - traceability_checks: \"From latest JSONL iteration record when present\"\n        on_missing_outputs:\n          action: \"Mark iteration as 'error', continue to next\"\n          # Canonical iteration record: include sessionId, generation, durationMs so the reducer can persist\n          # the failure without dropping the iteration. Schema source: state-format.md §Iteration Records.\n          command: |\n            cat <<'DEEP_LOOP_STATE_RECORD' | node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/append-state-record.cjs {state_paths.state_log}\n            {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"iteration\":{current_iteration},\"run\":{current_iteration},\"mode\":\"review\",\"status\":\"error\",\"focus\":\"{next_dimension}\",\"dimensions\":[\"{next_dimension}\"],\"filesReviewed\":[],\"findingsCount\":0,\"findingsSummary\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingsNew\":{\"P0\":0,\"P1\":0,\"P2\":0},\"findingDetails\":[],\"traceabilityChecks\":{\"summary\":{\"required\":0,\"executed\":0,\"pass\":0,\"partial\":0,\"fail\":0,\"blocked\":0,\"notApplicable\":0,\"gatingFailures\":0},\"results\":[]},\"newFindingsRatio\":0.0,\"durationMs\":0,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation},\"lineageMode\":\"{config.lineage.lineageMode}\"}\n            DEEP_LOOP_STATE_RECORD\n\n      step_post_iteration_claim_adjudication:\n        action: \"Validate typed claim-adjudication packets for any new P0/P1 findings and persist the result to state.jsonl so the next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate can read it\"\n        verify:\n          - typed_packets_present: \"Every new P0/P1 finding in review/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md contains a claim-adjudication JSON block\"\n          - packet_fields: \"Each packet includes claim, evidenceRefs, counterevidenceSought, alternativeExplanation, finalSeverity, confidence, downgradeTrigger\"\n          - missing_packet_ids: \"List of new P0/P1 finding IDs that are missing a typed packet or field; empty array when all packets validate\"\n        on_pass:\n          set:\n            claim_adjudication_passed: true\n          # Append via the deterministic stdin helper, never an edit/patch tool:\n          # the state log holds multi-KB single-line records that a context-matched\n          # apply_patch cannot anchor on (it halts the loop). See append-state-record.cjs.\n          command: |\n            cat <<'DEEP_LOOP_STATE_RECORD' | node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/append-state-record.cjs {state_paths.state_log}\n            {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":true,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":[],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}\n            DEEP_LOOP_STATE_RECORD\n          log: \"Claim adjudication passed for iteration {current_iteration}. All new P0/P1 findings have typed packets.\"\n        on_fail:\n          action: \"Mark the iteration as invalid for convergence. The next iteration's claimAdjudicationGate (step_check_convergence step 0) reads the persisted `passed: false` event and vetoes STOP until a follow-up iteration rewrites the packets.\"\n          set:\n            claim_adjudication_passed: false\n          command: |\n            cat <<'DEEP_LOOP_STATE_RECORD' | node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/append-state-record.cjs {state_paths.state_log}\n            {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"claim_adjudication\",\"mode\":\"review\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"passed\":false,\"activeP0P1\":{active_p0_p1_count},\"missingPackets\":{missing_packet_ids},\"reason\":\"Missing typed packet fields for new P0/P1 findings\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"generation\":{generation}}\n            DEEP_LOOP_STATE_RECORD\n          log: \"Claim adjudication incomplete for new P0/P1 findings. Event persisted. The next iteration's step_check_convergence claim-adjudication pre-check will veto STOP while `passed: false` remains the latest event and active P0/P1 > 0.\"\n\n      step_reduce_review_state:\n        action: \"Run reducer to refresh the canonical findings registry before dashboard generation\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} {reducer_artifact_arg} --create-missing-anchors\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.iteration_pattern}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        write:\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        failure_modes:\n          malformed_delta: \"skip + warn\"\n          missing_iteration_file: \"no-op + error\"\n          schema_mismatch: \"reject + conflict event\"\n        guarantee: \"Idempotent for identical inputs\"\n        note: \"Reducer outputs findingsRegistry, dashboardMetrics, and strategyUpdates. Re-running the same inputs must be idempotent.\"\n\n      step_graph_upsert:\n        action: \"Project canonical review coverage plus optional graphEvents into graph nodes and edges, then upsert it\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n        transform: |\n          1. Read the latest iteration JSONL record after reducer completion.\n          2. Seed one stable DIMENSION node for every configured review dimension, falling back to correctness, security, traceability, and maintainability.\n          3. Seed one stable FILE node for every latest-record filesReviewed entry and emit a COVERS edge from each latest-record dimension to each reviewed file.\n          4. Merge optional graphEvents nodes after normalizing type = uppercase(event.kind || event.nodeKind || event.type); keep only DIMENSION, FILE, FINDING, EVIDENCE, REMEDIATION, BUG_CLASS, INVARIANT, PRODUCER, CONSUMER, TEST.\n          5. Merge optional graphEvents edges after normalizing relation = uppercase(event.relation); keep only COVERS, EVIDENCE_FOR, CONTRADICTS, RESOLVES, CONFIRMS, ESCALATES, IN_DIMENSION, IN_FILE.\n          6. Emit nodes as { id, type, name, iteration, metadata } and edges as { id, relation, sourceId, targetId, metadata }, deduplicated by id.\n          7. Discard malformed or unknown optional events without discarding canonical dimension and file coverage.\n        bash: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs --spec-folder \\\"{spec_folder}\\\" --loop-type \\\"review\\\" --session-id \\\"{session_id}\\\" --nodes '{graph_nodes_json}' --edges '{graph_edges_json}'\"\n        note: \"Invoke the runtime script directly. Canonical iteration fields provide baseline coverage; graphEvents add richer evidence.\"\n        outputs:\n          - graph_nodes_json: \"JSON array of canonical and optional review graph nodes\"\n          - graph_edges_json: \"JSON array of canonical and optional review graph edges\"\n\n      step_generate_dashboard:\n        action: \"Generate or refresh the review dashboard\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        content: |\n          # Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n","lineStart":970,"lineEnd":1584,"totalLines":2123,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-review-auto.yaml","time":{"start":1784650212477,"end":1784650212587}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03f0e82d94f6d585016a5f99e44d388191b11297616ae21ac2"}},"id":"prt_f85712479001vd0GeqoRe6EZrw","sessionID":"ses_07a91b76bffeQVZz6UB7PapKuO","messageID":"msg_f8570c374001ieeOYdHuun9tY9"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784650212597,"sessionID":"ses_07a91b76bffeQVZz6UB7PapKuO","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_JNKuQ3Ov6ZbUxWLan2fwUgKa","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-review-auto.yaml","offset":1640,"limit":450},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-review-auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1640:       step_loop_decision:\n1641:         action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n1642:         goto: step_read_state\n1643: \n1644:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1645:   # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n1646:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1647:   phase_synthesis:\n1648:     purpose: Compile all iteration findings into review/review-report.md\n1649:     steps:\n1650: \n1651:       step_fanout_merge:\n1652:         description: \"Merge N lineage registries with strongest-restriction; bind p0/p1/p2 counts for step_derive_verdict; skip when single-executor\"\n1653:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n1654:         command: |\n1655:           node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n1656:             --loop-type review \\\n1657:             --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n1658:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1659:         wait_for_completion: true\n1660:         bind_from_output:\n1661:           p0_count: \"active_p0\"\n1662:           p1_count: \"active_p1\"\n1663:           p2_count: \"active_p2\"\n1664: \n1665:       step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n1666:         action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n1667:         read:\n1668:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1669:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1670:           - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n1671:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1672:         extract:\n1673:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n1674:           - p0_count: \"Total P0 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n1675:           - p1_count: \"Total P1 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n1676:           - p2_count: \"Total P2 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n1677:           - dimensions_covered: \"List of reviewed dimensions\"\n1678:           - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total\"\n1679:           - ac_coverage_signal: \"For spec-folder targets only: if level is 2+ and checklist.md exists and implementation-summary.md is in-progress or later, surface the AC_COVERAGE advisory status; otherwise mark exempt.\"\n1680:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records\"\n1681:           - reason: \"Use the latest stop reason if present, else the frozen default 'converged'. (Must be a member of the STOP_REASONS enum: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused.)\"\n1682: \n1683:       # H-1 verdict derivation: parse findings JSONL, map highest severity to verdict\n1684:       # - PASS: no P0 or P1 findings (P2-only or clean)\n1685:       # - CONDITIONAL: any P1 findings (no P0)\n1686:       # - FAIL: any P0 findings\n1687:       # Final line of iteration-NNN.md MUST be exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" / \"Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\" / \"Review verdict: FAIL\"\n1688:       step_derive_verdict:\n1689:         action: \"Derive review verdict from accumulated findings\"\n1690:         algorithm: |\n1691:           if p0_count > 0:\n1692:             verdict = \"FAIL\"\n1693:           elif p1_count > 0:\n1694:             verdict = \"CONDITIONAL\"\n1695:           else:\n1696:             verdict = \"PASS\"\n1697:           has_advisories = (verdict == \"PASS\" and p2_count > 0)\n1698:           ac_coverage_signal is advisory while the validation rule is INFO/default-off; include it in synthesis traceability, but do not change the exact verdict enum from this signal alone.\n1699:         outputs:\n1700:           - verdict: \"PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\"\n1701:           - has_advisories: \"Boolean true when verdict is PASS and any active P2 findings exist\"\n1702:           - ac_coverage_signal: \"exempt | disabled | pass | advisory-shortfall\"\n1703:         contract: |\n1704:           Every iteration-NNN.md must end with exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" (or CONDITIONAL or FAIL).\n1705:           Downstream automation parses this final line via exact string match — do not vary the format.\n1706: \n1707:       step_read_all_iterations:\n1708:         action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n1709:         read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n1710:         read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1711: \n1712:       step_build_finding_registry:\n1713:         action: \"Build deduplicated finding registry from all iterations\"\n1714:         algorithm: |\n1715:           1. Extract all findings from iteration JSONL delta files\n1716:           2. Compute content_hash for each finding (emission requirement):\n1717:              content_hash = sha256(file_path + \"\\u001f\" + line_range + \"\\u001f\" + finding_type + \"\\u001f\" + normalized_description_80chars)\n1718:              Normalized description = whitespace-collapsed, lowercased, first 80 chars of the finding description.\n1719:           3. Two-tier dedup:\n1720:              PRIMARY: group by content_hash field\n1721:                - Same content_hash, multiple dimensions → single finding, merged `dimensions: [<all>]` array\n1722:                - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n1723:              FALLBACK (legacy records lacking content_hash): file:line + normalized_title\n1724:                - Same file:line, multiple dimensions → single finding, multiple dimension tags\n1725:                - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n1726:           4. Track finding lifecycle:\n1727:              - status: active | duplicate | upgraded | downgraded | contested | resolved_false_positive\n1728:              - Record first_seen, upgraded_in, previous_severity for severity changes\n1729:              - Record dimensions array reflecting all dimensions that emitted this finding\n1730:           5. Resolve contradictions:\n1731:              - Findings marked contested across iterations → referee pass\n1732:              - Determine final severity and status\n1733:           6. Count only 'active' findings for totals\n1734:         outputs:\n1735:           - finding_registry: \"Deduplicated list of all findings with metadata\"\n1736:           - active_p0: \"Count of active P0 findings\"\n1737:           - active_p1: \"Count of active P1 findings\"\n1738:           - active_p2: \"Count of active P2 findings\"\n1739: \n1740:       step_adversarial_selfcheck:\n1741:         action: \"Final adversarial self-check on all P0 and P1 findings\"\n1742:         algorithm: |\n1743:           For each active P0/P1 finding:\n1744:             1. Hunter: Re-verify finding against source code (re-read file:line)\n1745:             2. Skeptic: Challenge severity — is this really P0/P1? Could it be P2?\n1746:             3. Referee: Final call — confirm, downgrade, or mark false_positive\n1747:           Update finding_registry with adjudicated results.\n1748: \n1749:       step_emit_resource_map:\n1750:         action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged review deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n1751:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} {reducer_artifact_arg} --create-missing-anchors --emit-resource-map\"\n1752:         read:\n1753:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1754:           - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n1755:         write:\n1756:           - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n1757:         guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n1758: \n1759:       step_resource_map_coverage_gate:\n1760:         action: \"If resource_map_present, compute the Resource Map Coverage Gate synthesis inputs; otherwise preserve the skip note\"\n1761:         note: \"Cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md. Report touched entries, untouched entries split into expected-by-scope vs gap, and implementation paths absent from the map. Findings raised here use category resource-map-coverage with severity calibrated to the gate outcome.\"\n1762: \n1763:       step_compile_review_report:\n1764:         action: \"Compile review/review-report.md with 9 core sections, a conditional Resource Map Coverage Gate section, and an embedded Planning Packet\"\n1765:         instructions: |\n1766:           Create review/review-report.md with the following sections:\n1767: \n1768:           1. **Executive Summary**\n1769:              - Overall verdict: PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\n1770:              - hasAdvisories: true when PASS carries active P2 items\n1771:              - P0/P1/P2 counts (active only)\n1772:              - Review scope summary\n1773: \n1774:           2. **Planning Trigger**\n1775:              - State whether `/speckit:plan` is required\n1776:              - Include a fenced `json` block labeled `Planning Packet`\n1777:              - The packet MUST include: `triggered`, `verdict`, `hasAdvisories`, `activeFindings`, `remediationWorkstreams`, `specSeed`, `planSeed`, `findingClasses`, `affectedSurfacesSeed`, `fixCompletenessRequired`\n1778:              - Build `activeFindings`, `findingClasses`, and `affectedSurfacesSeed` from reducer-owned state plus iteration JSONL `findingDetails`; if a field is missing, mark it `UNKNOWN` instead of inferring it from prose\n1779: \n1780:           3. **Active Finding Registry**\n1781:              - Unified registry for active P0/P1/P2 findings\n1782:              - For each: ID, severity, title, dimension, file:line, evidence, impact, fix recommendation, disposition, findingClass, scopeProof, affectedSurfaceHints\n1783: \n1784:           4. **Remediation Workstreams**\n1785:              - Ordered action groups: P0 first, then P1, with P2 advisories separated\n1786: \n1787:           5. **Spec Seed**\n1788:              - Concrete seed bullets for follow-on spec updates\n1789: \n1790:           6. **Plan Seed**\n1791:              - Concrete starter tasks for `/speckit:plan`\n1792: \n1793:            7. **Traceability Status**\n1794:               - Summarize required core protocols first, then applicable overlay protocols\n1795:               - Include status, evidence, and any unresolved drift per protocol\n1796:               - Include `AC_COVERAGE` status for lifecycle-active spec-folder targets: exempt, disabled, pass, or advisory-shortfall, with covered/total and floor when available\n1797: \n1798:           If `resource_map_present` is true, insert **## Resource Map Coverage Gate** after `Traceability Status` with exactly three bullets:\n1799:              - `Entries touched`: count of resource-map paths that appear in applied reports\n1800:              - `Entries not touched`: paths in resource-map not in implementation, labeled `expected-by-scope` or `gap`\n1801:              - `Implementation paths absent from resource-map`: `target_files` in applied reports not on the map\n1802: \n1803:           8. **Deferred Items**\n1804:              - Advisory-only or backlog-worthy follow-ups that do not block the current verdict\n1805: \n1806:           **Dimension Expansion Map**\n1807:              - Insert `## Dimension Expansion Map` after Deferred Items and before Search Ledger.\n1808:              - Render reducer-owned `divergence.saturatedDirections`, completed pivots, failed pivots, audited overrides, Council artifact references, selected review directions, and remaining frontier.\n1809:              - This section records breadth only. It cannot alter the Executive Summary verdict, hasAdvisories, finding registry, or adversarial self-check results.\n1810: \n1811:           9. **Search Ledger**\n1812:              - Always include this section before the appendix.\n1813:              - Render reducer-owned `searchCoverage`, `candidateCoverage`, `searchDebt`, `ruledOutCandidates`, and `cleanSearchProof`.\n1814:              - If all arrays are empty or absent, include: `*No search-depth state captured (legacy v1 record)*`.\n1815:              - When `searchDebt` is non-empty, state `hasSearchDebt: true` and carry the dashboard verdict as CONDITIONAL unless active P0 findings make it FAIL.\n1816: \n1817:           10. **Audit Appendix**\n1818:              - Convergence summary, coverage summary, ruled-out claims, sources reviewed\n1819:              - Cross-reference appendix MUST be split into `Core Protocols` and `Overlay Protocols`\n1820: \n1821:           Preserve machine-owned markers so the reducer-owned registry, dashboard, and strategy anchors can be refreshed on re-run without mutating prior synthesis. (Note: `completed-continue` lineage branch is deferred — see `deep-review/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches`.)\n1822:         output: \"{state_paths.review_output}\"\n1823: \n1824:       step_convergence_report:\n1825:         action: \"Append convergence report to JSONL\"\n1826:         command: |\n1827:           node --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1828:           import { appendFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync, statSync } from 'node:fs';\n1829: \n1830:           const paths = {\n1831:             stateLog: String.raw`{state_paths.state_log}`,\n1832:             registry: String.raw`{state_paths.findings_registry}`,\n1833:             review: String.raw`{state_paths.review_output}`,\n1834:             dashboard: String.raw`{state_paths.dashboard}`,\n1835:           };\n1836: \n1837:           function hasFile(filePath) {\n1838:             try {\n1839:               return existsSync(filePath) && statSync(filePath).isFile();\n1840:             } catch {\n1841:               return false;\n1842:             }\n1843:           }\n1844: \n1845:           function readJson(filePath) {\n1846:             try {\n1847:               return JSON.parse(readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8'));\n1848:             } catch {\n1849:               return null;\n1850:             }\n1851:           }\n1852: \n1853:           function readJsonl(filePath) {\n1854:             if (!hasFile(filePath)) return [];\n1855:             return readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8')\n1856:               .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n1857:               .map((line) => line.trim())\n1858:               .filter(Boolean)\n1859:               .flatMap((line) => {\n1860:                 try {\n1861:                   return [JSON.parse(line)];\n1862:                 } catch {\n1863:                   return [];\n1864:                 }\n1865:               });\n1866:           }\n1867: \n1868:           function countIterationFindings(record) {\n1869:             if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration') return 0;\n1870:             const numeric = Number(record.findingsCount);\n1871:             if (Number.isFinite(numeric) && numeric > 0) return Math.floor(numeric);\n1872:             if (Array.isArray(record.findingDetails)) return record.findingDetails.length;\n1873:             return 0;\n1874:           }\n1875: \n1876:           function normalizeFindingKey(value) {\n1877:             return String(value || '').trim().toLowerCase().replace(/\\s+/g, ' ');\n1878:           }\n1879: \n1880:           function findingKeys(candidate) {\n1881:             if (typeof candidate === 'string') {\n1882:               const key = normalizeFindingKey(candidate);\n1883:               return key ? [key] : [];\n1884:             }\n1885:             if (!candidate || typeof candidate !== 'object' || Array.isArray(candidate)) return [];\n1886:             return [...new Set([\n1887:               candidate.id,\n1888:               candidate.findingId,\n1889:               candidate.title,\n1890:               candidate.summary,\n1891:               candidate.text,\n1892:               candidate.finding,\n1893:               candidate.description,\n1894:             ].map(normalizeFindingKey).filter(Boolean))];\n1895:           }\n1896: \n1897:           function collectIterationFindingGroups(record) {\n1898:             if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration' || !Array.isArray(record.findingDetails)) return [];\n1899:             return record.findingDetails\n1900:               .map(findingKeys)\n1901:               .filter((keys) => keys.length > 0);\n1902:           }\n1903: \n1904:           function collectRegistryFindingKeys(registry) {\n1905:             return [registry?.openFindings, registry?.resolvedFindings, registry?.repeatedFindings]\n1906:               .filter(Array.isArray)\n1907:               .flatMap((findings) => findings)\n1908:               .flatMap(findingKeys);\n1909:           }\n1910: \n1911:           function appendEvent(event) {\n1912:             appendFileSync(paths.stateLog, `${JSON.stringify(event)}\\n`, 'utf8');\n1913:           }\n1914: \n1915:           const registry = readJson(paths.registry);\n1916:           const openCount = Array.isArray(registry?.openFindings) ? registry.openFindings.length : null;\n1917:           const resolvedCount = Array.isArray(registry?.resolvedFindings) ? registry.resolvedFindings.length : 0;\n1918:           const repeatedCount = Array.isArray(registry?.repeatedFindings) ? registry.repeatedFindings.length : 0;\n1919:           const registryFindingCount = openCount === null ? null : openCount + resolvedCount + repeatedCount;\n1920:           const stateRecords = readJsonl(paths.stateLog);\n1921:           const iterationFindingCount = stateRecords.reduce((sum, record) => sum + countIterationFindings(record), 0);\n1922:           const identifiableFindingGroups = stateRecords.flatMap(collectIterationFindingGroups);\n1923:           const registryFindingKeys = new Set(collectRegistryFindingKeys(registry));\n1924:           const missingStructuredFindingCount = identifiableFindingGroups.filter((keys) => !keys.some((key) => registryFindingKeys.has(key))).length;\n1925:           const identifiableFindingCount = identifiableFindingGroups.length;\n1926:           const missingArtifacts = [\n1927:             ['registry', paths.registry],\n1928:             ['review', paths.review],\n1929:             ['dashboard', paths.dashboard],\n1930:           ].filter(([, filePath]) => !hasFile(filePath)).map(([name, filePath]) => ({ name, path: filePath }));\n1931:           const invariantFailures = [];\n1932:           if (missingArtifacts.length > 0) invariantFailures.push('missing_synthesis_artifacts');\n1933:           if (registryFindingCount === null) invariantFailures.push('registry_missing_openFindings');\n1934:           if (iterationFindingCount > 0 && (registryFindingCount ?? 0) === 0) invariantFailures.push('state_findings_not_reflected_in_registry');\n1935:           if (identifiableFindingCount > 0 && registryFindingCount !== null && registryFindingCount < identifiableFindingCount) invariantFailures.push('structured_state_findings_partially_reflected_in_registry');\n1936:           if (missingStructuredFindingCount > 0) invariantFailures.push('structured_state_findings_missing_from_registry');\n1937: \n1938:           if (invariantFailures.length > 0) {\n1939:             appendEvent({\n1940:               type: 'event',\n1941:               event: 'synthesis_incomplete',\n1942:               mode: 'review',\n1943:               severity: 'warning',\n1944:               totalIterations: Number('{iteration_count}'),\n1945:               activeP0: Number('{active_p0}'),\n1946:               activeP1: Number('{active_p1}'),\n1947:               activeP2: Number('{active_p2}'),\n1948:               dimensionCoverage: Number('{dimension_coverage}'),\n1949:               verdict: '{verdict}',\n1950:               releaseReadinessState: '{release_readiness_state}',\n1951:               stopReason: '{reason}',\n1952:               reason: 'synthesis_artifact_invariant_failed',\n1953:               invariantFailures,\n1954:               missingArtifacts,\n1955:               registryFindingCount,\n1956:               iterationFindingCount,\n1957:               identifiableFindingCount,\n1958:               missingStructuredFindingCount,\n1959:               timestamp: '{ISO_8601_NOW}',\n1960:             });\n1961:           } else {\n1962:             appendEvent({\n1963:               type: 'event',\n1964:               event: 'synthesis_complete',\n1965:               mode: 'review',\n1966:               totalIterations: Number('{iteration_count}'),\n1967:               activeP0: Number('{active_p0}'),\n1968:               activeP1: Number('{active_p1}'),\n1969:               activeP2: Number('{active_p2}'),\n1970:               dimensionCoverage: Number('{dimension_coverage}'),\n1971:               verdict: '{verdict}',\n1972:               releaseReadinessState: '{release_readiness_state}',\n1973:               stopReason: '{reason}',\n1974:               timestamp: '{ISO_8601_NOW}',\n1975:             });\n1976:           }\n1977:           EOF\n1978:         note: \"Emit as numeric ratio (e.g., 0.75), not quoted string. Compute: dimensions_covered / total_dimensions.\"\n1979: \n1980:       step_update_config_status:\n1981:         action: \"Mark config as complete\"\n1982:         edit: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1983:         set_field: { status: \"complete\" }\n1984: \n1985:       step_leave_artifacts_unstaged:\n1986:         action: \"Leave all synthesized artifacts unstaged for explicit operator review\"\n1987:         note: \"Synthesis must not mutate the shared Git index. The operator retains staging and commit authority after reviewing the complete artifact directory.\"\n1988: \n1989:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1990:   # PHASE 4: SAVE\n1991:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1992:   phase_save:\n1993:     purpose: Preserve review context to memory system\n1994:     steps:\n1995: \n1996:       step_compose_save_payload:\n1997:         action: \"Compose the structured JSON payload consumed by generate-context.js\"\n1998:         output: \"/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json\"\n1999:         requirements:\n2000:           - \"Write this file before invoking generate-context.js; the loader fails closed if the explicit JSON file is absent.\"\n2001:           - \"Include `specFolder`, a concise `sessionSummary`, curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` from the completed review loop.\"\n2002:           - \"Use a session-scoped temp filename; do not use the retired shared `/tmp/save-context-data.json` path.\"\n2003:         example_payload: |\n2004:           {\n2005:             \"specFolder\": \"{spec_folder}\",\n2006:             \"sessionSummary\": \"Deep review completed; see review/review-report.md for verdict, findings, and workstreams.\",\n2007:             \"observations\": [\"Summarize the active findings, verdict, and remediation guidance.\"],\n2008:             \"recent_context\": [\"Point to the generated review artifacts and next action.\"],\n2009:             \"exchanges\": [],\n2010:             \"toolCalls\": []\n2011:           }\n2012: \n2013:       step_generate_context:\n2014:         action: \"Route continuity content into the correct canonical spec document via generate-context.js\"\n2015:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json {spec_folder}\"\n2016:         critical_rule: \"NEVER manually author files under retired memory/ paths (the runtime rejects them); use generate-context.js so the save routes into decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md\"\n2017: \n2018:       step_index_memory:\n2019:         action: \"Index the routed canonical spec document with memory_save when immediate MCP visibility is required\"\n2020:         mcp_tool: memory_save\n2021:         invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"[routed-canonical-spec-doc-path]\" })'\n2022:         note: \"Use the actual canonical spec-doc path returned by generate-context.js (decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md); memory_index_scan remains the bulk fallback\"\n2023: \n2024:       step_verify_save:\n2025:         action: \"Verify canonical save routed content into the correct spec document\"\n2026:         check: \"Does {spec_folder}/implementation-summary.md, {spec_folder}/decision-record.md, or {spec_folder}/handover.md carry the new continuity update?\"\n2027:         on_fail: \"Log warning but do not block completion\"\n2028: \n2029:       step_release_lock:\n2030:         action: \"Release the single-writer lock after save, skip-save, or cancellation cleanup has resolved\"\n2031:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}\"\n2032:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"lock_released\",\"path\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"releasePhase\":\"save\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n2033: \n2034:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n2035:   # COMPLETION\n2036:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n2037:   completion:\n2038:     message: |\n2039:       Deep review complete.\n2040:       Iterations: {iteration_count} | Stop reason: {reason}\n2041:       Findings: P0={active_p0} P1={active_p1} P2={active_p2}\n2042:       Verdict: {verdict} | hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n2043: \n2044:       Artifacts:\n2045:         - review/review-report.md (compiled from {iteration_count} iterations)\n2046:         - {iteration_count} iteration files in review/iterations/\n2047:         - State files in review/: deep-review-config.json, deep-review-state.jsonl, deep-review-findings-registry.json, deep-review-strategy.md, deep-review-dashboard.md\n2048:         - Memory context saved\n2049: \n2050:       STATUS=OK PATH={spec_folder}\n2051:     next_steps:\n2052:       - \"/speckit:plan [remediation] (if FAIL or CONDITIONAL verdict)\"\n2053:       - \"/create:changelog (if PASS, including PASS with hasAdvisories=true)\"\n2054:       - \"/deep:review [target] (for another review)\"\n2055:       - \"/memory:save {spec_folder} (refresh canonical continuity before the next session)\"\n2056: \n2057: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2058: # ERROR RECOVERY\n2059: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2060: error_recovery:\n2061:   agent_dispatch_timeout: \"Retry once with reduced scope (fewer files per iteration). If second timeout, mark as 'timeout' and continue.\"\n2062:   state_file_missing: \"If JSONL missing during loop, reconstruct from iteration files. If strategy missing, create minimal version.\"\n2063:   consecutive_failures: \"After 3 consecutive errors, halt loop and enter synthesis with partial findings.\"\n2064:   memory_save_failure: \"Preserve the review packet in review/ as backup. Log warning.\"\n2065: \n2066: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2067: # RULES\n2068: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2069: rules:\n2070:   ALWAYS:\n2071:     - follow_workflow_phases_in_order\n2072:     - dispatch_deep_review_agent_per_iteration\n2073:     - check_convergence_before_each_iteration\n2074:     - write_all_state_to_files\n2075:     - save_memory_context_after_synthesis\n2076:     - respect_max_iterations_cap\n2077:     - treat_review_target_as_read_only\n2078:     - deduplicate_findings_before_synthesis\n2079:     - run_adversarial_selfcheck_on_p0_p1\n2080:   NEVER:\n2081:     - skip_convergence_check\n2082:     - dispatch_non_leaf_agents\n2083:     - hold_iteration_findings_in_memory_only\n2084:     - modify_config_after_initialization\n2085:     - overwrite_jsonl_state_log\n2086:     - proceed_without_state_file_verification\n2087:     - modify_files_under_review\n2088:     - report_p0_without_file_line_evidence\n2089: \n\n(Showing lines 1640-2089 of 2123. Use offset=2090 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"      step_loop_decision:\n        action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n        goto: step_read_state\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_synthesis:\n    purpose: Compile all iteration findings into review/review-report.md\n    steps:\n\n      step_fanout_merge:\n        description: \"Merge N lineage registries with strongest-restriction; bind p0/p1/p2 counts for step_derive_verdict; skip when single-executor\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n            --loop-type review \\\n            --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-review-auto.yaml","text":"      step_loop_decision:\n        action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n        goto: step_read_state\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_synthesis:\n    purpose: Compile all iteration findings into review/review-report.md\n    steps:\n\n      step_fanout_merge:\n        description: \"Merge N lineage registries with strongest-restriction; bind p0/p1/p2 counts for step_derive_verdict; skip when single-executor\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n            --loop-type review \\\n            --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n        bind_from_output:\n          p0_count: \"active_p0\"\n          p1_count: \"active_p1\"\n          p2_count: \"active_p2\"\n\n      step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n        action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.findings_registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - p0_count: \"Total P0 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n          - p1_count: \"Total P1 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n          - p2_count: \"Total P2 findings across all iterations (deduped)\"\n          - dimensions_covered: \"List of reviewed dimensions\"\n          - dimension_coverage: \"covered / total\"\n          - ac_coverage_signal: \"For spec-folder targets only: if level is 2+ and checklist.md exists and implementation-summary.md is in-progress or later, surface the AC_COVERAGE advisory status; otherwise mark exempt.\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records\"\n          - reason: \"Use the latest stop reason if present, else the frozen default 'converged'. (Must be a member of the STOP_REASONS enum: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused.)\"\n\n      # H-1 verdict derivation: parse findings JSONL, map highest severity to verdict\n      # - PASS: no P0 or P1 findings (P2-only or clean)\n      # - CONDITIONAL: any P1 findings (no P0)\n      # - FAIL: any P0 findings\n      # Final line of iteration-NNN.md MUST be exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" / \"Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\" / \"Review verdict: FAIL\"\n      step_derive_verdict:\n        action: \"Derive review verdict from accumulated findings\"\n        algorithm: |\n          if p0_count > 0:\n            verdict = \"FAIL\"\n          elif p1_count > 0:\n            verdict = \"CONDITIONAL\"\n          else:\n            verdict = \"PASS\"\n          has_advisories = (verdict == \"PASS\" and p2_count > 0)\n          ac_coverage_signal is advisory while the validation rule is INFO/default-off; include it in synthesis traceability, but do not change the exact verdict enum from this signal alone.\n        outputs:\n          - verdict: \"PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\"\n          - has_advisories: \"Boolean true when verdict is PASS and any active P2 findings exist\"\n          - ac_coverage_signal: \"exempt | disabled | pass | advisory-shortfall\"\n        contract: |\n          Every iteration-NNN.md must end with exactly: \"Review verdict: PASS\" (or CONDITIONAL or FAIL).\n          Downstream automation parses this final line via exact string match — do not vary the format.\n\n      step_read_all_iterations:\n        action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n        read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n        read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_build_finding_registry:\n        action: \"Build deduplicated finding registry from all iterations\"\n        algorithm: |\n          1. Extract all findings from iteration JSONL delta files\n          2. Compute content_hash for each finding (emission requirement):\n             content_hash = sha256(file_path + \"\\u001f\" + line_range + \"\\u001f\" + finding_type + \"\\u001f\" + normalized_description_80chars)\n             Normalized description = whitespace-collapsed, lowercased, first 80 chars of the finding description.\n          3. Two-tier dedup:\n             PRIMARY: group by content_hash field\n               - Same content_hash, multiple dimensions → single finding, merged `dimensions: [<all>]` array\n               - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n             FALLBACK (legacy records lacking content_hash): file:line + normalized_title\n               - Same file:line, multiple dimensions → single finding, multiple dimension tags\n               - Keep highest severity on duplicates\n          4. Track finding lifecycle:\n             - status: active | duplicate | upgraded | downgraded | contested | resolved_false_positive\n             - Record first_seen, upgraded_in, previous_severity for severity changes\n             - Record dimensions array reflecting all dimensions that emitted this finding\n          5. Resolve contradictions:\n             - Findings marked contested across iterations → referee pass\n             - Determine final severity and status\n          6. Count only 'active' findings for totals\n        outputs:\n          - finding_registry: \"Deduplicated list of all findings with metadata\"\n          - active_p0: \"Count of active P0 findings\"\n          - active_p1: \"Count of active P1 findings\"\n          - active_p2: \"Count of active P2 findings\"\n\n      step_adversarial_selfcheck:\n        action: \"Final adversarial self-check on all P0 and P1 findings\"\n        algorithm: |\n          For each active P0/P1 finding:\n            1. Hunter: Re-verify finding against source code (re-read file:line)\n            2. Skeptic: Challenge severity — is this really P0/P1? Could it be P2?\n            3. Referee: Final call — confirm, downgrade, or mark false_positive\n          Update finding_registry with adjudicated results.\n\n      step_emit_resource_map:\n        action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged review deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} {reducer_artifact_arg} --create-missing-anchors --emit-resource-map\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n        write:\n          - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n        guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n\n      step_resource_map_coverage_gate:\n        action: \"If resource_map_present, compute the Resource Map Coverage Gate synthesis inputs; otherwise preserve the skip note\"\n        note: \"Cross-check target_files from {spec_folder}/applied/T-*.md against {spec_folder}/resource-map.md. Report touched entries, untouched entries split into expected-by-scope vs gap, and implementation paths absent from the map. Findings raised here use category resource-map-coverage with severity calibrated to the gate outcome.\"\n\n      step_compile_review_report:\n        action: \"Compile review/review-report.md with 9 core sections, a conditional Resource Map Coverage Gate section, and an embedded Planning Packet\"\n        instructions: |\n          Create review/review-report.md with the following sections:\n\n          1. **Executive Summary**\n             - Overall verdict: PASS | CONDITIONAL | FAIL\n             - hasAdvisories: true when PASS carries active P2 items\n             - P0/P1/P2 counts (active only)\n             - Review scope summary\n\n          2. **Planning Trigger**\n             - State whether `/speckit:plan` is required\n             - Include a fenced `json` block labeled `Planning Packet`\n             - The packet MUST include: `triggered`, `verdict`, `hasAdvisories`, `activeFindings`, `remediationWorkstreams`, `specSeed`, `planSeed`, `findingClasses`, `affectedSurfacesSeed`, `fixCompletenessRequired`\n             - Build `activeFindings`, `findingClasses`, and `affectedSurfacesSeed` from reducer-owned state plus iteration JSONL `findingDetails`; if a field is missing, mark it `UNKNOWN` instead of inferring it from prose\n\n          3. **Active Finding Registry**\n             - Unified registry for active P0/P1/P2 findings\n             - For each: ID, severity, title, dimension, file:line, evidence, impact, fix recommendation, disposition, findingClass, scopeProof, affectedSurfaceHints\n\n          4. **Remediation Workstreams**\n             - Ordered action groups: P0 first, then P1, with P2 advisories separated\n\n          5. **Spec Seed**\n             - Concrete seed bullets for follow-on spec updates\n\n          6. **Plan Seed**\n             - Concrete starter tasks for `/speckit:plan`\n\n           7. **Traceability Status**\n              - Summarize required core protocols first, then applicable overlay protocols\n              - Include status, evidence, and any unresolved drift per protocol\n              - Include `AC_COVERAGE` status for lifecycle-active spec-folder targets: exempt, disabled, pass, or advisory-shortfall, with covered/total and floor when available\n\n          If `resource_map_present` is true, insert **## Resource Map Coverage Gate** after `Traceability Status` with exactly three bullets:\n             - `Entries touched`: count of resource-map paths that appear in applied reports\n             - `Entries not touched`: paths in resource-map not in implementation, labeled `expected-by-scope` or `gap`\n             - `Implementation paths absent from resource-map`: `target_files` in applied reports not on the map\n\n          8. **Deferred Items**\n             - Advisory-only or backlog-worthy follow-ups that do not block the current verdict\n\n          **Dimension Expansion Map**\n             - Insert `## Dimension Expansion Map` after Deferred Items and before Search Ledger.\n             - Render reducer-owned `divergence.saturatedDirections`, completed pivots, failed pivots, audited overrides, Council artifact references, selected review directions, and remaining frontier.\n             - This section records breadth only. It cannot alter the Executive Summary verdict, hasAdvisories, finding registry, or adversarial self-check results.\n\n          9. **Search Ledger**\n             - Always include this section before the appendix.\n             - Render reducer-owned `searchCoverage`, `candidateCoverage`, `searchDebt`, `ruledOutCandidates`, and `cleanSearchProof`.\n             - If all arrays are empty or absent, include: `*No search-depth state captured (legacy v1 record)*`.\n             - When `searchDebt` is non-empty, state `hasSearchDebt: true` and carry the dashboard verdict as CONDITIONAL unless active P0 findings make it FAIL.\n\n          10. **Audit Appendix**\n             - Convergence summary, coverage summary, ruled-out claims, sources reviewed\n             - Cross-reference appendix MUST be split into `Core Protocols` and `Overlay Protocols`\n\n          Preserve machine-owned markers so the reducer-owned registry, dashboard, and strategy anchors can be refreshed on re-run without mutating prior synthesis. (Note: `completed-continue` lineage branch is deferred — see `deep-review/references/protocol/loop-protocol.md §Lifecycle Branches`.)\n        output: \"{state_paths.review_output}\"\n\n      step_convergence_report:\n        action: \"Append convergence report to JSONL\"\n        command: |\n          node --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n          import { appendFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync, statSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n          const paths = {\n            stateLog: String.raw`{state_paths.state_log}`,\n            registry: String.raw`{state_paths.findings_registry}`,\n            review: String.raw`{state_paths.review_output}`,\n            dashboard: String.raw`{state_paths.dashboard}`,\n          };\n\n          function hasFile(filePath) {\n            try {\n              return existsSync(filePath) && statSync(filePath).isFile();\n            } catch {\n              return false;\n            }\n          }\n\n          function readJson(filePath) {\n            try {\n              return JSON.parse(readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8'));\n            } catch {\n              return null;\n            }\n          }\n\n          function readJsonl(filePath) {\n            if (!hasFile(filePath)) return [];\n            return readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8')\n              .split(/\\r?\\n/)\n              .map((line) => line.trim())\n              .filter(Boolean)\n              .flatMap((line) => {\n                try {\n                  return [JSON.parse(line)];\n                } catch {\n                  return [];\n                }\n              });\n          }\n\n          function countIterationFindings(record) {\n            if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration') return 0;\n            const numeric = Number(record.findingsCount);\n            if (Number.isFinite(numeric) && numeric > 0) return Math.floor(numeric);\n            if (Array.isArray(record.findingDetails)) return record.findingDetails.length;\n            return 0;\n          }\n\n          function normalizeFindingKey(value) {\n            return String(value || '').trim().toLowerCase().replace(/\\s+/g, ' ');\n          }\n\n          function findingKeys(candidate) {\n            if (typeof candidate === 'string') {\n              const key = normalizeFindingKey(candidate);\n              return key ? [key] : [];\n            }\n            if (!candidate || typeof candidate !== 'object' || Array.isArray(candidate)) return [];\n            return [...new Set([\n              candidate.id,\n              candidate.findingId,\n              candidate.title,\n              candidate.summary,\n              candidate.text,\n              candidate.finding,\n              candidate.description,\n            ].map(normalizeFindingKey).filter(Boolean))];\n          }\n\n          function collectIterationFindingGroups(record) {\n            if (!record || record.type !== 'iteration' || !Array.isArray(record.findingDetails)) return [];\n            return record.findingDetails\n              .map(findingKeys)\n              .filter((keys) => keys.length > 0);\n          }\n\n          function collectRegistryFindingKeys(registry) {\n            return [registry?.openFindings, registry?.resolvedFindings, registry?.repeatedFindings]\n              .filter(Array.isArray)\n              .flatMap((findings) => findings)\n              .flatMap(findingKeys);\n          }\n\n          function appendEvent(event) {\n            appendFileSync(paths.stateLog, `${JSON.stringify(event)}\\n`, 'utf8');\n          }\n\n          const registry = readJson(paths.registry);\n          const openCount = Array.isArray(registry?.openFindings) ? registry.openFindings.length : null;\n          const resolvedCount = Array.isArray(registry?.resolvedFindings) ? registry.resolvedFindings.length : 0;\n          const repeatedCount = Array.isArray(registry?.repeatedFindings) ? registry.repeatedFindings.length : 0;\n          const registryFindingCount = openCount === null ? null : openCount + resolvedCount + repeatedCount;\n          const stateRecords = readJsonl(paths.stateLog);\n          const iterationFindingCount = stateRecords.reduce((sum, record) => sum + countIterationFindings(record), 0);\n          const identifiableFindingGroups = stateRecords.flatMap(collectIterationFindingGroups);\n          const registryFindingKeys = new Set(collectRegistryFindingKeys(registry));\n          const missingStructuredFindingCount = identifiableFindingGroups.filter((keys) => !keys.some((key) => registryFindingKeys.has(key))).length;\n          const identifiableFindingCount = identifiableFindingGroups.length;\n          const missingArtifacts = [\n            ['registry', paths.registry],\n            ['review', paths.review],\n            ['dashboard', paths.dashboard],\n          ].filter(([, filePath]) => !hasFile(filePath)).map(([name, filePath]) => ({ name, path: filePath }));\n          const invariantFailures = [];\n          if (missingArtifacts.length > 0) invariantFailures.push('missing_synthesis_artifacts');\n          if (registryFindingCount === null) invariantFailures.push('registry_missing_openFindings');\n          if (iterationFindingCount > 0 && (registryFindingCount ?? 0) === 0) invariantFailures.push('state_findings_not_reflected_in_registry');\n          if (identifiableFindingCount > 0 && registryFindingCount !== null && registryFindingCount < identifiableFindingCount) invariantFailures.push('structured_state_findings_partially_reflected_in_registry');\n          if (missingStructuredFindingCount > 0) invariantFailures.push('structured_state_findings_missing_from_registry');\n\n          if (invariantFailures.length > 0) {\n            appendEvent({\n              type: 'event',\n              event: 'synthesis_incomplete',\n              mode: 'review',\n              severity: 'warning',\n              totalIterations: Number('{iteration_count}'),\n              activeP0: Number('{active_p0}'),\n              activeP1: Number('{active_p1}'),\n              activeP2: Number('{active_p2}'),\n              dimensionCoverage: Number('{dimension_coverage}'),\n              verdict: '{verdict}',\n              releaseReadinessState: '{release_readiness_state}',\n              stopReason: '{reason}',\n              reason: 'synthesis_artifact_invariant_failed',\n              invariantFailures,\n              missingArtifacts,\n              registryFindingCount,\n              iterationFindingCount,\n              identifiableFindingCount,\n              missingStructuredFindingCount,\n              timestamp: '{ISO_8601_NOW}',\n            });\n          } else {\n            appendEvent({\n              type: 'event',\n              event: 'synthesis_complete',\n              mode: 'review',\n              totalIterations: Number('{iteration_count}'),\n              activeP0: Number('{active_p0}'),\n              activeP1: Number('{active_p1}'),\n              activeP2: Number('{active_p2}'),\n              dimensionCoverage: Number('{dimension_coverage}'),\n              verdict: '{verdict}',\n              releaseReadinessState: '{release_readiness_state}',\n              stopReason: '{reason}',\n              timestamp: '{ISO_8601_NOW}',\n            });\n          }\n          EOF\n        note: \"Emit as numeric ratio (e.g., 0.75), not quoted string. Compute: dimensions_covered / total_dimensions.\"\n\n      step_update_config_status:\n        action: \"Mark config as complete\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        set_field: { status: \"complete\" }\n\n      step_leave_artifacts_unstaged:\n        action: \"Leave all synthesized artifacts unstaged for explicit operator review\"\n        note: \"Synthesis must not mutate the shared Git index. The operator retains staging and commit authority after reviewing the complete artifact directory.\"\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 4: SAVE\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_save:\n    purpose: Preserve review context to memory system\n    steps:\n\n      step_compose_save_payload:\n        action: \"Compose the structured JSON payload consumed by generate-context.js\"\n        output: \"/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json\"\n        requirements:\n          - \"Write this file before invoking generate-context.js; the loader fails closed if the explicit JSON file is absent.\"\n          - \"Include `specFolder`, a concise `sessionSummary`, curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` from the completed review loop.\"\n          - \"Use a session-scoped temp filename; do not use the retired shared `/tmp/save-context-data.json` path.\"\n        example_payload: |\n          {\n            \"specFolder\": \"{spec_folder}\",\n            \"sessionSummary\": \"Deep review completed; see review/review-report.md for verdict, findings, and workstreams.\",\n            \"observations\": [\"Summarize the active findings, verdict, and remediation guidance.\"],\n            \"recent_context\": [\"Point to the generated review artifacts and next action.\"],\n            \"exchanges\": [],\n            \"toolCalls\": []\n          }\n\n      step_generate_context:\n        action: \"Route continuity content into the correct canonical spec document via generate-context.js\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json {spec_folder}\"\n        critical_rule: \"NEVER manually author files under retired memory/ paths (the runtime rejects them); use generate-context.js so the save routes into decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md\"\n\n      step_index_memory:\n        action: \"Index the routed canonical spec document with memory_save when immediate MCP visibility is required\"\n        mcp_tool: memory_save\n        invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"[routed-canonical-spec-doc-path]\" })'\n        note: \"Use the actual canonical spec-doc path returned by generate-context.js (decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md); memory_index_scan remains the bulk fallback\"\n\n      step_verify_save:\n        action: \"Verify canonical save routed content into the correct spec document\"\n        check: \"Does {spec_folder}/implementation-summary.md, {spec_folder}/decision-record.md, or {spec_folder}/handover.md carry the new continuity update?\"\n        on_fail: \"Log warning but do not block completion\"\n\n      step_release_lock:\n        action: \"Release the single-writer lock after save, skip-save, or cancellation cleanup has resolved\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"lock_released\",\"path\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"releasePhase\":\"save\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # COMPLETION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  completion:\n    message: |\n      Deep review complete.\n      Iterations: {iteration_count} | Stop reason: {reason}\n      Findings: P0={active_p0} P1={active_p1} P2={active_p2}\n      Verdict: {verdict} | hasAdvisories={has_advisories}\n\n      Artifacts:\n        - review/review-report.md (compiled from {iteration_count} iterations)\n        - {iteration_count} iteration files in review/iterations/\n        - State files in review/: deep-review-config.json, deep-review-state.jsonl, deep-review-findings-registry.json, deep-review-strategy.md, deep-review-dashboard.md\n        - Memory context saved\n\n      STATUS=OK PATH={spec_folder}\n    next_steps:\n      - \"/speckit:plan [remediation] (if FAIL or CONDITIONAL verdict)\"\n      - \"/create:changelog (if PASS, including PASS with hasAdvisories=true)\"\n      - \"/deep:review [target] (for another review)\"\n      - \"/memory:save {spec_folder} (refresh canonical continuity before the next session)\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# ERROR RECOVERY\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nerror_recovery:\n  agent_dispatch_timeout: \"Retry once with reduced scope (fewer files per iteration). If second timeout, mark as 'timeout' and continue.\"\n  state_file_missing: \"If JSONL missing during loop, reconstruct from iteration files. If strategy missing, create minimal version.\"\n  consecutive_failures: \"After 3 consecutive errors, halt loop and enter synthesis with partial findings.\"\n  memory_save_failure: \"Preserve the review packet in review/ as backup. Log warning.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# RULES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrules:\n  ALWAYS:\n    - follow_workflow_phases_in_order\n    - dispatch_deep_review_agent_per_iteration\n    - check_convergence_before_each_iteration\n    - write_all_state_to_files\n    - save_memory_context_after_synthesis\n    - respect_max_iterations_cap\n    - treat_review_target_as_read_only\n    - deduplicate_findings_before_synthesis\n    - run_adversarial_selfcheck_on_p0_p1\n  NEVER:\n    - skip_convergence_check\n    - dispatch_non_leaf_agents\n    - hold_iteration_findings_in_memory_only\n    - modify_config_after_initialization\n    - overwrite_jsonl_state_log\n    - proceed_without_state_file_verification\n    - modify_files_under_review\n    - report_p0_without_file_line_evidence\n","lineStart":1640,"lineEnd":2089,"totalLines":2123,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep-review-auto.yaml","time":{"start":1784650212482,"end":1784650212593}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_03f0e82d94f6d585016a5f99e44d3c819187b6fbeb6d96ccc4"}},"id":"prt_f8571247e001G2uJgoTMdIV7tT","sessionID":"ses_07a91b76bffeQVZz6UB7PapKuO","messageID":"msg_f8570c374001ieeOYdHuun9tY9"}}
