| Summary |\n32: |-----------|---------|-----------|---------|\n33: | Correctness | PASS | 001 | Sampled all three shipped packets; command, path-relocation, and persistent-DB invariants were clean under direct reads and 101 passing tests. |\n34: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n35: \n36: ## Running Findings\n37: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n38: - P0: 0 active\n39: - P1: 0 active\n40: - P2: 0 active\n41: - Delta: iteration 001 added no active findings\n42: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n43: \n44: ## What Worked\n45: \n46: - Initialization validated the manifest as 118 unique existing files and confirmed the pinned worktree HEAD.\n47: - Iteration 001: direct producer/consumer reads plus the command (12/12), engine (20/20), and database (69/69) suites sampled all three packets productively.\n48: \n49: ## What Failed\n50: \n51: - Spec Kit Memory returned no canonical packet results; packet-local files are the continuity authority.\n52: - Iteration 001: Code Graph was unavailable by dispatch contract; structural-impact analysis remains unavailable. `git diff --check` also exposed a blank-line-at-EOF warning for maintainability follow-up.\n53: \n54: ## Exhausted Approaches\n55: \n56: - None.\n57: \n58: ## 10A. SATURATED / SWEPT DIMENSIONS AND EXPANSION FRONTIER\n59: - Completed pivots: 0\n60: - Failed pivots: 0\n61: - Audited overrides: 0\n62: - Swept: none yet\n63: - Pivot lineage: none yet\n64: - Remaining frontier: none recorded\n65: \n66: ## Ruled Out Directions\n67: \n68: - Bundle-content review is out of scope; byte parity is the only permitted bundle-data question.\n69: - Persistent cutover is intentionally deferred and is not a defect.\n70: \n71: ## Next Focus\n72: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n73: - Dimension: correctness\n74: - Dimension: security\n75: - Focus area: persistent publication pointers and flat-artifact hydration trust boundaries\n76: - Reason: the sampled producer/consumer seam crosses mutable state, path containment, generation identity, and authoritative flat-file reads.\n77: - Rotation status: correctness inventory complete; rotating to the first unchecked dimension.\n78: - Blocked/productive carry-forward: Code Graph unavailable; direct reads and executable adversarial tests productive.\n79: - Required evidence: pointer parsing/open behavior, symlink containment, digest/generation binding, cutover/rollback input validation, and counterevidence tests.\n80: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n81: \n82: ## Known Context\n83: \n84: ### Bounded Context Snapshot\n85: \n86: - Target pointers: `spec.md`, `goal-file-manifest.txt`, five interface command bodies, styles path seam and moved engine/database modules, database operator/schema/retrieval code, their tests, and completion metadata for packets 012/008 and 015/001/005/006.\n87: - Behavior claims: exactly one shared include per interface body, no command-owned taste, moved-module behavioral parity, a single path authority, legacy default without lazy build, absent-generation fail-closed behavior, honest test and completion claims.\n88: - Reuse and conventions: `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md` severity and evidence doctrine; target packet requirements and acceptance scenarios.\n89: - Risks and gaps: build dispatches had unrestricted workspace permission; Code Graph readiness is absent; memory retrieval returned no canonical packet result; use direct reads, exact search, pinned Git comparisons, and executable tests.\n90: - Resource map: target `resource-map.md` is absent, so the input coverage gate is skipped. Synthesis may still emit a lineage-local review resource map.\n91: \n92: ## Cross-Reference Status\n93: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n94: \n95: | Protocol | Level | Status | Iteration | Notes |\n96: |----------|-------|--------|-----------|-------|\n97: | `spec_code` | core | partial | 001 | Sampled command, path-seam, and database-default claims; full requirement replay remains. |\n98: | `checklist_evidence` | core | pending | - | 