{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784651271126,"sessionID":"ses_07a91b76bffeQVZz6UB7PapKuO","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_CthUT36avoWrEPt8CXLE76GH","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"node \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/verify-iteration.cjs\" --loop-type review --artifact-dir \".opencode/specs/sk-design/017-remediation-program-review/review/lineages/gpt-56-sol-high\" --iteration 2 --json","workdir":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review","timeout":120000},"output":"{\"ok\":true,\"reason\":null,\"detail\":\"iteration 2 complete: narrative + route-proof + delta\"}\n","metadata":{"output":"{\"ok\":true,\"reason\":null,\"detail\":\"iteration 2 complete: narrative + route-proof + delta\"}\n","exit":0,"truncated":false},"title":"node \".opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/scripts/verify-iteration.cjs\" --loop-type review --artifact-dir \".opencode/specs/sk-design/017-remediation-program-review/review/lineages/gpt-56-sol-high\" --iteration 2 --json","time":{"start":1784651271123,"end":1784651271125}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_007da1cb574446ec016a5f9e06f4a88197831cdf6792caf717"}},"id":"prt_f85814b820019QnAhQYgKqhgQ5","sessionID":"ses_07a91b76bffeQVZz6UB7PapKuO","messageID":"msg_f85811ceb001eGWSeFzbGCdZpa"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784651271174,"sessionID":"ses_07a91b76bffeQVZz6UB7PapKuO","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_RnXMi2B1LmObJG3Wh9ZbFNh8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/specs/sk-design/017-remediation-program-review/review/lineages/gpt-56-sol-high/iterations/iteration-002.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/specs/sk-design/017-remediation-program-review/review/lineages/gpt-56-sol-high/iterations/iteration-002.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Review Iteration 002 — Security\n2: \n3: ## Dispatcher\n4: \n5: - Route: `Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review`\n6: - Session: `fanout-gpt-56-sol-high-1784650021792-031fvi`\n7: - Generation / lineage: `1` / `new`\n8: - Budget profile: `scan`\n9: - Scope: validated 118-file `goal-file-manifest.txt` at pinned HEAD `7b9d3b6b71`\n10: - Structural caveat: Code Graph was unavailable by dispatch contract; direct reads, exact searches, and focused tests were used.\n11: \n12: ## Files Reviewed\n13: \n14: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/generation-manifest.mjs`\n15: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/schema.mjs`\n16: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/indexer.mjs`\n17: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/operator.mjs`\n18: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/retrieval.mjs`\n19: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/engine/persistent-adapter.mjs`\n20: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/engine/hydrate.mjs`\n21: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/tests/database/manifest.test.mjs`\n22: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/tests/database/schema.test.mjs`\n23: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/tests/database/operator.test.mjs`\n24: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/tests/database/retrieval.test.mjs`\n25: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/tests/database/adapter.test.mjs`\n26: - `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/tests/engine/hydrate-guard.test.mjs`\n27: \n28: ## Findings - New\n29: \n30: ### P0 Findings\n31: \n32: None.\n33: \n34: ### P1 Findings\n35: \n36: 1. **Published SQLite opens do not enforce the manifest's content digest** -- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/schema.mjs:343` -- The publication manifest records and can verify each artifact's SHA-256, but the production open path resolves the pointer and checks only the mutable database's internal `generation_hash`. A same-generation database modified after publication can therefore supply altered query/provenance rows while still passing the pointer binding. The local-filesystem write prerequisite keeps this below P0, but it defeats the content-addressed publication integrity boundary. [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/generation-manifest.mjs:212-234`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/schema.mjs:343-355`]\n37:    - Finding class: cross-consumer\n38:    - Scope proof: Exact search found `resolveManifestArtifacts(..., { verifyDigests: true })` exercised by manifest tests, while every production published-database consumer funnels through `openPublishedStyleDatabase`, which never invokes that verifier. The affected open path is shared by query, hydration, status, and vector repair.\n39:    - Affected surface hints: `[\"published database open\", \"persistent query\", \"persistent hydration\", \"operator status/repair\"]`\n40:    - Recommendation: Bind production opens to the manifest artifact digest before trusting database rows, or provide an equivalently enforced immutable/read-only publication guarantee and test same-generation post-publication tampering through `openPublishedStyleDatabase`.\n41:    - Content hash: `sha256:b9ba3149517c5b8648902997375a7f0fd36629b93eba9523849ee381136587b8`\n42: \n43: ```json\n44: {\"type\":\"security-integrity\",\"claim\":\"A published SQLite artifact can be altered without changing its internal generation_hash and production opens will not compare it with the manifest sha256.\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/generation-manifest.mjs:212-234\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/schema.mjs:343-355\"],\"counterevidenceSought\":\"Reviewed pointer containment, generation-mismatch, artifact-tamper, operator, retrieval, adapter, and hydration tests; 35/35 passed. The tamper test proves the optional digest verifier works, but no production open calls it.\",\"alternativeExplanation\":\"The artifact may be assumed immutable because it is generation-named and local; however, the reviewed code does not enforce read-only immutability and explicitly stores the digest as publication identity.\",\"finalSeverity\":\"P1\",\"confidence\":0.91,\"downgradeTrigger\":\"Downgrade if an in-scope enforced filesystem guarantee proves published artifacts cannot change, or if the production open path is shown to verify the manifest digest before exposing database rows.\"}\n45: ```\n46: \n47: ### P2 Findings\n48: \n49: None.\n50: \n51: ## Traceability Checks\n52: \n53: - `spec_code`: **partial**. Publication is atomic, pointer/artifact realpaths are contained, and open-time generation identity is checked, but the manifest's recorded SQLite digest is not enforced by the production open path [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/generation-manifest.mjs:156-185`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/schema.mjs:343-355`].\n54: - `checklist_evidence`: **pending**. Dedicated traceability replay remains assigned to the next dimension.\n55: \n56: ## Integration Evidence\n57: \n58: - Exact shared surface reviewed: `openPublishedStyleDatabase` in `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/schema.mjs:343-356`; its consumers include persistent retrieval/hydration and operator status/repair.\n59: - Focused verification: 35/35 tests passed across manifest, schema, operator, retrieval, adapter, and hydration-guard suites, including pointer symlink escape, generation mismatch, optional digest verification, flat-artifact digest checks, and missing-generation refusal.\n60: \n61: ## Edge Cases\n62: \n63: - The digest gap requires write access to the published SQLite artifact or a compromised local publisher; no remote or privilege-escalation path was established, so the supported severity is P1 rather than P0.\n64: - Generation-named files are described as immutable, but no in-scope enforcement of immutability was found; that assumption cannot be treated as a pass.\n65: - Code Graph structural-impact analysis was unavailable; exact import/call searches and direct consumer reads supplied the bounded fallback.\n66: \n67: ## Confirmed-Clean Surfaces\n68: \n69: - Pointer payload parsing rejects invalid shapes and confines SQLite resolution to the generation directory [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/generation-manifest.mjs:127-185`].\n70: - Rollback/cutover requires a same-directory regular file, resolves symlinks for containment, runs SQLite integrity validation, and requires an internal generation identity [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/indexer.mjs:1138-1179`].\n71: - Legacy and persistent hydration enforce generation equality, realpath containment, per-flat-artifact SHA-256, rights restrictions, and byte caps [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/engine/persistent-adapter.mjs:175-280`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/engine/hydrate.mjs:225-370`].\n72: \n73: ## Ruled Out\n74: \n75: - Pointer path traversal and escaping symlinks: rejected by basename validation plus realpath containment; adversarial schema/hydration tests passed.\n76: - Missing-generation fallback: persistent retrieval fails closed instead of silently serving an unbound generation [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/tests/database/retrieval.test.mjs:52-60`].\n77: - Cutover to an outside-directory generation: rejected by resolved-directory and realpath containment checks [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/indexer.mjs:1141-1158`].\n78: \n79: ## Next Focus\n80: \n81: - Dimension: traceability\n82: - Focus area: full requirement and checklist-evidence replay for publication integrity, deferred cutover, and completion claims\n83: - Reason: security found a production digest-binding gap while core traceability protocols remain partial/pending\n84: - Rotation status: correctness and security completed; rotate to the next unchecked dimension\n85: - Blocked/productive carry-forward: Code Graph unavailable; exact searches, direct reads, and focused executable tests remain productive\n86: - Required evidence: packet requirements, checklist rows, implementation-summary claims, production digest/open behavior, and named test evidence\n87: \n88: Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\n\n(End of file - total 88 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Review Iteration 002 — Security\n\n## Dispatcher\n\n- Route: `Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review`\n- Session: `fanout-gpt-56-sol-high-1784650021792-031fvi`\n- Generation / lineage: `1` / `new`\n- Budget profile: `scan`\n- Scope: validated 118-file `goal-file-manifest.txt` at pinned HEAD `7b9d3b6b71`\n- Structural caveat: Code Graph was unavailable by dispatch contract; direct reads, exact searches, and focused tests were used.\n\n## Files Reviewed\n\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/generation-manifest.mjs`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/schema.mjs`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/indexer.mjs`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/operator.mjs`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/retrieval.mjs`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/engine/persistent-adapter.mjs`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/engine/hydrate.mjs`","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/specs/sk-design/017-remediation-program-review/review/lineages/gpt-56-sol-high/iterations/iteration-002.md","text":"# Deep Review Iteration 002 — Security\n\n## Dispatcher\n\n- Route: `Resolved route: mode=review target_agent=deep-review`\n- Session: `fanout-gpt-56-sol-high-1784650021792-031fvi`\n- Generation / lineage: `1` / `new`\n- Budget profile: `scan`\n- Scope: validated 118-file `goal-file-manifest.txt` at pinned HEAD `7b9d3b6b71`\n- Structural caveat: Code Graph was unavailable by dispatch contract; direct reads, exact searches, and focused tests were used.\n\n## Files Reviewed\n\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/generation-manifest.mjs`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/schema.mjs`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/indexer.mjs`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/operator.mjs`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/retrieval.mjs`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/engine/persistent-adapter.mjs`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/engine/hydrate.mjs`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/tests/database/manifest.test.mjs`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/tests/database/schema.test.mjs`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/tests/database/operator.test.mjs`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/tests/database/retrieval.test.mjs`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/tests/database/adapter.test.mjs`\n- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/tests/engine/hydrate-guard.test.mjs`\n\n## Findings - New\n\n### P0 Findings\n\nNone.\n\n### P1 Findings\n\n1. **Published SQLite opens do not enforce the manifest's content digest** -- `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/schema.mjs:343` -- The publication manifest records and can verify each artifact's SHA-256, but the production open path resolves the pointer and checks only the mutable database's internal `generation_hash`. A same-generation database modified after publication can therefore supply altered query/provenance rows while still passing the pointer binding. The local-filesystem write prerequisite keeps this below P0, but it defeats the content-addressed publication integrity boundary. [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/generation-manifest.mjs:212-234`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/schema.mjs:343-355`]\n   - Finding class: cross-consumer\n   - Scope proof: Exact search found `resolveManifestArtifacts(..., { verifyDigests: true })` exercised by manifest tests, while every production published-database consumer funnels through `openPublishedStyleDatabase`, which never invokes that verifier. The affected open path is shared by query, hydration, status, and vector repair.\n   - Affected surface hints: `[\"published database open\", \"persistent query\", \"persistent hydration\", \"operator status/repair\"]`\n   - Recommendation: Bind production opens to the manifest artifact digest before trusting database rows, or provide an equivalently enforced immutable/read-only publication guarantee and test same-generation post-publication tampering through `openPublishedStyleDatabase`.\n   - Content hash: `sha256:b9ba3149517c5b8648902997375a7f0fd36629b93eba9523849ee381136587b8`\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"security-integrity\",\"claim\":\"A published SQLite artifact can be altered without changing its internal generation_hash and production opens will not compare it with the manifest sha256.\",\"evidenceRefs\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/generation-manifest.mjs:212-234\",\".opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/schema.mjs:343-355\"],\"counterevidenceSought\":\"Reviewed pointer containment, generation-mismatch, artifact-tamper, operator, retrieval, adapter, and hydration tests; 35/35 passed. The tamper test proves the optional digest verifier works, but no production open calls it.\",\"alternativeExplanation\":\"The artifact may be assumed immutable because it is generation-named and local; however, the reviewed code does not enforce read-only immutability and explicitly stores the digest as publication identity.\",\"finalSeverity\":\"P1\",\"confidence\":0.91,\"downgradeTrigger\":\"Downgrade if an in-scope enforced filesystem guarantee proves published artifacts cannot change, or if the production open path is shown to verify the manifest digest before exposing database rows.\"}\n```\n\n### P2 Findings\n\nNone.\n\n## Traceability Checks\n\n- `spec_code`: **partial**. Publication is atomic, pointer/artifact realpaths are contained, and open-time generation identity is checked, but the manifest's recorded SQLite digest is not enforced by the production open path [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/generation-manifest.mjs:156-185`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/schema.mjs:343-355`].\n- `checklist_evidence`: **pending**. Dedicated traceability replay remains assigned to the next dimension.\n\n## Integration Evidence\n\n- Exact shared surface reviewed: `openPublishedStyleDatabase` in `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/schema.mjs:343-356`; its consumers include persistent retrieval/hydration and operator status/repair.\n- Focused verification: 35/35 tests passed across manifest, schema, operator, retrieval, adapter, and hydration-guard suites, including pointer symlink escape, generation mismatch, optional digest verification, flat-artifact digest checks, and missing-generation refusal.\n\n## Edge Cases\n\n- The digest gap requires write access to the published SQLite artifact or a compromised local publisher; no remote or privilege-escalation path was established, so the supported severity is P1 rather than P0.\n- Generation-named files are described as immutable, but no in-scope enforcement of immutability was found; that assumption cannot be treated as a pass.\n- Code Graph structural-impact analysis was unavailable; exact import/call searches and direct consumer reads supplied the bounded fallback.\n\n## Confirmed-Clean Surfaces\n\n- Pointer payload parsing rejects invalid shapes and confines SQLite resolution to the generation directory [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/generation-manifest.mjs:127-185`].\n- Rollback/cutover requires a same-directory regular file, resolves symlinks for containment, runs SQLite integrity validation, and requires an internal generation identity [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/indexer.mjs:1138-1179`].\n- Legacy and persistent hydration enforce generation equality, realpath containment, per-flat-artifact SHA-256, rights restrictions, and byte caps [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/engine/persistent-adapter.mjs:175-280`] [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/engine/hydrate.mjs:225-370`].\n\n## Ruled Out\n\n- Pointer path traversal and escaping symlinks: rejected by basename validation plus realpath containment; adversarial schema/hydration tests passed.\n- Missing-generation fallback: persistent retrieval fails closed instead of silently serving an unbound generation [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/tests/database/retrieval.test.mjs:52-60`].\n- Cutover to an outside-directory generation: rejected by resolved-directory and realpath containment checks [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/database/indexer.mjs:1141-1158`].\n\n## Next Focus\n\n- Dimension: traceability\n- Focus area: full requirement and checklist-evidence replay for publication integrity, deferred cutover, and completion claims\n- Reason: security found a production digest-binding gap while core traceability protocols remain partial/pending\n- Rotation status: correctness and security completed; rotate to the next unchecked dimension\n- Blocked/productive carry-forward: Code Graph unavailable; exact searches, direct reads, and focused executable tests remain productive\n- Required evidence: packet requirements, checklist rows, implementation-summary claims, production digest/open behavior, and named test evidence\n\nReview verdict: CONDITIONAL","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":88,"totalLines":88,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/017-remediation-program-review/review/lineages/gpt-56-sol-high/iterations/iteration-002.md","time":{"start":1784651271154,"end":1784651271171}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_007da1cb574446ec016a5f9e06f4bc8197a15618208fd04270"}},"id":"prt_f85814be4001ejshKZkuiK7wBG","sessionID":"ses_07a91b76bffeQVZz6UB7PapKuO","messageID":"msg_f85811ceb001eGWSeFzbGCdZpa"}}
