HOR:dimension-expansion -->\n42: <!-- ANCHOR:findings-summary -->\n43: ## 3. FINDINGS SUMMARY\n44: \n45: | Severity | Count |\n46: |----------|------:|\n47: | P0 (Blockers) | 0 |\n48: | P1 (Required) | 10 |\n49: | P2 (Suggestions) | 0 |\n50: | Resolved | 1 |\n51: \n52: <!-- /ANCHOR:findings-summary -->\n53: <!-- ANCHOR:progress -->\n54: ## 4. PROGRESS\n55: \n56: | # | Focus | Dimensions | Ratio | P0/P1/P2 | Status |\n57: |---|-------|------------|-------|----------|--------|\n58: | 1 | correctness inventory and behavioral invariants across the interface-command rewrite, styles-library restructure, and persistent-database activation | correctness | 0.00 | 0/0/0 | complete |\n59: | 2 | persistent publication pointers and flat-artifact hydration trust boundaries | security | 1.00 | 0/1/0 | complete |\n60: | 3 | full spec_code and checklist_evidence replay across packet 012/008, packets 015/001/005/006, the 015 parent, and the playbook capability overlay; refine P1-001 with complete adjudication | traceability | 0.83 | 0/3/0 | complete |\n61: | 4 | maintainability closure for stale paths, generated metadata integrity, command authority consistency, and file-format follow-up | maintainability | 0.40 | 0/2/0 | complete |\n62: | 5 | packet-level consumer closure across runtime entry points and regeneration boundaries | correctness | 0.00 | 0/0/0 | complete |\n63: | 6 | error propagation and trust-boundary closure across the facade, persistent adapter, database retrieval/operator code, md-generator child-process handling, and four corpus fallback classifiers | security | 0.17 | 0/1/0 | complete |\n64: | 7 | test-to-claim closure for all six active P1 findings, with stable-ID numeric-confidence refinement of P1-006 | traceability | 0.08 | 0/1/0 | complete |\n65: | 8 | operator/API parity for options, defaults, exits, result fields, repair semantics, and absent-generation behavior | maintainability | 0.25 | 0/2/0 | complete |\n66: | 9 | correctness third-pass adversarial challenge of shadow-parity and p95 performance claims with stable-ID hash repair for P1-007/P1-008 | correctness | 0.30 | 0/4/0 | complete |\n67: | 10 | correctness final adversarial stabilization/replay of all ten substantive active P1 claims and append-only reducer identity repair | correctness | 0.20 | 0/2/0 | complete |\n68: \n69: <!-- /ANCHOR:progress -->\n70: <!-- ANCHOR:dimension-coverage -->\n71: ## 5. DIMENSION COVERAGE\n72: \n73: | Dimension | Status | Open findings |\n74: |-----------|--------|--------------:|\n75: | correctness | covered | 10 |\n76: | security | covered | 0 |\n77: | traceability | covered | 0 |\n78: | maintainability | covered | 0 |\n79: \n80: <!-- /ANCHOR:dimension-coverage -->\n81: <!-- ANCHOR:blocked-stops -->\n82: ## 6. BLOCKED STOPS\n83: No blocked-stop events recorded.\n84: \n85: <!-- /ANCHOR:blocked-stops -->\n86: <!-- ANCHOR:graph-convergence -->\n87: ## 7. GRAPH CONVERGENCE\n88: - graphConvergenceScore: 0.00\n89: - graphDecision: none\n90: - graphBlockers: none\n91: \n92: <!-- /ANCHOR:graph-convergence -->\n93: <!-- ANCHOR:trend -->\n94: ## 8. TREND\n95: - Last 3 ratios: 0.25 -> 0.30 -> 0.20\n96: - convergenceScore: 0.80\n97: - openFindings: 10\n98: - persistentSameSeverity: 2\n99: - severityChanged: 0\n100: - repeatedFindings (deprecated combined bucket): 2\n101: \n102: <!-- /ANCHOR:trend -->\n103: <!-- ANCHOR:corruption-warnings -->\n104: ## 9. CORRUPTION WARNINGS\n105: No corrupt JSONL lines detected.\n106: \n107: <!-- /ANCHOR:corruption-warnings -->\n108: <!-- ANCHOR:search-debt -->\n109: ## 10. SEARCH DEBT\n110: - No search-depth state captured (legacy v1 record).\n111: - graphCoverageMode: none\n112: \n113: <!-- /ANCHOR:search-debt -->\n114: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n115: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n116: - Dimension: synthesis - Focus area: synthesize the ten active P1 claims, including the `P1-007`→`P1-011` and `P1-008`→`P1-012` identity-repair transitions - Reason: iteration 10 reached the configured maximum with every substantive claim still supported - Rotation status: all review dimensions and final stabilization are complete; no further LEAF iteration is authorized - Blocked/productive carry-forward: Code Graph remains unavailable; lineage artifacts, direct anchors, and focused-test receipts remain productive for synthesis - Required evidence: iteration 010 narrative/delta/state agreement, ten active P1 identities, two identity-only resolutions, and `maxIterationsReached` Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\n117: \n118: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n119: <!-- ANCHOR:active-risks -->\n120: ## 12. ACTIVE RISKS\n121: - 10 active P1 finding(s) — required before release; not a P0 but still blocks PASS.\n122: \n123: <!-- /ANCHOR:active-risks -->\n\n(End of file - total 123 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Dashboard\ndescription: Auto-generated reducer view over the review packet.\n---\n\n# Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n\nAuto-generated from JSONL state log, iteration files, findings registry, and strategy state. Never manually edited.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:overview -->\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nReducer-generated observability surface for the active review packet.\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:overview -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:status -->\n## 2. STATUS\n- Review Target: .opencode/specs/sk-design/017-remediation-program-review (spec-folder)\n- Started: 2026-07-21T16:11:30.000Z\n- Status: INITIALIZED","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/specs/sk-design/017-remediation-program-review/review/lineages/gpt-56-sol-high/deep-review-dashboard.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Review Dashboard\ndescription: Auto-generated reducer view over the review packet.\n---\n\n# Deep Review Dashboard - Session Overview\n\nAuto-generated from JSONL state log, iteration files, findings registry, and strategy state. Never manually edited.\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:overview -->\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nReducer-generated observability surface for the active review packet.\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:overview -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:status -->\n## 2. STATUS\n- Review Target: .opencode/specs/sk-design/017-remediation-program-review (spec-folder)\n- Started: 2026-07-21T16:11:30.000Z\n- Status: INITIALIZED\n- Iteration: 10 of 10\n- Provisional Verdict: CONDITIONAL\n- hasSearchDebt: false\n- hasAdvisories: false\n- Session ID: fanout-gpt-56-sol-high-1784650021792-031fvi\n- Parent Session: none\n- Lifecycle Mode: new\n- Generation: 1\n- continuedFromRun: none\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:status -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:dimension-expansion -->\n## 2A. DIMENSION EXPANSION\n- Completed pivots: 0\n- Failed pivots: 0\n- Audited overrides: 0\n- Swept: none yet\n- Pivot lineage: none yet\n- Remaining frontier: none recorded\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:dimension-expansion -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:findings-summary -->\n## 3. FINDINGS SUMMARY\n\n| Severity | Count |\n|----------|------:|\n| P0 (Blockers) | 0 |\n| P1 (Required) | 10 |\n| P2 (Suggestions) | 0 |\n| Resolved | 1 |\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:findings-summary -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:progress -->\n## 4. PROGRESS\n\n| # | Focus | Dimensions | Ratio | P0/P1/P2 | Status |\n|---|-------|------------|-------|----------|--------|\n| 1 | correctness inventory and behavioral invariants across the interface-command rewrite, styles-library restructure, and persistent-database activation | correctness | 0.00 | 0/0/0 | complete |\n| 2 | persistent publication pointers and flat-artifact hydration trust boundaries | security | 1.00 | 0/1/0 | complete |\n| 3 | full spec_code and checklist_evidence replay across packet 012/008, packets 015/001/005/006, the 015 parent, and the playbook capability overlay; refine P1-001 with complete adjudication | traceability | 0.83 | 0/3/0 | complete |\n| 4 | maintainability closure for stale paths, generated metadata integrity, command authority consistency, and file-format follow-up | maintainability | 0.40 | 0/2/0 | complete |\n| 5 | packet-level consumer closure across runtime entry points and regeneration boundaries | correctness | 0.00 | 0/0/0 | complete |\n| 6 | error propagation and trust-boundary closure across the facade, persistent adapter, database retrieval/operator code, md-generator child-process handling, and four corpus fallback classifiers | security | 0.17 | 0/1/0 | complete |\n| 7 | test-to-claim closure for all six active P1 findings, with stable-ID numeric-confidence refinement of P1-006 | traceability | 0.08 | 0/1/0 | complete |\n| 8 | operator/API parity for options, defaults, exits, result fields, repair semantics, and absent-generation behavior | maintainability | 0.25 | 0/2/0 | complete |\n| 9 | correctness third-pass adversarial challenge of shadow-parity and p95 performance claims with stable-ID hash repair for P1-007/P1-008 | correctness | 0.30 | 0/4/0 | complete |\n| 10 | correctness final adversarial stabilization/replay of all ten substantive active P1 claims and append-only reducer identity repair | correctness | 0.20 | 0/2/0 | complete |\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:progress -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:dimension-coverage -->\n## 5. DIMENSION COVERAGE\n\n| Dimension | Status | Open findings |\n|-----------|--------|--------------:|\n| correctness | covered | 10 |\n| security | covered | 0 |\n| traceability | covered | 0 |\n| maintainability | covered | 0 |\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:dimension-coverage -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:blocked-stops -->\n## 6. BLOCKED STOPS\nNo blocked-stop events recorded.\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:blocked-stops -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:graph-convergence -->\n## 7. GRAPH CONVERGENCE\n- graphConvergenceScore: 0.00\n- graphDecision: none\n- graphBlockers: none\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:graph-convergence -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:trend -->\n## 8. TREND\n- Last 3 ratios: 0.25 -> 0.30 -> 0.20\n- convergenceScore: 0.80\n- openFindings: 10\n- persistentSameSeverity: 2\n- severityChanged: 0\n- repeatedFindings (deprecated combined bucket): 2\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:trend -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:corruption-warnings -->\n## 9. CORRUPTION WARNINGS\nNo corrupt JSONL lines detected.\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:corruption-warnings -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:search-debt -->\n## 10. SEARCH DEBT\n- No search-depth state captured (legacy v1 record).\n- graphCoverageMode: none\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:search-debt -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n- Dimension: synthesis - Focus area: synthesize the ten active P1 claims, including the `P1-007`→`P1-011` and `P1-008`→`P1-012` identity-repair transitions - Reason: iteration 10 reached the configured maximum with every substantive claim still supported - Rotation status: all review dimensions and final stabilization are complete; no further LEAF iteration is authorized - Blocked/productive carry-forward: Code Graph remains unavailable; lineage artifacts, direct anchors, and focused-test receipts remain productive for synthesis - Required evidence: iteration 010 narrative/delta/state agreement, ten active P1 identities, two identity-only resolutions, and `maxIterationsReached` Review verdict: CONDITIONAL\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:active-risks -->\n## 12. ACTIVE RISKS\n- 10 active P1 finding(s) — required before release; not a P0 but still blocks PASS.\n\n<!-- /ANCHOR:active-risks -->","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":123,"totalLines":123,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/sk-design/017-remediation-program-review/review/lineages/gpt-56-sol-high/deep-review-dashboard.md","time":{"start":1784655581317,"end":1784655581323}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_01b60e6f54af92ec016a5faedd1918819192a12541606d187c"}},"id":"prt_f85c3107c001CUQCMjU3Qw7miP","sessionID":"ses_07a91b76bffeQVZz6UB7PapKuO","messageID":"msg_f85c2c786001GHqq42e0Bi5mar"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1784655581386,"sessionID":"ses_07a91b76bffeQVZz6UB7PapKuO","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_QyFwckCFTuSY49RJ3C9Dwfoe","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/specs/sk-design/017-remediation-program-review/review/lineages/gpt-56-sol-high/deep-review-strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.worktrees/0094-sk-design-017-remediation-review/.opencode/specs/sk-design/017-remediation-program-review/review/lineages/gpt-56-sol-high/deep-review-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Review Strategy: sk-design Remediation Program\n2: \n3: ## Topic\n4: \n5: Review the pinned 118-file implementation, test, command, and packet-document surface for the sk-design interface-command rewrite, styles-library restructure, and persistent-database activation.\n6: \n7: ## Review Dimensions\n8: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n9: - [x] Correctness — Iterations 001, 005, 009, and 010 CONDITIONAL (inventory/consumer closure, parity/performance challenge, and final ten-claim stabilization)\n10: - [x] Security — Iterations 002 and 006 CONDITIONAL (publication-integrity seam plus stale-generation fallback classification)\n11: - [x] Traceability — Iterations 003 and 007 CONDITIONAL (parent/playbook drift; active-finding assertion closure; P1-006 refinement)\n12: - [x] Maintainability — Iterations 004 and 008 CONDITIONAL (path/metadata drift plus operator input and clean-checkout status parity)\n13: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n14: \n15: ## Non-Goals\n16: \n17: - Do not inspect the contents of the 7,741 mechanically moved bundle data files; verify only the stated byte-parity boundary.\n18: - Do not review the concurrent system-deep-loop or 036 work.\n19: - Do not treat the intentionally legacy database default or deferred cutover as defects.\n20: - Do not modify reviewed files or implement remediation.\n21: \n22: ## Stop Conditions\n23: \n24: - Dispatch exactly 10 complete review iterations.\n25: - Treat convergence before iteration 10 as telemetry only and broaden the review angle.\n26: - Stop early only for an unrecoverable state-integrity or safety failure.\n27: \n28: ## Completed Dimensions\n29: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n30: \n31: | Dimension | Verdict | Iteration | Summary |\n32: |-----------|---------|-----------|---------|\n33: | Correctness | PASS | 001 | Sampled all three shipped packets; command, path-relocation, and persistent-DB invariants were clean under direct reads and 101 passing tests. |\n34: | Security | CONDITIONAL | 002 | Pointer containment, generation checks, operator inputs, and flat-artifact hydration guards were strong; production SQLite opens do not enforce the publication manifest digest. |\n35: | Traceability | CONDITIONAL | 003 | Child deferrals and test counts are mostly honest, but the manual playbook uses removed paths, the parent phase map is stale, and P1-001 remains active. |\n36: | Maintainability | CONDITIONAL | 004 | Central code paths and command authority are coherent, but the database README has dead operator commands and generated graph metadata retains stale states/paths. |\n37: | Correctness (second pass) | PASS | 005 | All four mode consumers use the moved facade, md-generator resolves the moved CLI/manifest, command metadata names current owners, and 60/60 focused consumer tests passed; generated-state consumer closure remains partial without widening the manifest. |\n38: | Security (second pass) | CONDITIONAL | 006 | Child-process and persistent hydration guards fail closed, but all four corpus consumers misclassify post-query generation drift as no-fit instead of requery-required. |\n39: | Traceability (second pass) | CONDITIONAL | 007 | All six active P1 findings were mapped to executable assertions or explicit missing/blocked coverage; P1-006 was refined with numeric confidence and unchanged stable hash. |\n40: | Maintainability (second pass) | CONDITIONAL | 008 | Valid operator/API DTOs are coherent, but malformed option values silently select defaults and status throws when the clean-checkout database directory is absent. |\n41: | Correctness (third pass) | CONDITIONAL | 009 | Persistent oracle replay is deterministic, but the 10/10 full-DTO and p95 1150→53 ms claims exceed the reproducible manifest evidence; P1-007/P1-008 hashes were repaired. |\n42: | Correctness (final stabilization) | CONDITIONAL | 010 | All ten substantive claims survived counterevidence replay; P1-007/P1-008 were identity-only resolved and superseded by distinct active P1-011/P1-012 records. |\n43: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n44: \n45: ## Running Findings\n46: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n47: - P0: 0 active\n48: - P1: 10 active\n49: - P2: 0 active\n50: - Resolved: 2 identity-only supersessions (`P1-007`, `P1-008`), not defect fixes\n51: - Delta: iteration 010 added `P1-011`/`P1-012` with distinct canonical hashes; the other eight active IDs remain unchanged and ten active P1 findings carry into synthesis\n52: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n53: \n54: ## What Worked\n55: \n56: - Initialization validated the manifest as 118 unique existing files and confirmed the pinned worktree HEAD.\n57: - Iteration 001: direct producer/consumer reads plus the command (12/12), engine (20/20), and database (69/69) suites sampled all three packets productively.\n58: - Iteration 002: exact producer/consumer searches, focused publication/hydration reads, and 35/35 security-relevant tests isolated the enforced guards from the missing production digest binding.\n59: - Iteration 003: full in-manifest packet/checklist replay plus pinned-HEAD command (19/19), engine (20/20), and database (69/69) suites verified reported counts and separated honest deferrals from stale authorities.\n60: - Iteration 004: manifest-scoped stale-path/metadata scanning, focused producer-consumer reads, clean `git diff --check`, and the 12/12 command-contract test separated active operational drift from intentional migration history.\n61: - Iteration 005: manifest-scoped consumer enumeration, direct path/facade/corpus/md-generator reads, and 60/60 focused mode-corpus tests closed the active moved-path consumer surface without duplicating existing findings.\n62: - Iteration 006: direct trust-boundary reads plus 76/76 focused adapter, retrieval, operator, and corpus tests separated fail-closed containment from a repeated stale-generation classification defect.\n63: - Iteration 007: manifest-restricted assertion inventory plus 75/75 focused manifest/schema/corpus tests mapped every active P1 to executable, missing, or scope-blocked coverage and repaired P1-006 adjudication confidence to numeric form.\n64: - Iteration 008: direct operator/API schema comparison, 13/13 focused tests, and read-only malformed/absence probes separated valid-command parity from two reproducible boundary defects.\n65: - Iteration 009: direct comparator/oracle/packet reads plus 11/11 focused tests separated deterministic persistent replay from unproven full-DTO shadow parity and p95 methodology; canonical stable-ID hashes now keep P1-007/P1-008 distinct.\n66: - Iteration 010: direct anchor replay, two read-only boundary probes, and 64/64 focused operator/adapter/corpus tests confirmed all ten claims while repairing append-only reducer identity through superseding IDs.\n67: \n68: ## What Failed\n69: \n70: - Spec Kit Memory returned no canonical packet results; packet-local files are the continuity authority.\n71: - Iteration 001: Code Graph was unavailable by dispatch contract; structural-impact analysis remains unavailable. `git diff --check` also exposed a blank-line-at-EOF warning for maintainability follow-up.\n72: - Iteration 002: Code Graph remained unavailable. Existing tamper coverage exercises the optional manifest verifier but not the production `openPublishedStyleDatabase` path.\n73: - Iteration 003: the 001 checklist is absent from the validated manifest, so its reported 14/15 evidence remains partial; the stale reducer-generated BLOCKED entries for pending traceability protocols conflict with the explicit iteration-003 replay assignment.\n74: - Iteration 004: Code Graph remained unavailable. One exact-search command accidentally covered the wider sk-design graph-metadata tree; all out-of-manifest hits were discarded and the scope violation is preserved in the iteration artifact/state.\n75: - Iteration 005: Code Graph remained unavailable, and the md-generator Vitest binary was unavailable because backend dependencies are absent; direct source/test reads verified its moved paths, but that TypeScript suite was not executed.\n76: - Iteration 006: Code Graph and md-generator Vitest remained unavailable; malformed-output/nonzero-child behavior and some adapter failure shapes therefore have direct-read but not executable evidence.\n77: - Iteration 007: Code Graph and md-generator Vitest remained unavailable. One broad exact grep was contained to four manifest-listed hits, and an initial manifest-search regex error was corrected before evidence was used.\n78: - Iteration 008: Code Graph remained unavailable. The first exact search surfaced lineage-local review hits with manifest evidence; no out-of-target code evidence was consumed, and finding anchors were directly re-read.\n79: - Iteration 009: Code Graph remained unavailable. The manifest-path search again surfaced lineage-local review hits, which were discarded; no raw ten-query shadow trace or p95 benchmark artifact exists in the frozen manifest.\n80: - Iteration 010: Code Graph remained unavailable. Green happy-path suites did not cover the reproduced malformed-option or absent-parent status boundaries, and no in-manifest counterevidence closed any active claim.\n81: \n82: ## Exhausted Approaches\n83: \n84: - Runtime moved-path consumer closure is complete for the manifest-listed facade, four corpus consumers, md-generator study seam, and command metadata; do not repeat this exact enumeration without changed evidence.\n85: - Error-propagation and stale-generation fallback classification is complete across the named facade, adapter, child-process, database, and four corpus surfaces; do not repeat without changed implementation or tests.\n86: - Test-to-claim closure is complete for active `P1-001` through `P1-006`; do not repeat the same assertion inventory without changed tests, implementation, or manifest scope.\n87: - Operator happy-path commands, retrieval result fields, default mode, and documented repair semantics are exhausted; do not repeat this matrix without changed evidence. Boundary defects are `P1-007` and `P1-008`.\n88: - Shadow parity/performance claim challenge is complete: comparator semantics, nine-scenario oracle, scale replay, relevance fixtures, timing harness, and packet claims were reviewed; iteration 10 should replay active claims, not reopen discovery.\n89: - Final active-claim stabilization is complete: all ten substantive claims were replayed, the reducer hash collision was repaired append-only, and synthesis is the only remaining action.\n90: \n91: ## 10A. SATURATED / SWEPT DIMENSIONS AND EXPANSION FRONTIER\n92: - Completed pivots: 0\n93: - Failed pivots: 0\n94: - Audited overrides: 0\n95: - Swept: none yet\n96: - Pivot lineage: none yet\n97: - Remaining frontier: none recorded\n98: \n99: ## Ruled Out Directions\n100: \n101: - Bundle-content review is out of scope; byte parity is the only permitted bundle-data question.\n102: - Persistent cutover is intentionally deferred and is not a defect.\n103: - The 012 live include sentinel and 005 Checkpoint B are explicitly deferred and were not converted into findings.\n104: - Historical before/after paths in the 005 migration docs and fixture-local underscore manifest names are intentional evidence/overrides, not active stale interfaces.\n105: - Existing `P1-005` already owns stale generated graph state; iteration 005 did not create or refine a duplicate finding because generator/runtime consumers fall outside the frozen manifest.\n106: \n107: ## Next Focus\n108: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n109: - Dimension: synthesis\n110: - Focus area: synthesize the ten active P1 claims and the two append-only identity-repair supersessions\n111: - Reason: iteration 010 reached `maxIterationsReached` with all substantive claims still supported.\n112: - Rotation status: all configured dimensions and final stabilization are complete; no further LEAF iteration remains.\n113: - Blocked/productive carry-forward: Code Graph remains unavailable; lineage artifacts, direct anchors, and focused-test receipts remain productive for synthesis.\n114: - Required evidence: narrative/state/delta agreement, ten active P1 identities, two identity-only resolutions, and conditional release readiness.\n115: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n116: \n117: ## Known Context\n118: \n119: ### Bounded Context Snapshot\n120: \n121: - Target pointers: `spec.md`, `goal-file-manifest.txt`, five interface command bodies, styles path seam and moved engine/database modules, database operator/schema/retrieval code, their tests, and completion metadata for packets 012/008 and 015/001/005/006.\n122: - Behavior claims: exactly one shared include per interface body, no command-owned taste, moved-module behavioral parity, a single path authority, legacy default without lazy build, absent-generation fail-closed behavior, honest test and completion claims.\n123: - Reuse and conventions: `.opencode/skills/sk-code/code-review/references/review-core.md` severity and evidence doctrine; target packet requirements and acceptance scenarios.\n124: - Risks and gaps: build dispatches had unrestricted workspace permission; Code Graph readiness is absent; memory retrieval returned no canonical packet result; use direct reads, exact search, pinned Git comparisons, and executable tests.\n125: - Resource map: target `resource-map.md` is absent, so the input coverage gate is skipped. Synthesis may still emit a lineage-local review resource map.\n126: \n127: ## Cross-Reference Status\n128: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n129: \n130: | Protocol | Level | Status | Iteration | Notes |\n131: |----------|-------|--------|-----------|-------|\n132: | `spec_code` | core | fail | 003 | Child behavior/test claims largely match; parent phase state is stale and P1-001 remains active. |\n133: | `checklist_evidence` | core | partial | 003 | All in-manifest checklists replayed; 001 checklist is absent from the validated manifest. |\n134: | `feature_catalog_code` | overlay | notApplicable | - | No feature catalog is named in the manifest. |\n135: | `playbook_capability` | overlay | fail | 003 | Mandatory scenarios use removed `_db/` and `_engine/` paths. |\n136: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n137: \n138: ## Files Under Review\n139: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n140: \n141: | Scope | Manifest Lines | Dimensions Reviewed | Last Iteration | Findings | Status |\n142: |-------|----------------|---------------------|----------------|----------|--------|\n143: | Interface command rewrite | 1-27, 89-95 | Correctness | 005 | 0 | consumer-closure-clean |\n144: | Styles library restructure | 12-27, 31-88, 102-108 | Correctness, Maintainability | 005 | 1 P1 | conditional |\n145: | Persistent DB activation | 28-39, 46, 53-64, 73-88, 109-115 | Correctness, Security | 005 | 1 P1 | conditional |\n146: | Cross-packet completion metadata | 89-118 | Traceability, Maintainability | 004 | 3 P1 | conditional |\n147: \n148: The complete ordered scope is the validated 118-entry `.opencode/specs/sk-design/017-remediation-program-review/goal-file-manifest.txt`.\n149: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n150: \n151: ## Review Boundaries\n152: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n153: - Max iterations: 10\n154: - Stop policy: max-iterations\n155: - Convergence threshold: 0.1\n156: - Rolling stop threshold: 0.08\n157: - No-progress threshold: 0.05\n158: - Coverage stabilization passes required: 1\n159: - Session lineage: `fanout-gpt-56-sol-high-1784650021792-031fvi`, generation 1, new\n160: - Findings registry: `deep-review-findings-registry.json`\n161: - Severity threshold: P2\n162: - Review target type: spec-folder\n163: - Core protocols: `spec_code`, `checklist_evidence`\n164: - Overlay protocols: `feature_catalog_code`, `playbook_capability`\n165: - Started: 2026-07-21T16:11:30.000Z\n166: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n167: \n168: <!-- ANCHOR:review-dimensions -->\n169: ## 3. REVIEW DIMENSIONS (remaining)\n170: [All dimensions complete]\n171: \n172: <!-- /ANCHOR:review-dimensions -->\n173: \n174: <!-- ANCHOR:completed-dimensions -->\n175: ## 4. COMPLETED DIMENSIONS\n176: - [x] correctness\n177: - [x] security\n178: - [x] traceability\n179: - [x] maintainability\n180: \n181: <!-- /ANCHOR:completed-dimensions -->\n182: \n183: <!-- ANCHOR:running-findings -->\n184: ## 5. RUNNING FINDINGS\n185: - P0 (Blockers): 0\n186: - P1 (Required): 10\n187: - P2 (Suggestions): 0\n188: - Resolved: 1\n189: \n190: <!-- /ANCHOR:running-findings -->\n191: \n192: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n193: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n194: ### **Bundle-byte review:** not attempted; mechanically moved bundle contents are explicitly out of scope. -- BLOCKED (iteration 1, 1 attempts)\n195: - What was tried: **Bundle-byte review:** not attempted; mechanically moved bundle contents are explicitly out of scope.\n196: - Why blocked: Repeated iteration evidence ruled this direction out.\n197: - Do NOT retry: **Bundle-byte review:** not attempted; mechanically moved bundle contents are explicitly out of scope.\n198: \n199: ### **Lazy query-time database build:** ruled out in sampled facade/adapter paths; query dispatch opens or queries a published database and contains no build call [SOURCE: `.opencode/skills/sk-design/styles/lib/engine/persistent-adapter.mjs:144-165`]. -- BLOC